description: circ_KIAA1429 could accelerate HCC advancement, maintained the expression of Zeb1 through the mechanism of m(6)A-YTHDF3-Zeb1 in HCC.

title: CircMMP11 acts as a ce-circRNA in breast cancer progression by regulating miR-1204.
description: The circMMP11/miR-1204/MMP11 axis regulates breast cancer progression via a competitive endogenous RNA (ceRNA) mechanism. CircMMP11 may serve as a potential therapeutic target in BC.

title: Circular RNA circ-LDLRAD3 serves as an oncogene to promote non-small cell lung cancer progression by upregulating SLC1A5 through sponging miR-137.
description: knock-down of circ-LDLRAD3 inhibited the development of NSCLC by regulating miR-137/SLC1A5 axis.

title: Circular RNA S-7 promotes ovarian cancer EMT via sponging miR-641 to up-regulate ZEB1 and MDM2.
description: CiRS-7 serves as a competing endogenous RNA of miR-641 that promoted cell growth and metastasis in OC, via regulating ZEB1 and MDM2-mediated EMT. High ciRS-7 expression was a poor prognosis of TNM stages, lymph node metastasis status and overall survival rate in OC patients. Targeting ciRS-7/miR-641/ZEB1 or ciRS-7/miR-641/MDM2 axis may be a novel diagnostic, prognostic and therapeutic strategy for OC.

title: circNFATC3 sponges miR-548I acts as a ceRNA to protect NFATC3 itself and suppressed hepatocellular carcinoma progression.
description: both circNFATC3 and NFATC3 were shown to inhibit the phosphorylation of JNK, c-Jun, AKT, and mTOR signaling pathways. Overall, the circNFATC3 can sponge miR-548I to protect NFATC3 itself, then it regulates hepatoma cell function via the JNK, c-Jun, AKT, and mTOR signaling pathways, and the circNFATC3 can be a tumor-repressor on HCC.

title: Sevoflurane Regulates Glioma Progression by Circ_0002755/miR-628-5p/MAGT1 Axis.
description: overexpression of circ_0002755 overturned Sev-mediated inhibitory effect on glioma progression. Further research indicated that circ_0002755 targeted miR-628-5p, and miR-628-5p targeted MAGT1, and Sev modulated glioma progression via circ_0002755/miR-628-5p/MAGT1 axis. Moreover, Sev hindered tumor growth in vivo.

title: Circular RNA Hsa_circ_0066755 as an Oncogene via sponging miR-651 and as a Promising Diagnostic Biomarker for Nasopharyngeal Carcinoma.
description: hsa_circ_0066755 played a role of oncogene in NPC and could be used as an effective diagnostic marker for NPC, and that hsa_circ_0066755 / miR-651 axis also involved in the progression of NPC.

title: Circular RNA hsa-circ-0007766 modulates the progression of Gastric Carcinoma via miR-1233-3p/GDF15 axis.
description: This study unveils a mechanism by which hsa-circ-0007766 regulates GDF15 via hsa-circ-0007766/miR-1233-3p/GDF15 axis, which may provide new insight for GC therapeutic strategies.

title: Circ_0000527 promotes the progression of retinoblastoma by regulating miR-646/LRP6 axis.
description: Circ_0000527 enhances the proliferation and metastasis of RB cells by modulating the miR-646/LRP6 axis.

title: A Novel Circular RNA hsa_circRPPH1_015 Exerts an Oncogenic Role in Breast Cancer by Impairing miRNA-326-Mediated ELK1 Inhibition.
description: hsa_circRPPH1_015 could bind to miRNA-326 that negatively regulates ELK1. Elevation of miRNA-326 expression resulted in inhibition of cell proliferation, colony formation, and cell invasion of MCF-7. Disturbance of miRNA-326 or overexpression of ELK1 restored the proliferation and aggressiveness in hsa_circRPPH1_015-depleted MCF-7 cells.

title: Circular RNA circ_0091579 Promotes Hepatocellular Carcinoma Proliferation, Migration, Invasion, and Glycolysis Through miR-490-5p/CASC3 Axis.
description: circ_0091579 promoted cell proliferation, migration, invasion, and glycolysis partially through miR-490-5p/CASC3 axis in HCC cells.

title: Hsa_circ_0088036 promotes the proliferation and migration of fibroblast-like synoviocytes by sponging miR-140-3p and upregulating SIRT 1 expression in rheumatoid arthritis.
description: circ0088036 may play an essential role in promoting synovial pathogenesis via the circ0088036/miR-140-3p/SIRT 1 axis in RA, providing new insight into circRNAs during RA progression.

title: Circular RNA-9119 suppresses in ovarian cancer cell viability via targeting the microRNA-21-5p-PTEN-Akt pathway.
description: circ9119 could regulate cell proliferation and apoptosis of OC cells via by acting as an miR-21 sponge and targeting the PTEN-Akt pathway.

title: CircHECTD1 up-regulates mucin 1 expression to accelerate hepatocellular carcinoma development by targeting microRNA-485-5p via a competing endogenous RNA mechanism.
description: circHECTD1 facilitates HCC progression by sponging miR-485-5p to up-regulate MUC1.

title: Knockdown of Circ_0081143 Mitigates Hypoxia-Induced Migration, Invasion, and EMT in Gastric Cancer Cells Through the miR-497-5p/EGFR Axis.
description: The present work suggested that circ_0081143 knockdown ameliorated hypoxia-induced migration, invasion, and EMT in GC cells at least partly by the miR-497-5p/EGFR axis, illuminating a novel molecular target for GC treatment.

title: Circular RNA circVEGFC accelerates high glucose-induced vascular endothelial cells apoptosis through miR-338-3p/HIF-1alpha/VEGFA axis.
description: the promotion of circVEGFC/miR-338-3p/HIF-1alpha/VEGFA axis in the HG-induced ECs apoptosis, providing a potential treatment strategy for ECs damage in DM.

title: CircAGFG1 drives metastasis and stemness in colorectal cancer by modulating YY1/CTNNB1.
description: circAGFG1 modulated YY1/CTNNB1 axis to drive metastasis and stemness in CRC by sponging miR-4262 and miR-185-5p.

title: Circular RNA HIPK3 regulates human lens epithelial cell dysfunction by targeting the miR-221-3p/PI3K/AKT pathway in age-related cataract.
description: circHIPK3 protected HLECs from dysfunction by regulating miR-221-3p/PI3K/AKT pathway, indicating a new insight into the pathogenesis of ARC and providing a potential therapeutic target for ARC.

title: Circular RNA Circ_0000064 promotes the proliferation and fibrosis of mesangial cells via miR-143 in diabetic nephropathy.
description: Circular RNA Circ_0000064 promotes the proliferation and fibrosis of mesangial cells via miR-143 in diabetic nephropathy.

title: Hsa-circRNA-103809 Promotes Hepatocellular Carcinoma Development via MicroRNA-1270/PLAG1 Like Zinc Finger 2 Axis.
description: Hsa-circRNA-103809 promoted development of HCC via sequestering miR-1270 and up-regulating PLAGL2.

title: Circular RNA circFANCL motivates the glioma progression via the action on the miR-337-3p/HMGB1 signal axis.
description: Through the illustration of oncogenic function of circFANCL in glioma by the miR-337-3p/HMGB1 axis, we believed that circFANCL might be a great target in the early diagnosis and late treatment of glioma.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0005909 modulates osteosarcoma progression via the miR-936/HMGB1 axis.
description: Circ_0005909 inhibition impeded the progression of OS via downregulating HMGB1 via sponging miR-936.

title: circITGA7 Functions as an Oncogene by Sponging miR-198 and Upregulating FGFR1 Expression in Thyroid Cancer.
description: circITGA7 Functions as an Oncogene by Sponging miR-198 and Upregulating FGFR1 Expression in Thyroid Cancer.

title: Circular RNA_CNST Promotes the Tumorigenesis of Osteosarcoma Cells by Sponging miR-421.
description: circCNST promotes the tumorigenesis of OS cells by sponging miR-421, and provides a potential biomarker for patients with OS.

title: Circular RNA circCTNNA1 promotes colorectal cancer progression by sponging miR-149-5p and regulating FOXM1 expression.
description: circCTNNA1 facilitated CC proliferation and invasion via the circCTNNA1/miR-149-5p/FOXM1 axis, and it might function as a novel diagnostic or therapeutic target for patients with CC.

title: Hsa_circ_0046263 functions as a ceRNA to promote nasopharyngeal carcinoma progression by upregulating IGFBP3.
description: circ-0046263 plays a tumor-promoting role in NPC to enhance malignant behavior through the miR-133a-5p/IGFBP3 axis, which could be a potential target for NPC therapy.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0000073 contributes to osteosarcoma cell proliferation, migration, invasion and methotrexate resistance by sponging miR-145-5p and miR-151-3p and upregulating NRAS.
description: hsa_circ_0000073 facilitated the proliferation, migration, invasion and MTX resistance of OS cells through the inhibition of miR-145-5p and miR-151-3p-mediated downregulation of NRAS.

title: Downregulation of circular RNA hsa_circ_0000735 boosts prostate cancer sensitivity to docetaxel via sponging miR-7.
description: Hsa_circ_0000735 downregulation boosted PCa sensitivity to DTX and reduced tumor growth via sponging miR-7, providing a promising prognostic biomarker and therapeutic target for PCa.

title: Circular RNA ITCH suppresses proliferation, invasion, and glycolysis of ovarian cancer cells by up-regulating CDH1 via sponging miR-106a.
description: Circ-ITCH suppressed proliferation, invasion, glycolysis, and promoted apoptosis of ovarian cancer cells by modulating the miR-106a/CDH1 axis.

title: Knockdown of Circ_CCNB2 Sensitizes Prostate Cancer to Radiation Through Repressing Autophagy by the miR-30b-5p/KIF18A Axis.
description: knockdown of circ_CCNB2 was shown to promote PCa radiosensitivity through autophagy repression by miR-30b-5p/KIF18A axis, developing a molecular resistance mechanism of PCa radiotherapy and a feasible strategy to increase radiosensitivity.

title: Circular RNA DHX33 promotes malignant behavior in ccRCC by targeting miR-489-3p/MEK1 axis.
description: circDHX33 plays a role in promoting ccRCC via the miR-489-3p/MEK1 axis and may serve as a novel therapeutic target for the treatment of ccRCC patients.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0076690 acts as a prognostic biomarker in osteoporosis and regulates osteogenic differentiation of hBMSCs via sponging miR-152.
description: hsa_circ_0076690 may act as a potential diagnostic biomarker for osteoporosis patients and hsa_circ_0076690 could regulate osteogenic differentiation of hBMSCs via sponging miR-152.

title: Circular RNA circREPS2 Acts as a Sponge of miR-558 to Suppress Gastric Cancer Progression by Regulating RUNX3/beta-catenin Signaling.
description: circREPS2 suppresses the progression of GC via miR-558/RUNX3/beta-catenin signaling and is a novel promising biomarker and target for GC treatment.

title: CircKIAA0907 Retards Cell Growth, Cell Cycle, and Autophagy of Gastric Cancer In Vitro and Inhibits Tumorigenesis In Vivo via the miR-452-5p/KAT6B Axis.
description: CircKIAA0907 Retards Cell Growth, Cell Cycle, and Autophagy of Gastric Cancer In Vitro and Inhibits Tumorigenesis In Vivo via the miR-452-5p/KAT6B Axis.

title: Circular RNA SFMBT2 Inhibits the Proliferation and Metastasis of Glioma Cells Through Mir-182-5p/Mtss1 Pathway.
description: circRNA Scm like with 4 Mbt domains 2/microRNA-182-5p/metastasis suppressor 1 axis could be a putative therapeutic target for the treatment of patients with glioma.

title: Circular RNA circ_001842 plays an oncogenic role in renal cell carcinoma by disrupting microRNA-502-5p-mediated inhibition of SLC39A14.
description: circ_001842 in RCC pathogenesis through a miR-502-5p-dependent SLC39A14 mechanism, suggesting circ_001842 is a potential target for RCC treatment.

title: A novel circRNA, circNUP98, a potential biomarker, acted as an oncogene via the miR-567/ PRDX3 axis in renal cell carcinoma.
description: silencing of circ NUP98 inhibited RCC progression by down-regulating of PRDX3 via up-regulation of miR-567. Furthermore, STAT3 was identified as an inducer of circ NUP98 in RCC cells. CircNUP98 acts as an oncogene by a novel STAT3/circ NUP98/miR-567/PRDX3 axis, which may provide a potential biomarker and therapeutic target for the treatment of RCC.

title: Circ_0000105 promotes liver cancer by regulating miR-498/PIK3R1.
description: Circ_0000105 overexpression promoted liver cancer cell proliferation and inhibited apoptosis, whereas knocking down circ_0000105 triggered the opposite effect. miR-498 was a downstream target of circ_0000105, inhibiting liver cancer cell proliferation and promoting apoptosis. Mechanistically, circ_0000105 indirectly up-regulated the expression of PIK3R1 by adsorbing miR-498.

title: Circular RNA 000554 represses epithelial-mesenchymal transition in breast cancer by regulating microRNA-182/ZFP36 axis.
description: circRNA_000554 functioned as an inhibitor of EMT in BC and suggests a molecular mechanism that circRNA_000554 bound to miR-182 to upregulate ZFP36 in this process.

title: Circular RNA MTO1 Inhibits the Proliferation and Invasion of Ovarian Cancer Cells Through the miR-182-5p/KLF15 Axis.
description: Upregulation of circMTO1 inhibited proliferation and invasion of ovarian cancer cells while downregulation of circMTO1 promoted these processes. Mechanistically, we showed that circMTO1 sponged miR-182-5p to support KLF15 expression, eventually leading to inhibition of ovarian cancer progression.

title: Circular RNA circFAT1(e2) Promotes Osteosarcoma Progression and Metastasis by Sponging miR-181b and Regulating HK2 Expression.
description: circFAT1(e2) exerted oncogenic roles in OS and suggested the circFAT1(e2)/miR-181b/HK2 axis might be a potential therapeutic target.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0001588 promotes the malignant progression of lung adenocarcinoma by modulating miR-524-3p/NACC1 signaling.
description: hsa_circ_0001588 upregulated the expression of NACC1 by combining with miR-524-3p to promote the proliferation, migration, and invasion of lung adenocarcinoma cells, suggesting that hsa_circ_0001588 may be an underlying therapeutic target for lung adenocarcinoma.

title: Circular RNA PRKCI silencing represses esophageal cancer progression and elevates cell radiosensitivity through regulating the miR-186-5p/PARP9 axis.
description: CircPRKCI regulated cell malignancy and radioresistance through modulating the miR-186-5p /PARP9 axis in EC, which provided a might target for EC treatment.

title: Circular RNA circ-CPA4/ let-7 miRNA/PD-L1 axis regulates cell growth, stemness, drug resistance and immune evasion in non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC).
description: circ-CPA4 regulated cell growth, mobility, stemness and drug resistance in NSCLC cells and inactivated CD8(+) T cells in the tumor immune microenvironment through let-7 miRNA/PD-L1 axis.

title: Circular RNA MYLK Promotes Glycolysis and Proliferation of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Cells by Sponging miR-195-5p and Increasing Glucose Transporter Member 3 Expression.
description: Circular RNA MYLK Promotes Glycolysis and Proliferation of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Cells by Sponging miR-195-5p and Increasing Glucose Transporter Member 3 Expression.

title: Circular RNA Circ_0016760 Modulates Non-Small-Cell Lung Cancer Growth Through the miR-577/ZBTB7A Axis.
description: Circ_0016760 and ZBTB7A were upregulated and miR-577 was downregulated in NSCLC tissues and cells. Circ_0016760 exhaustion curbed the colony formation, migration, invasion, and ECAR of NSCLC cells in vitro and impeded tumor growth in vivo.Circ_0016760 silencing impeded NSCLC advancement through regulation of the miR-577/ZBTB7A axis.

title: circIQCH sponges miR-145 to promote breast cancer progression by upregulating DNMT3A expression.
description: our study demonstrated the pivotal role of circIQCH-miR-145-DNMT3A axis in breast cancer growth and metastasis via the mechanism of competing endogenous RNAs. Thus, circIQCH could be a potential therapeutic target for breast cancer.

title: Exosomes Mediated Transfer of Circ_UBE2D2 Enhances the Resistance of Breast Cancer to Tamoxifen by Binding to MiR-200a-3p.
description: Exosomes mediated transfer of circ_UBE2D2 reinforced tamoxifen resistance in breast cancer by binding to miR-200a-3p, providing new insights into the boost of the effectiveness of tamoxifen on breast cancer patients.

title: Circ_0109291 Promotes Cisplatin Resistance of Oral Squamous Cell Carcinoma by Sponging miR-188-3p to Increase ABCB1 Expression.
description: Circ_0109291 could promote the DDP resistance of OSCC, suggesting that silenced circ_0109291 might be a key step to inhibit OSCC resistance.

title: Circular RNA UBAP2 contributes to tumor growth and metastasis of cervical cancer via modulating miR-361-3p/SOX4 axis.
description: CircUBAP2 represents a prognostic marker and contributes to tumor growth and metastasis via modulating miR-361-3p/SOX4 axis in CC, which indicates a potential therapeutic target for CC treatment.

title: The Circular RNA CDR1as Regulates the Proliferation and Apoptosis of Human Cardiomyocytes Through the miR-135a/HMOX1 and miR-135b/HMOX1 Axes.
description: CDR1as is a potential biomarker of CHF that is mechanistically involved in the disease pathogenesis and participates in regulating the occurrence and development of CHF through the miR-135a/HMOX1 and miR-135b/HMOX1 signaling axes.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0096157 contributes to cisplatin resistance by proliferation, cell cycle progression, and suppressing apoptosis of non-small-cell lung carcinoma cells.
description: increased hsa_circ_0096157 expression contributed to DDP resistance in NSCLC cells by promoting cell proliferation, migration, invasion and cell cycle progression and inhibiting apoptosis.

title: Circ_0068655 Promotes Cardiomyocyte Apoptosis via miR-498/PAWR Axis.
description: the expression of circ_0068655 can promote cardiomyocyte apoptosis through the modulation of miR-498-PAWR axis in vitro, which highlights the diagnostic and therapeutic value of circ_0068655 in patients with MI.

title: Low expression of CircRNA HIPK3 promotes osteoarthritis chondrocyte apoptosis by serving as a sponge of miR-124 to regulate SOX8.
description: Our results demonstrated that CircHIPK3 was significantly upregulated in OA cartilage tissue and cells. Low expression of CircHIPK3 promoted the apoptosis of OA chondrocytes by promoting miR-124 to suppress SOX8 expression. The molecular mechanism of CircHIPK3 in present study is expected to provide new ideas for the treatment of osteoarthritis.

title: Circular RNA CirCHIPK3 promotes cell proliferation and invasion of breast cancer by sponging miR-193a/HMGB1/PI3K/AKT axis.
description: CirCHIPK3 regulated miR-193a/HMGB1/PI3K/AKT signaling to facilitate BC development and progression, providing a novel therapeutic target for BC.

title: Circ0061052 regulation of FoxC1/Snail pathway via miR-515-5p is involved in the epithelial-mesenchymal transition of epithelial cells during cigarette smoke-induced airway remodeling.
description: by regulating miR-515-5p through a FoxC1/Snail regulatory axis, circ0061052 is involved in the CS-induced EMT and airway remodeling in COPD.

title: Circular RNA YAP1 attenuates osteoporosis through up-regulation of YAP1 and activation of Wnt/beta-catenin pathway.
description: It was firstly uncovered in present study that circ_0024097 attenuated osteoporosis through promoting osteogenic differentiation via miR-376b-3p/YAP1 axis and Wnt/beta-catenin pathway.

title: Circ_0067934 promotes non-small cell lung cancer development by regulating miR-1182/KLF8 axis and activating Wnt/beta-catenin pathway.
description: Circ_0067934 acted as a competing endogenous RNA to facilitate NSCLC progression by regulating the miR-1182/KLF8 axis and activating Wnt/beta-catenin pathway.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0000517 modulates hepatocellular carcinoma advancement via the miR-326/SMAD6 axis.
description: Hsa_circ_0000517 depletion repressed HCC advancement via regulating the miR-326/SMAD6 axis.

title: CircPOSTN/miR-361-5p/TPX2 axis regulates cell growth, apoptosis and aerobic glycolysis in glioma cells.
description: circPOSTN regulated cell growth, apoptosis, and aerobic glycolysis in glioma through miR-361-5p/TPX2 axis.

title: Circular RNA circMAGI3 accelerates the glycolysis of non-small cell lung cancer through miR-515-5p/HDGF.
description: circMAGI3 promoted the glycolysis and proliferation of NSCLC cells. Mechanistically, circMAGI3 functioned as a sponge for miR-515-5p to relieve its target gene HDGF expression, thereby accelerating the glycolysis of NSCLC.

title: Circular RNA circHIPK3 Promotes Cell Metastasis through miR-637/STAT3 Axis in Osteosarcoma.
description: our research uncovered an important role of the circHIPK3/miR-637/STAT3 pathway in the migration and invasion of OS cells and suggested that circHIPK3 may be a prognostic marker and a promising therapeutic target for OS.

title: Downregulated circular RNA zRANB1 mediates Wnt5a/beta-Catenin signaling to promote neuropathic pain via miR-24-3p/LPAR3 axis in CCI rat models.
description: cZRNAB1 regulated Wnt5a/beta-Catenin Signaling expression via miR-24-3p/LPAR3 axis in CCI rat models.

title: circRACGAP1 promotes non-small cell lung cancer proliferation by regulating miR-144-5p/CDKL1 signaling pathway.
description: our study revealed a novel machinery of circRACGAP1/miR-144-5p/CDKL1 for the NSCLC tumorigenesis and development, providing potential diagnostic and therapeutic targets for NSCLC.

title: Silencing hsa_circRNA_0008035 exerted repressive function on osteosarcoma cell growth and migration by upregulating microRNA-375.
description: silencing hsa_circRNA_0008035 exerted repressive function on OSA cell growth and migration and Notch pathway by accelerating miR-375.

title: A Regulatory Axis of circ_0008193/miR-1180-3p/TRIM62 Suppresses Proliferation, Migration, Invasion, and Warburg Effect in Lung Adenocarcinoma Cells Under Hypoxia.
description: Upregulating circ_0008193 inhibited LUAD cell proliferation, migration, invasion, and Warburg effect under hypoxia in vitro and in vivo through regulation of the miR-1180-3p/TRIM62 axis.

title: Circ_0007841 promotes the progression of multiple myeloma through targeting miR-338-3p/BRD4 signaling cascade.
description: Circ_0007841 acted as an oncogene to promote the proliferation, cell cycle and motility and restrain the apoptosis of MM cells through sequestering miR-338-3p to up-regulate the expression of BRD4.

title: Effects of the circ_101238/miR-138-5p/CDK6 axis on proliferation and apoptosis keloid fibroblasts.
description: circ_101238 may serve as a promising therapeutic candidate for keloid therapy and that circ_101238/miR-138-5p/CDK6 signaling has the potential to regulate the growth of keloid fibroblasts.

title: Serum-Derived Exosomes-Mediated Circular RNA ARHGAP10 Modulates the Progression of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Through the miR-638/FAM83F Axis.
description: Inhibition of serum-derived exosomes-mediated circARHGAP10 curbed NSCLC progression through the miR-638/FAM83F axis.

title: Circular RNA hsa_Circ_101141 as a Competing Endogenous RNA Facilitates Tumorigenesis of Hepatocellular Carcinoma by Regulating miR-1297/ROCK1 Pathway.
description: circRNA circ_101141 acted as a ceRNA to facilitate tumorigenesis of HCC by regulating miR-1297/ROCK1 pathway.

title: Interference with circBC048201 inhibits the proliferation, migration, and invasion of bladder cancer cells through the miR-1184/ITGA3 axis.
description: circBC048201 was abnormally highly expressed in bladder cancer tissues and cells, and the interference with circBC048201 inhibited the proliferation, migration, and invasion of bladder cancer cells through the miR-1184/ITGA3 axis.

title: CircRSF1 contributes to endothelial cell growth, migration and tube formation under ox-LDL stress through regulating miR-758/CCND2 axis.
description: CircRSF1 could protect against ox-LDL-induced endothelial cell injury in vitro via miR-758/CCND2 axis, suggesting circRSF1 as a potential target for the treatment of atherosclerosis.

title: Circular RNA circTNPO3 Regulates Paclitaxel Resistance of Ovarian Cancer Cells by miR-1299/NEK2 Signaling Pathway.
description: circTNPO3 contributed to PTX resistance of OC cells at least partly through upregulating NEK2 expression by sponging miR-1299. circTNPO3/miR-1299/NEK2 signaling pathway might play vital roles in the tumorigenesis and chemoresistance of OC.

title: The circular RNA circ-GRB10 participates in the molecular circuitry inhibiting human intervertebral disc degeneration.
description: circ-GBR10 participates in the molecular circuitry that controls human IDD development. These findings provide a basis for further functional, diagnostic and therapeutic studies of circ-GRB10 in IDD.

title: Circular RNA DGKB Promotes the Progression of Neuroblastoma by Targeting miR-873/GLI1 Axis.
description: our work proved that circDGKB promoted NB progression via targeting miR-873/GLI1 axis in vitro and in vivo. Our study provided a new target for NB treatment and indicated that circDGKB could act as a novel diagnostic marker for NB.

title: Circular RNA circ-SLC7A6 acts as a tumor suppressor in non-small cell lung cancer through abundantly sponging miR-21.
description: circ-SLC7A6 is a novel tumor suppressor in NSCLC, targeting circ-SLC7A6/miR-21 axis may be a promising treatment for NSCLC patients.

title: Hsa_circ_0029589 knockdown inhibits the proliferation, migration and invasion of vascular smooth muscle cells via regulating miR-214-3p and STIM1.
description: Circ_0029589 knockdown repressed proliferation, migration and invasion of VSMCs challenged via ox-LDL by regulating miR-214-3p and STIM1, indicating that circ_0029589 might play important role in atherosclerosis.

title: Circular noncoding RNA circMBOAT2 is a novel tumor marker and regulates proliferation/migration by sponging miR-519d-3p in colorectal cancer.
description: circMBOAT2 regulated cell proliferation and migration by competitively binding to miR-519d-3p and targeting troponin-associated protein (TROAP) in CRC cells.

title: Circ_WBSCR17 aggravates inflammatory responses and fibrosis by targeting miR-185-5p/SOX6 regulatory axis in high glucose-induced human kidney tubular cells.
description: Circ_WBSCR17 triggered the dysfunction of HG-induced HK-2 cells, including inflammatory responses and fibrosis, which was accomplished via the miR-185-5p/SOX6 regulatory axis.

title: CircTADA2A suppresses the progression of colorectal cancer via miR-374a-3p/KLF14 axis.
description: CircTADA2A functioned as a tumor suppressor in CRC to inhibit the glycolysis and cell cycle and potentiate the apoptosis of CRC cells via miR-374a-3p/KLF14 axis.

title: CircZNF609 is involved in the pathogenesis of focal segmental glomerulosclerosis by sponging miR-615-5p.
description: circZNF609 may play an important role in FSGS by sponging miR-615-5p.

title: CircPlekha7 plays an anti-fibrotic role in intrauterine adhesions by modulating endometrial stromal cell proliferation and apoptosis.
description: circPlekha7 plays an anti-fibrotic role in IUA and may serve as a promising prognostic biomarker for patients with IUA. Therefore, overexpression of circPlekha7 could be a potential treatment strategy for IUA.

title: Circular RNA circLPAR3 Facilitates Esophageal Squamous Cell Carcinoma Progression Through Upregulating HMGB1 via Sponging miR-375/miR-433.
description: CircLPAR3 might play an oncogenic role in ESCC through sponging miR-375/miR-433 to promote HMGB1 expression, which might provide a theoretical basis for circLPAR3 to become a biomarker for ESCC therapy.

title: Circular RNA ZNF609 Promoted Hepatocellular Carcinoma Progression by Upregulating PAP2C Expression via Sponging miR-342-3p.
description: CircZNF609 was highly expressed in HCC tissues and driven HCC progression by sponging miR-342-3p and upregulating RAP2C. This study may provide new potential therapeutic targets for HCC treatment.

title: CircEPSTI1 Promotes the Progression of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Through miR-145/HMGB3 Axis.
description: CircEPSTI1 aggravated the progression of NSCLC through elevating the expression of HMGB3 via sponging miR-145.

title: Circ_0046599 Promotes the Development of Hepatocellular Carcinoma by Regulating the miR-1258/RPN2 Network.
description: Our results provided new evidence that circ_0046599 could promote the progression of HCC by increasing RPN2 expression via sponging miR-1258.

title: A novel circular RNA hsa_circ_0060927 may serve as a potential diagnostic biomarker for human colorectal cancer.
description: the results of our study illustrated the expression levels hsa_circ_0060927 in CRC; however, further studies are required to validate the present results.

title: Up-regulation of circular RNA hsa_circ_01844 induces apoptosis and suppresses proliferation and migration of glioblastoma cells.
description: Hsa_circ_01844 shows decreased expression in glioblastoma and its overexpression induces apoptosis and inhibits proliferation, migration, and invasion of glioblastoma cells.

title: Circ-SMARCA5 suppresses colorectal cancer progression via downregulating miR-39-3p and upregulating ARID4B.
description: Circ-SMARCA5 functions as a tumor suppressor by upregulating ARID4B expression via sponging miR-39-3p, and thereby inhibited CRC progression.

title: Circulating exosomal circFoxp1 confers cisplatin resistance in epithelial ovarian cancer cells.
description: circFoxp1 is an oncogene in EOC cells and can confer DDP resistance to EOC cells. Circulating exosomal circFoxp1 can be used as a biomarker and potential therapeutic target for EOC.

title: CircIL4R facilitates the tumorigenesis and inhibits ferroptosis in hepatocellular carcinoma by regulating the miR-541-3p/GPX4 axis.
description: CircIL4R played an oncogenic role in HCC via the miR-541-3p/GPX4 axis in vivo. Our data suggested that circIL4R served for a tumor promoter and ferroptosis inhibitor in HCC by the miR-541-3p/GPX4 network.

title: Circular RNA PRMT5 confers cisplatin-resistance via miR-4458/REV3L axis in non-small-cell lung cancer.
description: Circ-PRMT5 promoted DDP resistance via REV3L by sponging miR-4458 in NSCLC, thus providing a novel therapeutic strategy for patients with NSCLC.

title: Hypoxia inducible factor-1 (HIF-1alpha) reduced inflammation in spinal cord injury via miR-380-3p/ NLRP3 by Circ 0001723.
description: We concluded that HIF-1alpha reduced inflammation in spinal cord injury via miR-380-3p/ NLRP3 by Circ 0001723.

title: CircHIPK3 Promotes Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma (ccRCC) Cells Proliferation and Metastasis via Altering of miR-508-3p/CXCL13 Signal.
description: circHIPK3 promoted ccRCC cell proliferation and metastasis by altering miR-5083p/CXCL13 signaling. The present findings might provide a novel target for the molecular treatment of ccRCC.

title: Knockdown of circ_0000512 Inhibits Cell Proliferation and Promotes Apoptosis in Colorectal Cancer by Regulating miR-296-5p/RUNX1 Axis.
description: Knockdown of circ_0000512 inhibited cell proliferation and induced apoptosis in CRC cell by regulating miR-296-5p/RUNX1 axis, which might provide a potential therapeutic target for CRC treatment.

title: circ_0136666 Facilitates the Progression of Colorectal Cancer via miR-383/CREB1 Axis.
description: circ_0136666 deteriorated CRC through miR-383/CREB1 axis. circ_0136666/miR-383/CREB1 axis might be an underlying therapeutic target for CRC therapy.

title: Analysis of Circular RNAs in the Coronary Arteries of Patients with Kawasaki Disease.
description: For circWHAMMP1 and circZNF124, the microRNAs that may be regulated by these circRNAs were also identified.

title: Analysis of Circular RNAs in the Coronary Arteries of Patients with Kawasaki Disease.
description: For circWHAMMP1 and circZNF124, the microRNAs that may be regulated by these circRNAs were also identified.

title: Hsa_circ_0008934 promotes the proliferation and migration of osteosarcoma cells by targeting miR-145-5p to enhance E2F3 expression.
description: Elevated hsa_circ_0008934 expression promotes the proliferation and migration of osteosarcoma cells by sponging miR-145-5p to enhance E2F3 expression.

title: Circ_0000218 plays a carcinogenic role in laryngeal cancer through regulating microRNA-139-3p/Smad3 axis.
description: Circ_0000218 inhibition inhibited the growth of LSCC by targeting miR-139-3p/Smad3 axis.

title: Circular RNA VMA21 ameliorates sepsis-associated acute kidney injury by regulating miR-9-3p/SMG1/inflammation axis and oxidative stress.
description: Circular RNA VMA21 ameliorates sepsis-associated acute kidney injury by regulating miR-9-3p/SMG1/inflammation axis and oxidative stress.

title: Circ_0010220-mediated miR-503-5p/CDCA4 axis contributes to osteosarcoma progression tumorigenesis.
description: circ_0010220 can be an important biomarker for osteosarcoma via regulating miR-503-5p and CDCA4.

title: CircZNF609 aggravates neuropathic pain via miR-22-3p/ENO1 axis in CCI rat models.
description: circZNF609 promoted inflammation factors expression to aggravate neuropathic pain progression via miR-22-3p/ENO1 axis in CCI rat models.

title: Downregulation of circEPSTI1 represses the proliferation and invasion of non-small cell lung cancer by inhibiting TRIM24 via miR-1248 upregulation.
description: downregulation of circEPSTI1 represses the proliferation and invasion of NSCLC by inhibiting TRIM24 via miR-1248 upregulation.

title: Circular RNA has circ 0001591 promoted cell proliferation and metastasis of human melanoma via ROCK1/PI3K/AKT by targeting miR-431-5p.
description: circ 0001591 inhibits the progression of human melanoma through ROCK1/PI3K/AKT signal pathway by targeting ROCK1 by miR-431-5p.

title: Circular RNA SIPA1L1 promotes osteogenesis via regulating the miR-617/Smad3 axis in dental pulp stem cells.
description: CircRNASIPA1L1 promotes osteogenesis of DPSCs by adsorbing miR-617 and further targeting Smad3.

title: Circular RNA circ_0020123 promotes non-small cell lung cancer progression by sponging miR-590-5p to regulate THBS2.
description: Circular RNA circ_0020123 regulated THBS2 by sponging miR-590-5p to promote cell proliferation and migration and inhibit cell apoptosis in NSCLC cells.

title: FOXA1-induced circOSBPL10 potentiates cervical cancer cell proliferation and migration through miR-1179/UBE2Q1 axis.
description: FOXA1-induced circOSBPL10 facilitates CC progression through miR-1179/UBE2Q1 axis, highlighting a strong potential for circOSBPL10 to serve as a promising therapeutic target in CC.

title: CircZFR functions as a sponge of miR-578 to promote breast cancer progression by regulating HIF1A expression.
description: the silencing of circZFR suppressed BC malignant progression in vitro via the regulation of the miR-578/HIF1A axis, providing evidence for the crucial involvement of circZFR in BC pathogenesis.

title: Knockdown of circHIPK3 Facilitates Temozolomide Sensitivity in Glioma by Regulating Cellular Behaviors Through miR-524-5p/KIF2A-Mediated PI3K/AKT Pathway.
description: Knockdown of circHIPK3 promoted TMZ sensitivity in glioma by modulating proliferation, metastasis, and apoptosis through miR-524-5p/KIF2A-mediated PI3K/AKT pathway. CircHIPK3 may be the potential target for the diagnosis and therapy of TMZ-resistant glioma.

title: Circ_0011292 Enhances Paclitaxel Resistance in Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer by Regulating miR-379-5p/TRIM65 Axis.
description: Circ_0011292 facilitated tumorigenesis and PTX resistance in NSCLC by regulating the miR-379-5p/TRIM65 axis, suggesting that circ_0011292 was a promising therapeutic target for NSCLC chemotherapy.

title: Circ_0079593 facilitates proliferation, metastasis, glucose metabolism and inhibits apoptosis in melanoma by regulating the miR-516b/GRM3 axis.
description: circ_0079593 accelerated melanoma progression via upregulating GRM3 by sponging miR-516b, which suggested that circ_0079593 had the potential to be a new therapeutic biomarker for melanoma.

title: [Effect of circular RNA hsa_circ_0008898 on oral squamous cell carcinoma and its mechanism].
description: Knockdown of hsa_circ_0008898 inhibited OSCC cells proliferation, cloning, migration and invasion and induced cell cycle arrest in vitro by regulating the miR-197-5p/RHOA. Additionally, Knockdown of hsa_circ_0008898 also inhibited tumor formation of OSCC cells in vivo.

title: Circular RNA has_circ_0000034 accelerates retinoblastoma advancement through the miR-361-3p/ADAM19 axis.
description: ADAM19 overexpression abolished the influence of miR-361-3p mimic on viability, migration, invasion, apoptosis, and EMT of RB cells. Circ_0000034 expedited RB progression through upregulating ADAM19 via sponging miR-361-3p, which indicated that circ_0000034 might a target for RB therapy.

title: CircRNA hsa_circ_0002577 accelerates endometrial cancer progression through activating IGF1R/PI3K/Akt pathway.
description: circRNA hsa_circ_002577 accelerated EC progression by acting as a miR-625-5p sponge, upregulating IGF1R and activating the PI3K/Akt pathway, suggesting the potential therapeutic use of hsa_circ_002577 in EC treatment.

title: Rno_circ_0005139 regulates apoptosis by targeting Wnt5a in rat anorectal malformations.
description: Rno_circ_0005139 influences cell proliferation and apoptosis by acting as a miR-324-3p sponge, thereby downregulating Wnt5a in ARM. Accordingly, rno_circ_0005139, miR-324-3p, and Wnt5a could be targeted therapeutic factors for ARM.

title: The Potential Tumor Promotional Role of circVAPA in Retinoblastoma via Regulating miR-615-3p and SMARCE1.
description: circVAPA promoted RB proliferation and metastasis by sponging miR-615-3p, thereby upregulating SMARCE1. CircVAPA was a potential biomarker for Rb therapy.

title: Circular RNA MAT2B Induces Colorectal Cancer Proliferation via Sponging miR-610, Resulting in an Increased E2F1 Expression.
description: circMAT2B promoted CRC proliferation by regulating the miR-610/E2F1 axis, which may serve as a potential therapeutic target for CRC treatment.

title: Circular RNA circNHSL1 Contributes to Gastric Cancer Progression Through the miR-149-5p/YWHAZ Axis.
description: circNHSL1 knockdown repressed migration, invasion, and glutaminolysis in vitro and inhibited tumor growth in vivo by miR-149-5p/YWHAZ axis in GC, implying an underlying circRNA-targeted therapy for GC treatment.

title: Circular RNA 103862 Promotes Proliferation and Invasion of Laryngeal Squamous Cell Carcinoma Cells Through the miR-493-5p/GOLM1 Axis.
description: circRNA_103862 promotes the proliferation of LSCC through targeting the miR-493-5p/GOLM1 axis, and it might serve as a potential prognosis marker and therapy target for LSCC.

title: Circular RNA cMTO1 Promotes PTEN Expression Through Sponging miR-181b-5p in Liver Fibrosis.
description: cMTO1 inhibits HSC activation, at least in part, through miR-181b-5p-mediated PTEN expression. Our results also suggest that cMTO1 may be a novel therapeutic target in liver fibrosis.

title: Circular RNA circCCDC66 Contributes to Malignant Phenotype of Osteosarcoma by Sponging miR-338-3p to Upregulate the Expression of PTP1B.
description: circCCDC66 contributed to malignant behaviors of OS cells by miR-338-3p/PTP1B pathway, which suggested circCCDC66/miR-338-3p/PTP1B axis might be a potential therapeutic target.

title: Circular RNA circ_0026359 Enhances Cisplatin Resistance in Gastric Cancer via Targeting miR-1200/POLD4 Pathway.
description: miR-1200/POLD4 pathway mediated the promoting role of circ_0026359 in CDDP resistance of gastric cancer. circ_0026359 could be used as a potential target for CDDP-resistant gastric cancer therapy.

title: circ_0037128/miR-17-3p/AKT3 axis promotes the development of diabetic nephropathy.
description: we have characterized the function of a novel circ_0037128 and illustrated the significance of circ_0037128-miR-17-3p-AKT3 axis in DN pathogenesis.

title: Circular RNA circ_0029589 regulates proliferation, migration, invasion, and apoptosis in ox-LDL-stimulated VSMCs by regulating miR-424-5p/IGF2 axis.
description: Circ_0029589 silence might inhibit the progression of AS by regulating miR-424-5p/IGF2 axis, providing a novel mechanism for pathogenesis of AS.

title: Circular RNA circ_0000517 regulates hepatocellular carcinoma development via miR-326/IGF1R axis.
description: Circ_0000517 knockdown repressed hepatocellular carcinoma development in vitro and in vivo by modulating miR-326 and IGF1R.

title: Circ_0000140 restrains the proliferation, metastasis and glycolysis metabolism of oral squamous cell carcinoma through upregulating CDC73 via sponging miR-182-5p.
description: Circ_0000140 restrains the proliferation, metastasis and glycolysis metabolism of oral squamous cell carcinoma through upregulating CDC73 via sponging miR-182-5p.

title: Circ_0007031 enhances tumor progression and promotes 5-fluorouracil resistance in colorectal cancer through regulating miR-133b/ABCC5 axis.
description: Our current work had led to the identification of circ_0007031 knockdown that repressed CRC cell malignant progression and enhanced 5-FU sensitivity via regulating ABCC5 expression by sponging miR-133b.

title: CircDHDDS/miR-361-3p/WNT3A Axis Promotes the Development of Retinoblastoma by Regulating Proliferation, Cell Cycle, Migration, and Invasion of Retinoblastoma Cells.
description: circDHDDS/miR-361-3p/WNT3A axis stimulated the development of RB by regulation of proliferation, cell cycle program, migration, and invasion of RB cells.

title: The circRNA circ_0000291 acts as a sponge of microRNA 326 to regulate E26 transformation-specific sequence-1 expression and promote breast cancer progression.
description: Circ_0000291 is the novel oncogenic circRNA and promotes BC progression via modulating the miR-326/ETS1 axis.

title: hsa_circ_0003738 Inhibits the Suppressive Function of Tregs by Targeting miR-562/IL-17A and miR-490-5p/IFN-gamma Signaling Pathway.
description: upregulated circ_0003738 decreased the suppressive function of psoriatic Tregs via the miR-562/IL17RA and miR-490-5p/IFNGR2 (IFN-gamma receptor 2) axis, which indicated the involvement of circRNAs in the pathogenesis of dysfunctional Tregs. These findings will provide new therapeutic targets for the treatment of psoriasis.

title: CircRNA circ_0072995 promotes the progression of epithelial ovarian cancer by modulating miR-147a/CDK6 axis.
description: CircRNA circ_0072995 promotes the progression of epithelial ovarian cancer by modulating miR-147a/CDK6 axis.

title: hsa_circRNA_001587 upregulates SLC4A4 expression to inhibit migration, invasion, and angiogenesis of pancreatic cancer cells via binding to microRNA-223.
description: hsa_circRNA_001587 upregulates SLC4A4 expression to inhibit migration, invasion, and angiogenesis of pancreatic cancer cells via binding to microRNA-223.

title: Circular RNA circEXOC6B Inhibits the Progression of Ovarian Cancer by Sponging miR-421 and Regulating RUS1 Expression.
description: we found that circEXOC6B suppressed the growth of ovarian cancer cells through upregulating RSU1 partially via sponging miR-421. Therefore, circEXOC6B might be a potential target for the treatment of ovarian cancer.

title: Blocking circ_0013912 Suppressed Cell Growth, Migration and Invasion of Pancreatic Ductal Adenocarcinoma Cells in vitro and in vivo Partially Through Sponging miR-7-5p.
description: Circ_0013912 knockdown could suppress cell growth and metastasis of PDAC cells via sponging miR-7-5p.

title: Circ_0015756 Aggravates Hepatocellular Carcinoma Development by Regulating FGFR1 via Sponging miR-610.
description: Circ_0015756 played its tumorigenic properties in HCC by activating FGFR1 via sponging miR-610, and circ_0015756 was expected to be a vital indicator in HCC diagnosis and treatment.

title: Identification of circular RNA hsa_circ_0044556 and its effect on the progression of colorectal cancer.
description: Hsa_circ_0044556 promoted the progression of CRC. It is possible that hsa_circ_0044556 will become a novel biomarker or therapeutic target for CRC.

title: Circular RNA HIPK3 exacerbates diabetic nephropathy and promotes proliferation by sponging miR-185.
description: circHIPK3 exhibits a promotive function in DN by sponging miR-185 and this evidence suggests that circHIPK3 might be a biomarker or therapeutic target for DN.

title: Circular RNA circ_0007142 regulates cell proliferation, apoptosis, migration and invasion via miR-455-5p/SGK1 axis in colorectal cancer.
description: Circ_0007142/miR-455-5p/SGK1 axis regulated cell proliferation, apoptosis, migration and invasion of CRC cells, providing a probable therapy target for CRC.

title: Circ_0000144 facilitates the progression of thyroid cancer via the miR-217/AKT3 pathway.
description: Circ_0000144 exerts a cancer-promoting effect on TC cells via the miR-217/AKT3 pathway.

title: Circular RNA Circ_0000442 acts as a sponge of MiR-148b-3p to suppress breast cancer via PTEN/PI3K/Akt signaling pathway.
description: Circular RNA Circ_0000442 acts as a sponge of MiR-148b-3p to suppress breast cancer via PTEN/PI3K/Akt signaling pathway.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0000034 promotes the progression of retinoblastoma via sponging microRNA-361-3p.
description: hsa_circ_0000034 promoted the oncogenicity of retinoblastoma via regulation of miR-361-3p expression, a finding that may contribute toward retinoblastoma therapeutics.

title: Circular RNA CDR1as disrupts the p53/MDM2 complex to inhibit Gliomagenesis.
description: Rather than acting as a miRNA sponge, CDR1as functions as a tumor suppressor through binding directly to p53 at its DBD region to restrict MDM2 interaction. Thus, CDR1as binding disrupts the p53/MDM2 complex to prevent p53 from ubiquitination and degradation. CDR1as may also sense DNA damage signals and form a protective complex with p53 to preserve p53 function.

title: Circular RNA circ-MTO1 serves as a novel potential diagnostic and prognostic biomarker for gallbladder cancer.
description: Circ-MTO1 is a potential early diagnostic and prognostic biomarker for patients with gallbladder cancer. Thus, our present work might provide a new understanding of the diagnosis and treatment of GBC.

title: Knockdown of circ0082374 inhibits cell viability, migration, invasion and glycolysis in glioma cells by miR-326/SIRT1.
description: silence of circ0082374 repressed the viability, migration, invasion and glycolysis in glioma cells by regulating miR-326 and SIRT1 in a ceRNA mechanism, providing a new mechanism for the pathogenesis of glioma.

title: Knockdown of circular RNA circMAT2B reduces oxygen-glucose deprivation-induced inflammatory injury in H9c2 cells through up-regulating miR-133.
description: circMAT2B knockdown works as an inflammatory inhibitor in OGD-induced H9c2 cells inflammatory injury through up-regulating miR-133.

title: A novel identified circular RNA, circ_0000491, aggravates the extracellular matrix of diabetic nephropathy glomerular mesangial cells through suppressing miR_101b by targeting TGFbetaRI.
description: circRNA_0000491/miR_101b/TGFbetaRI axis in ECM accumulation and fibrosis_associated protein expression levels of mesangial cells, which suggested that circRNA_0000491 may be beneficial for the development of an effective therapeutic target for DN.

title: Circular RNA NOX4 promotes the development of colorectal cancer via the microRNA_485_5p/CKS1B axis.
description: circNOX4 may serve an oncogenic role in CRC by promoting the proliferation, migration, invasion and glycolysis of CRC cells via the miR_485_5p/CKS1B axis.

title: Circular RNA circNFATC3 acts as a miR-9-5p sponge to promote cervical cancer development by upregulating SDC2.
description: Our data indicate that circNFATC3 sponges miR-9-5p to regulate SDC2 expression and, thereby, to promote CC tumor development.

title: CircHIPK3 regulates cardiac fibroblast proliferation, migration and phenotypic switching through the miR-152-3p/TGF-beta2 axis under hypoxia.
description: These findings demonstrated that circHIPK3 acted as a miR-152-3p sponge to regulate CF proliferation, migration and phenotypic transformation through TGF-beta2, revealing that modulation of circHIPK3 expression may represent a potential target to promote the transition of hypoxia-induced CFs to myofibroblasts.

title: The Significance of Circular RNA DDX17 in Prostate Cancer.
description: our findings indicated that the circDDX17/miR-346/LHPP pathway inhibited the progression of prostate cancer and that circDDX17 may be a new potential therapeutic or diagnostic target for treating and diagnosing prostate cancer.

title: Circular RNA MYLK Promotes Hepatocellular Carcinoma Progression Through the miR29a/KMT5C Signaling Pathway.
description: circMYLK promotes HCC progression by acting as a competing endogenous RNA of miR-29a, which regulates the downstream oncogene KMT5C.

title: Exosomal circFBLIM1 Promotes Hepatocellular Carcinoma Progression and Glycolysis by Regulating the miR-338/LRP6 Axis.
description: CircFBLIM1 facilitated HCC progression and glycolysis via modulating the miR-338/LRP6 axis, which may provide promising therapeutic targets for HCC.

title: Profiling of circular RNAs in age-related cataract reveals circZNF292 as an antioxidant by sponging miR-23b-3p.
description: circZNF292, a down-regulated circRNA in the anterior lens capsule of ARC patients, may be involved in resistance to oxidative damage and apoptosis of lens epithelial cells by sponging miR-23b-3p, providing a potential target for prevention and treatment of ARC.

title: Novel circular RNA 2960 contributes to secondary damage of spinal cord injury by sponging miRNA-124.
description: A novel circRNA-2960 was the most significantly upregulated in the SCI group. It could downregulate its target molecule miRNA_124, then exacerbate the inflammatory response and induce apoptosis at the lesion site.

title: CircMMP1 promotes the progression of glioma through miR-433/HMGB3 axis in vitro and in vivo.
description: CircMMP1 promoted the progression of glioma through acting as a competitive endogenous RNA (ceRNA) of miR-433 to up-regulate HMGB3. CircMMP1 level in serum exosomes might be a potential marker for the diagnosis of glioma patients. Targeting circMMP1/miR-433/HMGB3 signaling might be a novel insight for glioma treatment.

title: circCRKL suppresses the progression of prostate cancer cells by regulating the miR-141/KLF5 axis.
description: These findings revealed that circCRKL inhibited the progression of PCa through upregulating KLF5 expression by sponging miR-141, elucidating a novel regulatory pathway in PCa cells. Our research suggested an underlying circRNA-targeted therapy for PCa.

title: Downregulation of Hsa_circ_0000735 Inhibits the Proliferation, Migration, Invasion, and Glycolysis in Non-small-cell Lung Cancer by Targeting miR-940/BMPER Axis.
description: Circ_0000735 regulated proliferation, migration, invasion, and glycolysis in NSCLC cells by targeting miR-940/BMPER axis.

title: Circular RNA circRNA_103809 Accelerates Bladder Cancer Progression and Enhances Chemo-Resistance by Activation of miR-516a-5p/FBXL18 Axis.
description: circRNA_103809 promotes proliferation, migration, invasion and chemo-resistance of BC cells through regulating miR-516a-5p/FBXL18 axis.

title: Circ_0000376, a Novel circRNA, Promotes the Progression of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Through Regulating the miR-1182/NOVA2 Network.
description: Circ_0000376 promoted NSCLC progression by regulating the miR-1182/NOVA2 axis, suggesting that circ_0000376 might be a potential biomarker for NSCLC treatment.

title: Blocking circ_0000520 Suppressed Breast Cancer Cell Growth, Migration and Invasion Partially via miR-1296/SP1 Axis Both in vitro and in vivo.
description: Circ_0000520 knockdown could suppress cell growth, migration and invasion both in vitro and in vivo through regulating miR-1296/SP1 pathway.

title: Genome-wide analysis of circular RNA expression profiles in patients with atrial fibrillation.
description: All of 4 upregulated circRNAs (circRNA_0031, circRNA_1837, circRNA_5901 and circRNA_7571) and 3 out of 4 downregulated circRNAs (circRNA_5801, circRNA_7386 and circRNA_7577) were randomly confirmed by RT-PCR.

title: Genome-wide analysis of circular RNA expression profiles in patients with atrial fibrillation.
description: All of 4 upregulated circRNAs (circRNA_0031, circRNA_1837, circRNA_5901 and circRNA_7571) and 3 out of 4 downregulated circRNAs (circRNA_5801, circRNA_7386 and circRNA_7578) were randomly confirmed by RT-PCR.

title: Genome-wide analysis of circular RNA expression profiles in patients with atrial fibrillation.
description: All of 4 upregulated circRNAs (circRNA_0031, circRNA_1837, circRNA_5901 and circRNA_7571) and 3 out of 4 downregulated circRNAs (circRNA_5801, circRNA_7386 and circRNA_7579) were randomly confirmed by RT-PCR.

title: Genome-wide analysis of circular RNA expression profiles in patients with atrial fibrillation.
description: All of 4 upregulated circRNAs (circRNA_0031, circRNA_1837, circRNA_5901 and circRNA_7571) and 3 out of 4 downregulated circRNAs (circRNA_5801, circRNA_7386 and circRNA_7580) were randomly confirmed by RT-PCR.

title: Genome-wide analysis of circular RNA expression profiles in patients with atrial fibrillation.
description: All of 4 upregulated circRNAs (circRNA_0031, circRNA_1837, circRNA_5901 and circRNA_7571) and 3 out of 4 downregulated circRNAs (circRNA_5801, circRNA_7386 and circRNA_7581) were randomly confirmed by RT-PCR.

title: Genome-wide analysis of circular RNA expression profiles in patients with atrial fibrillation.
description: All of 4 upregulated circRNAs (circRNA_0031, circRNA_1837, circRNA_5901 and circRNA_7571) and 3 out of 4 downregulated circRNAs (circRNA_5801, circRNA_7386 and circRNA_7582) were randomly confirmed by RT-PCR.

title: Genome-wide analysis of circular RNA expression profiles in patients with atrial fibrillation.
description: All of 4 upregulated circRNAs (circRNA_0031, circRNA_1837, circRNA_5901 and circRNA_7571) and 3 out of 4 downregulated circRNAs (circRNA_5801, circRNA_7386 and circRNA_7583) were randomly confirmed by RT-PCR.

title: EIF4A3-induced circular RNA ASAP1 promotes tumorigenesis and temozolomide resistance of glioblastoma via NRAS/MEK1/ERK1-2 signaling.
description: CircASAP1 expression was significantly upregulated in recurrent GBM tissues and TMZ-resistant cell lines. CircASAP1 overexpression enhanced GBM cell proliferation and TMZ resistance, which could be reduced by circASAP1 knockdown. Further experiments revealed that circASAP1 increased the expression of NRAS via sponging miR-502-5p. Moreover, circASAP1 depletion effectively restored the sensitivity of TMZ-resistant xenografts to TMZ treatment in vivo.

title: CircATP2B4 promotes hypoxia-induced proliferation and migration of pulmonary arterial smooth muscle cells via the miR-223/ATR axis.
description: CircATP2B4 potentiated hypoxia-induced proliferation and migration of PASMCs through the miR-223/ATR axis. Restoration of the level of miR-223 might be an effective therapeutic method for the treatment of PAH.

title: CircPAN3 ameliorates myocardial ischaemia/reperfusion injury by targeting miR-421/Pink1 axis-mediated autophagy suppression.
description: Our findings reveal a novel role for circPAN3 in modulating autophagy and apoptosis in myocardial I/R injury and the circPAN3-miR-421-Pink1 axis as a regulatory network, which might provide potential therapeutic targets for cardiovascular diseases.

title: circ-PRKCB acts as a ceRNA to regulate p66Shc-mediated oxidative stress in intestinal ischemia/reperfusion.
description: Our findings reveal a crucial role for the circ-PRKCB/miR-339-5p/p66Shc signaling pathway in regulating oxidative stress in the I/R intestine. This pathway may be a potential therapeutic target for intestinal I/R injury.

title: circPTCH1 promotes invasion and metastasis in renal cell carcinoma via regulating miR-485-5p/MMP14 axis.
description: circPTCH1 promotes RCC metastasis via the miR-485-5p/MMP14 axis and activation of the EMT process. Targeting circPTCH1 may represent a promising therapeutic strategy for metastatic RCC.

title: Targeting Mitochondria-Located circRNA SCAR Alleviates NASH via Reducing mROS Output.
description: Targeting Mitochondria-Located circRNA SCAR Alleviates NASH via Reducing mROS Output.

title: CircARHGAP12 promotes nasopharyngeal carcinoma migration and invasion via ezrin-mediated cytoskeletal remodeling.
description: circARHGAP12 was found to promote the malignant biological phenotype of NPC via cytoskeletal remodeling, thus providing a clue for targeted therapy of NPC.

title: Circ_0086720 knockdown strengthens the radiosensitivity of non-small cell lung cancer via mediating the miR-375/SPIN1 axis.
description: circ_0086720 downregulation enhanced the sensitivity of NSCLC to radiation by regulating the miR-375/SPIN1 axis, contributing to the improvement of the radiotherapies in NSCLC.

title: Circular RNA circ-NCOR2 accelerates papillary thyroid cancer progression by sponging miR-516a-5p to upregulate metastasis-associated protein 2 expression.
description: Circular RNA circ-NCOR2 accelerates papillary thyroid cancer progression by sponging miR-516a-5p to upregulate metastasis-associated protein 2 expression.

title: Peripheral blood circular RNA hsa_circ_0082688-hsa_circ_0008675 can be used as a candidate biomarker of systemic lupus erythematosus with renal involvement.
description: The level of hsa_circ_0082688, hsa_circ_0082689 and hsa_circ_0008675 were significantly elevated in SLE+RI patients with respect to the SLE-RI, RA, NWS patients and the HC. The level of hsa_circ_0082688, hsa_circ_0082689 and hsa_circ_0008675 were associated with C4, anti-dsDNA, anti-nucleosome.

title: Peripheral blood circular RNA hsa_circ_0082688-hsa_circ_0008675 can be used as a candidate biomarker of systemic lupus erythematosus with renal involvement.
description: The level of hsa_circ_0082688, hsa_circ_0082689 and hsa_circ_0008675 were significantly elevated in SLE+RI patients with respect to the SLE-RI, RA, NWS patients and the HC. The level of hsa_circ_0082688, hsa_circ_0082689 and hsa_circ_0008675 were associated with C4, anti-dsDNA, anti-nucleosome.

title: Peripheral blood circular RNA hsa_circ_0082688-hsa_circ_0008675 can be used as a candidate biomarker of systemic lupus erythematosus with renal involvement.
description: The level of hsa_circ_0082688, hsa_circ_0082689 and hsa_circ_0008675 were significantly elevated in SLE+RI patients with respect to the SLE-RI, RA, NWS patients and the HC. The level of hsa_circ_0082688, hsa_circ_0082689 and hsa_circ_0008675 were associated with C4, anti-dsDNA, anti-nucleosome.

title: Circ-ZNF609 Accelerates the Radioresistance of Prostate Cancer Cells by Promoting the Glycolytic Metabolism Through miR-501-3p/HK2 Axis.
description: Circ-ZNF609 promoted the progression and radioresistance of PCa cells through accelerating the glycolysis via miR-501-3p/HK2 axis, providing promising targets for improving the prognosis of PCa patients.

title: Exosomal Circ-ZNF652 Promotes Cell Proliferation, Migration, Invasion and Glycolysis in Hepatocellular Carcinoma via miR-29a-3p/GUCD1 Axis.
description: Exosomal circ-ZNF652 contributes to HCC cell proliferation, migration, invasion and glycolysis by miR-29a-3p/GUCD1 axis.

title: CircUBE2D2 (hsa_circ_0005728) promotes cell proliferation, metastasis and chemoresistance in triple-negative breast cancer by regulating miR-512-3p/CDCA3 axis.
description: CircUBE2D2 promoted TNBC progression and doxorubicin resistance through acting as a sponge of miR-512-3p to up-regulate CDCA3 expression. Targeting circUBE2D2 combine with doxorubicin might be exploited as a novel therapy for TNBC.

title: Diagnostic value of exosomal circMYC in radioresistant nasopharyngeal carcinoma.
description: circMYC is an oncogene in NPC cells and can enhance the radiotherapy resistance of NPC cells. Circulating exosomal circMYC can be used as a potential therapeutic target for NPC.

title: Circular RNA circ_0010283 regulates the viability and migration of oxidized low_density lipoprotein_induced vascular smooth muscle cells via an miR_370_3p/HMGB1 axis in atherosclerosis.
description: circ_0010283 mediated cell viability and migration via a miR_370_3p/HMGB1 axis in ox_LDL_induced VSMCs.

title: Propofol suppresses gastric cancer tumorigenesis by modulating the circular RNA_PVT1/miR_195_5p/E26 oncogene homolog 1 axis.
description: propofol inhibited the proliferation and invasion, but enhanced the apoptosis of GC cells by regulating the circ_PVT1/miR_195_5p/ETS1 axis.

title: Circular RNA circ_HN1 facilitates gastric cancer progression through modulation of the miR-302b-3p/ROCK2 axis.
description: circ_HN1 exerted an oncogenic role in GC through upregulating ROCK2 via sponging miR-302b-3p, offering evidence that circ_HN1 is a potential target for GC therapy.

title: Silencing circ_0062389 alleviates cardiomyocyte apoptosis in heart failure rats via modulating TGF-beta1/Smad3 signaling pathway.
description: Silencing circ_0062389 could alleviate cardiomyocyte apoptosis in HF rats via modulating TGF-beta1/Smad3 signaling pathway, which might be a promising target for the treatment of HF.

title: TV-circRGPD6 Nanoparticle Suppresses Breast Cancer Stem Cell-Mediated Metastasis via the miR-26b/YAF2 Axis.
description: we have developed a TV-circRGPD6 nanoparticle that selectively expresses circRGPD6 in metastatic BCSCs to eradicate breast cancer metastasis, therefore providing a novel avenue to treat breast cancers.

title: Quietness of circular RNA circ_0054633 alleviates the inflammation and proliferation in lipopolysaccharides-induced acute lung injury model through NF-kappaB signaling pathway.
description: Quietness of circ_0054633 alleviated LPS-induced ALI via NF-kappaB signaling pathway, implicating circ_0054633 may be a potential biomarker for diagnose and therapy of ALI.

title: CircSFXN1 regulates the behaviour of trophoblasts and likely mediates preeclampsia.
description: we identified a novel circRNA that regulates tumorigenic activities, suggesting a new pathway governing CircSFXN1/sFLT1-mediated regulation of trophoblast behaviour.

title: Circ_0000079 Decoys the RNA-Binding Protein FXR1 to Interrupt Formation of the FXR1/PRCKI Complex and Decline Their Mediated Cell Invasion and Drug Resistance in NSCLC.
description: circ_0000079 might inhibit cell invasion and drug resistance in NSCLC by interrupting the formation of the FXR1/PRCKI complex by interacting with FXR1, and circ_0000079 could act as a potential biomarker and therapeutic target for NSCLC.

title: CircRNA CircRIMS Acts as a MicroRNA Sponge to Promote Gastric Cancer Metastasis.
description: circRIMS has potential as an early biomarker for use in predicting invasive metastasis in GC and to guide clinical diagnosis and treatment for precision medicine.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0001649 suppresses the growth of osteosarcoma cells via sponging multiple miRNAs.
description: circ_0001649 worked as a sponge to absorb miR-338-5p, miR-647 and miR-942 to suppress cell proliferation, induce apoptosis and inhibit STAT pathway. Circ_0001649 suppressed OS cell proliferation and STAT pathway and induced apoptosis through sponging miR-338-5p, miR-647 and miR-942.

title: Silencing circular RNA hsa_circ_009755 promotes growth and metastasis of oral squamous cell carcinoma.
description: The expression of hsa_circ_009755 was low in OSCC tissues and three OSCC cell lines. Silencing hsa_circ_009755 significantly enhanced the proliferation, migration, and invasion and suppressed the apoptosis of OSCC cells.

title: Circular RNA CircITGA7 Promotes Tumorigenesis of Osteosarcoma via miR-370/PIM1 Axis.
description: circITGA7 promotes OS proliferation and metastasis via miR-370/PIM1.

title: circKMT2D contributes to H(2)O(2)-attenuated osteosarcoma progression via the miR-210/autophagy pathway.
description: these findings indicated that circKMT2D knockdown may contribute to the inhibition of H(2)O(2)-attenuated OS progression via miR-210/autophagy pathway.

title: Circular RNA GLIS2 promotes colorectal cancer cell motility via activation of the NF-kappaB pathway.
description: our study reveals that circGLIS2, acting as a potential oncogene, maintains the abnormal activation state of the NF-kappaB signaling pathway via the miR-671 sponge mechanism in CRC cells. This study provides a scientific basis for targeting circGLIS2 in colorectal cancer interventions.

title: CircZNF609 promotes cell proliferation, migration, invasion, and glycolysis in nasopharyngeal carcinoma through regulating HRAS via miR-338-3p.
description: circZNF609 acted as a competing endogenous RNA of miR-338-3p to regulate HRAS. CircZNF609 knockdown suppressed cell tumorigenesis in NPC via regulating miR-338-3p/HRAS axis, suggesting a novel therapeutic strategy for NPC.

title: Upregulation of circ_0000142 promotes multiple myeloma progression by adsorbing miR-610 and upregulating AKT3 expression.
description: circ_0000142 functioned as a competitive endogenous RNA, directly targeting miR-610 and positively regulating AKT3 expression. In brief, circ_0000142 enhances the proliferation and metastasis of MM cells by modulating the miR-610/AKT3 axis.

title: Upregulated hsa_circ_0005785 Facilitates Cell Growth and Metastasis of Hepatocellular Carcinoma Through the miR-578/APRIL Axis.
description: our current study revealed an oncogenic role of hsa_circ_0005785 in the tumorigenesis of HCC. Moreover, targeting to the hsa_circ_0005785/miR-578/APRIL regulatory pathway might be a promising diagnostic and therapeutic strategy for HCC clinical practice.

title: Downregulation of hsa_circ_0000936 sensitizes resistant glioma cells to temozolomide by sponging miR-1294.
description: downregulation of hsa_circ_0000936 sensitizes TMZ-resistant glioma cells to TMZ by sponging miR-1294, suggesting that hsa_circ_0000936 may be a potential target for overcoming the resistance of glioma cells to TMZ.

title: Circular RNA expression profiling identifies novel biomarkers in uterine leiomyoma.
description: Bioinformatics analysis suggested that most differentially expressed circRNAs participate in pathways were related to pathological processes of ULM.
