title: Circular RNA circCUL3 Accelerates the Warburg Effect Progression of Gastric Cancer through Regulating the STAT3/HK2 Axis.
description: circCUL3/miR-515-5p/STAT3/HK2 axis regulation on the GC Warburg effect, providing a novel possibility for an understanding of GC pathogenesis.

title: hsa_circ_0001955 Enhances In Vitro Proliferation, Migration, and Invasion of HCC Cells through miR-145-5p/NRAS Axis.
description: hsa_circ_0001955 Enhances In Vitro Proliferation, Migration, and Invasion of HCC Cells through miR-145-5p/NRAS Axis.

title: circNR3C1 Suppresses Bladder Cancer Progression through Acting as an Endogenous Blocker of BRD4/C-myc Complex.
description: circNR3C1 inhibits BC progression through acting as endogenous blocker of BRD4/C-myc complex.

title: circRNA CDR1as Promotes Pulmonary Artery Smooth Muscle Cell Calcification by Upregulating CAMK2D and CNN3 via Sponging miR-7-5p.
description: the CDR1as/miR-7-5p/CNN3 and CAMK2D regulatory axis mediates HPASMC osteoblastic differentiation and calcification induced by hypoxia. This evidence reveals an approach to the treatment of PH.

title: Exosome-Shuttled circSHOC2 from IPASs Regulates Neuronal Autophagy and Ameliorates Ischemic Brain Injury via the miR-7670-3p/SIRT1 Axis.
description: our findings indicate that circSHOC2 in IPAS-EXOs suppressed neuronal apoptosis and ameliorated neuronal damage by regulating autophagy and acting on the miR-7670-3p/SIRT1 axis, which might contribute to a therapeutic strategy for ischemic stroke treatment.

title: Circular RNA circRIMS1 Acts as a Sponge of miR-433-3p to Promote Bladder Cancer Progression by Regulating CCAR1 Expression.
description: our research demonstrated that circRIMS1 promotes tumor growth, migration, and invasion through the miR-433-3p/CCAR1 regulatory axis, representing a potential therapeutic target and biomarker in bladder cancer.

title: circPARD3 drives malignant progression and chemoresistance of laryngeal squamous cell carcinoma by inhibiting autophagy through the PRKCI-Akt-mTOR pathway.
description: Our study reveals that the novel autophagy-suppressive circPARD3 promotes LSCC progression and chemoresistance through the PRKCI-Akt-mTOR pathway, providing new insights into circRNA-mediated autophagy regulation and potential biomarker and target for LSCC treatment.

title: CircSOD2 induced epigenetic alteration drives hepatocellular carcinoma progression through activating JAK2/STAT3 signaling pathway.
description: The novel signaling axis circSOD2/miR-502-5p/DNMT3a/JAK2/STAT3/circSOD2 provides a better understanding of HCC tumorigenesis. The molecular mechanism underlying this signaling axis offers new prevention and treatment of HCC.

title: The microarray identification circular RNA hsa_circ_0105015 up-regulated involving inflammation pathway in essential hypertension.
description: Hyperexpression of hsa_circ_0105015 is a significant risk factor of EH and its association with EH involves inflammatory pathways. Hyperexpression of hsa_circ_0105015 combined with hypoexpression of hsa-miR-637 indicates vascular inflammation or endothelial dysfunction and has potential as a biomarker for early diagnosis of EH.

title: G protein-coupled oestrogen receptor promotes cell growth of non-small cell lung cancer cells via YAP1/QKI/circNOTCH1/m6A methylated NOTCH1 signalling.
description: GPER could promote NSCLC cell growth via regulating the YAP1/QKI/circNOTCH1/m6A methylated NOTCH1 pathway, and targeting our identified molecules may be a potentially therapeutic approach to suppress NSCLC development.

title: Identification of Two Novel Circular RNAs Deriving from BCL2L12 and Investigation of Their Potential Value as a Molecular Signature in Colorectal Cancer.
description: circ-BCL2L12-2 expression is inversely associated with TNM stage, while circ-BCL2L12-1 overexpression is associated with shorter overall survival in CRC, particularly among TNM stage II patients. Overall, we identified two novel BCL2L12 circRNAs, one of which can further stratify TNM stage II patients into two subgroups with substantially distinct prognosis.

title: Identification of Two Novel Circular RNAs Deriving from BCL2L12 and Investigation of Their Potential Value as a Molecular Signature in Colorectal Cancer.
description: circ-BCL2L12-2 expression is inversely associated with TNM stage, while circ-BCL2L12-1 overexpression is associated with shorter overall survival in CRC, particularly among TNM stage II patients. Overall, we identified two novel BCL2L12 circRNAs, one of which can further stratify TNM stage II patients into two subgroups with substantially distinct prognosis.

title: Circ_SATB2 Attenuates the Anti-Tumor Role of Celastrol in Non-Small-Cell Lung Carcinoma Through Targeting miR-33a-5p/E2F7 Axis.
description: Cela suppressed NSCLC development through regulating circ_SATB2/miR-33a-5p/E2F7 signaling cascade.

title: Interference of circRNA HIPK3 alleviates cardiac dysfunction in lipopolysaccharide-induced mice models and apoptosis in H9C2 cardiomyocytes.
description: we characterized the expression and regulation of circHIPK3 in LPS-induced myocarditis in the animal model and H9c2 cells. The results demonstrated that circHIPK3 expression is significantly upregulated when exposed to LPS in vivo and in vitro. Knockdown of circHIPK3 effectively alleviated LPS-induced myocarditis.

title: HIPK3 Circular RNA Promotes Metastases of HCC Through Sponging miR-338-3p to Induce ZEB2 Expression.
description: CircHIPK3 plays a regulatory role in metastatic HCC by sponging miR-338-3p to induce ZEB2 expression, thus promoting EMT procession.

title: Circular RNA circ_0004507 contributes to laryngeal cancer progression and cisplatin resistance by sponging miR-873 to upregulate multidrug resistance 1 and multidrug resistance protein 1.
description: Knockdown of circ_0004507 inhibited laryngeal cancer progression and cisplatin resistance by sponging miR-873, providing a potential target for laryngeal cancer therapy.

title: Hsa_circ_0006872 promotes cigarette smoke-induced apoptosis, inflammation and oxidative stress in HPMECs and BEAS-2B cells through the miR-145-5p/NF-kappaB axis.
description: Hsa_circ_0006872 promotes cigarette smoke-induced apoptosis, inflammation and oxidative stress in HPMECs and BEAS-2B cells through the miR-145-5p/NF-kappaB axis.

title: Oxidized low-density lipoprotein accelerates the injury of endothelial cells via circ-USP36/miR-98-5p/VCAM1 axis.
description: Ox-LDL promoted the apoptosis and inflammation but suppressed the viability of HUVEC cells through upregulating circ-USP36, thus elevating the expression of VCAM1 via miR-98-5p.

title: Tumor promoting effects of circRNA_001287 on renal cell carcinoma through miR-144-targeted CEP55.
description: circ_001287 can up-regulate CEP55 by binding to miR-144, which resulted in increased proliferative, invasive and migratory capacities and tumor growth in vivo.

title: Circular RNA 100146 Promotes Colorectal Cancer Progression by the MicroRNA 149/HMGA2 Axis.
description: circRNA 100146 knockdown repressed proliferation, enhanced apoptosis, and hindered migration and invasion in SW620 and SW480 cells through targeting the miR-149/HMGA2 axis.

title: Circ-UBR1 facilitates proliferation, metastasis, and inhibits apoptosis in breast cancer by regulating the miR-1299/CCND1 axis.
description: circ-UBR1 might play a pro-cancer role in BC progression by regulating the miR-1299/CCND1 axis.

title: Circular RNA circGSK3B Promotes Cell Proliferation, Migration, and Invasion by Sponging miR-1265 and Regulating CAB39 Expression in Hepatocellular Carcinoma.
description: circGSK3B-miR-1265-CAB39 axis can promote the proliferation, migration, invasion of HCC cells, indicating that circGSKB may serve as a promising diagnostic and prognostic marker in HCC.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0000658 inhibits osteosarcoma cell proliferation and migration via the miR-1227/IRF2 axis.
description: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0000658 inhibits osteosarcoma cell proliferation and migration via the miR-1227/IRF2 axis.

title: A novel circular RNA, circXPO1, promotes lung adenocarcinoma progression by interacting with IGF2BP1.
description: circXPO1 could bind with IGF2BP1 and enhance CTNNB1 mRNA stability, and subsequently promote LUAD progression.

title: A novel circular RNA hsa_circRNA_103809/miR-377-3p/GOT1 pathway regulates cisplatin-resistance in non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC).
description: Analysis of data suggested that targeting the hsa_circRNA_103809/miR-377-3p/GOT1 pathway increased susceptibility of CR-NSCLC cells to cisplatin, and this study provided novel targets to improve the therapeutic efficacy of cisplatin for NSCLC treatment in clinic.

title: Circ-PRMT5 promotes breast cancer by the miR-509-3p/TCF7L2 axis activating the PI3K/AKT pathway.
description: Functionally, knockdown of circ-PRMT5 suppresses cell proliferation and angiogenesis and increases cell apoptosis in breast cancer. Mechanistically, we identified that circ-PRMT5 up-regulates TCF7L2 expression by acting as a miR-509-3p sponge. The negative expression correlation between miR-509-3p and circ-PRMT5 or TCF7L2 in clinical tissues was further demonstrated.

title: CircRNA-1806 Decreases T Cell Apoptosis and Prolongs Survival of Mice After Cryptococcal Infection by Sponging miRNA-126.
description: CircRNA-1806 Decreases T Cell Apoptosis and Prolongs Survival of Mice After Cryptococcal Infection by Sponging miRNA-126.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0005114-miR-142-3p/miR-590-5p-adenomatous polyposis coli protein axis as a potential target for treatment of glioma.
description: hsa-miR-142-3p/hsa-miR-590-5p-APC-related circ/ceRNA axes may be important in glioma, and hsa_circ_0005114 interacted with both of these miRNAs. Functional analysis showed that hsa_circ_0005114 was involved in insulin secretion, while APC was associated with the Wnt signaling pathway.

title: Hsa_circ_0002483 regulates miR-758-3p/MYC axis to promote acute myeloid leukemia progression.
description: miR-758-3p overexpression restrained cell proliferation and promoted cycle arrest and apoptosis via decreasing MYC. Circ_0002483 knockdown repressed AML cell proliferation and promoted cycle arrest and apoptosis via controlling miR-758-3p/MYC axis.

title: Circular RNA circ_ASAP2 promotes cell viability, migration, and invasion of gastric cancer cells by regulating the miR-770-5p/CDK6 axis.
description: Circ_ASAP2 knockdown can repress the development of GC cells partly through regulating the miR-770-5p/CDK6 axis, suggesting an underlying circRNA-targeted therapy for GC treatment.

title: Circ_0025033 promotes the progression of ovarian cancer by activating the expression of LSM4 via targeting miR-184.
description: Circ_0025033 promotes the progression of OC by regulating LSM4 expression via targeting miR-184, which provided a new strategy to treat OC.

title: Circ0120816 acts as an oncogene of esophageal squamous cell carcinoma by inhibiting miR-1305 and releasing TXNRD1.
description: circ0120816 played an active role in promoting ESCC development by targeting miR-1305 and upregulating oncogene TXNRD1.

title: Exosome-transferred hsa_circ_0014235 promotes DDP chemoresistance and deteriorates the development of non-small cell lung cancer by mediating the miR-520a-5p/CDK4 pathway.
description: Exosome-transferred hsa_circ_0014235 promotes DDP chemoresistance and deteriorates the development of non-small cell lung cancer by mediating the miR-520a-5p/CDK4 pathway.

title: CircSMYD4 regulates proliferation, migration and apoptosis of hepatocellular carcinoma cells by sponging miR-584-5p.
description: Up-regulation of circSMYD4 inhibited the proliferation, invasion and migration and promoted the apoptosis of HCC cells in vitro, while it inhibited tumor growth, promoted apoptosis-related proteins, and suppressed alpha-fetoprotein (AFP) levels in vivo. CircSMYD4 could be used as a miRNA sponge to target miR-584-5p. In addition, miR-584-5p overexpression partially reversed the regulatory effect of circSMYD4 on HCC.

title: Circ_0015756 promotes the progression of ovarian cancer by regulating miR-942-5p/CUL4B pathway.
description: CircSMYD4 prevents the development of HCC through regulating multiple signaling pathways such as metastasis and apoptosis by sponging miR-584-5p.

title: Circ-EEF2 facilitated autophagy via interaction with mir-6881-3p and ANXA2 in EOC.
description: circEEF2 could directly bind with ANXA2 to inhibit the expression of p-mTOR. In conclusion, findings of the current study illustrate that circEEF2 promoted autophagy, proliferation, and invasion of EOC by interacting with miR-6881-3p and ANXA2.

title: Circular RNA circPLK1 promotes breast cancer cell proliferation, migration and invasion by regulating miR-4500/IGF1 axis.
description: CircPLK1 silence inhibited BC cell growth, migration and invasion by regulating miR-4500/IGF1 axis, suggesting circPLK1/miR-4500/IGF axis might be a potential therapeutic target.

title: Circ_0003998 enhances doxorubicin resistance in hepatocellular carcinoma by regulating miR-218-5p/EIF5A2 pathway.
description: Circ_0003998 knockdown sensitized HCC cell to DOX by regulating miR-218-5p/EIF5A2 axis, indicating new markers of poor response to DOX and potential therapeutic strategies for the chemotherapy of HCC.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0001829 promotes gastric cancer progression through miR-155-5p/SMAD2 axis.
description: our findings firstly demonstrated a novel oncogenic role of hsa_circ_0001829 in GC progression through miR-155-5p-SMAD2 axis, and our study may offer novel biomarkers and therapeutic targets for GC.

title: CircCDKN2B-AS1 interacts with IMP3 to stabilize hexokinase 2 mRNA and facilitate cervical squamous cell carcinoma aerobic glycolysis progression.
description: circCDKN2B-AS1 facilitates aerobic glycolysis by sponging the IMP3 protein to stabilize HK2 mRNA, consequently promoting the malignant phenotype in cervical cancer, which may provide a potential approach for cervical cancer therapeutics.

title: CircLRRK1 targets miR-223-3p to inhibit the proliferation, migration and invasion of trophoblast cells by regulating the PI3K/AKT signaling pathway.
description: CircLRRK1 could suppress the proliferation, migration and invasion of trophoblast cells by regulating the PI3K/AKT signaling pathway via targeting miR-223-3p, suggesting that circLRRK1 might be a potential biomarker for the treatment of PE.

title: CircRNA hsa_circRNA_104348 promotes hepatocellular carcinoma progression through modulating miR-187-3p/RTKN2 axis and activating Wnt/beta-catenin pathway.
description: circular RNA hsa_circRNA_104348 might function as a competing endogenous RNA (ceRNA) to promotes HCC progression by targeting miR-187-3p/RTKN2 axis and activating Wnt/beta-catenin pathway.

title: Plasma circular RNA panel acts as a novel diagnostic biomarker for colorectal cancer detection.
description: We ultimately determined that hsa_circ_0001900, hsa_circ_0001178, and hsa_circ_0005927 were upregulated in the plasma of CRC patients relative to healthy controls and were correlated with clinicopathological findings in these patients.

title: Plasma circular RNA panel acts as a novel diagnostic biomarker for colorectal cancer detection.
description: We ultimately determined that hsa_circ_0001900, hsa_circ_0001178, and hsa_circ_0005928 were upregulated in the plasma of CRC patients relative to healthy controls and were correlated with clinicopathological findings in these patients.

title: Plasma circular RNA panel acts as a novel diagnostic biomarker for colorectal cancer detection.
description: We ultimately determined that hsa_circ_0001900, hsa_circ_0001178, and hsa_circ_0005929 were upregulated in the plasma of CRC patients relative to healthy controls and were correlated with clinicopathological findings in these patients.

title: circEYA1 Functions as a Sponge of miR-582-3p to Suppress Cervical Adenocarcinoma Tumorigenesis via Upregulating CXCL14.
description: circEYA1 Functions as a Sponge of miR-582-3p to Suppress Cervical Adenocarcinoma Tumorigenesis via Upregulating CXCL14.

title: circRASGRF2 functions as an oncogenic gene in hepatocellular carcinoma by acting as a miR-1224 sponge.
description: circRASGRF2 functions as an oncogenic gene in hepatocellular carcinoma by acting as a miR-1224 sponge.

title: Circular RNA Circ-03955 Promotes Epithelial-Mesenchymal Transition in Osteosarcoma by Regulating miR-3662/Metadherin Pathway.
description: Mechanism analysis revealed that circ-03955 could bind to miR-3662, and the latter could target MTDH, leading to its suppressed expression and facilitating epithelial-mesenchymal transition (EMT). All these findings demonstrate that the presence of circ-03955 promotes EMT in osteosarcoma by acting as miR-3662 sponge-mediated MTDH expression.

title: Comprehensive analysis of circular RNA in oral leukoplakia: upregulated circHLA-C as a potential biomarker for diagnosis and prognosis.
description: circHLA-C as a promising diagnostic biomarker with potential as a therapeutic genetic target for OLK.

title: circ_100984-miR-432-3p axis regulated c-Jun/YBX-1/beta-catenin feedback loop promotes bladder cancer progression.
description: circ_100984-miR-432-3p axis regulated c-Jun/YBX-1/beta-catenin feedback loop promotes BC progression, providing a potential therapeutic axis for BC progression.

title: Circ_0005198 enhances temozolomide resistance of glioma cells through miR-198/TRIM14 axis.
description: circ_0005198-miR-198-TRIM14 regulatory pathway is critical to TMZ resistance of glioma.

title: CircRNA_0000392 promotes colorectal cancer progression through the miR-193a-5p/PIK3R3/AKT axis.
description: CircRNA_0000392 functions as an oncogene through the miR-193a-5p/PIK3R3/Akt axis in CRC cells.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0008003 facilitates tumorigenesis and development of non-small cell lung carcinoma via modulating miR-488/ZNF281 axis.
description: circ-0008003 triggered tumour formation in NSCLC, which was adjusted via miR-488/ZNF281 axis.

title: CircPUM1 promotes hepatocellular carcinoma progression through the miR-1208/MAP3K2 axis.
description: circPUM1 could promote the development of HCC by up-regulating the expression of MAP3K2 via sponging miR-1208.

title: Screening and functional prediction of differentially expressed circular RNAs in human glioma of different grades.
description: Our findings indicated that 4 circRNAs (hsa_circ_0000915, hsa_circ_0127664, hsa_circ_0008362, and hsa_circ_0001467) are associated with the pathological characteristics of glioma and revealed critical regulatory functions at multiple levels. The results presented here might provide vital molecular biomarkers and potential therapeutic targets for glioma.

title: Screening and functional prediction of differentially expressed circular RNAs in human glioma of different grades.
description: Our findings indicated that 4 circRNAs (hsa_circ_0000915, hsa_circ_0127664, hsa_circ_0008362, and hsa_circ_0001468) are associated with the pathological characteristics of glioma and revealed critical regulatory functions at multiple levels. The results presented here might provide vital molecular biomarkers and potential therapeutic targets for glioma.

title: Screening and functional prediction of differentially expressed circular RNAs in human glioma of different grades.
description: Our findings indicated that 4 circRNAs (hsa_circ_0000915, hsa_circ_0127664, hsa_circ_0008362, and hsa_circ_0001469) are associated with the pathological characteristics of glioma and revealed critical regulatory functions at multiple levels. The results presented here might provide vital molecular biomarkers and potential therapeutic targets for glioma.

title: Screening and functional prediction of differentially expressed circular RNAs in human glioma of different grades.
description: Our findings indicated that 4 circRNAs (hsa_circ_0000915, hsa_circ_0127664, hsa_circ_0008362, and hsa_circ_0001470) are associated with the pathological characteristics of glioma and revealed critical regulatory functions at multiple levels. The results presented here might provide vital molecular biomarkers and potential therapeutic targets for glioma.

title: Hsa_circ_0000069 Knockdown Inhibits Tumorigenesis and Exosomes with Downregulated hsa_circ_0000069 Suppress Malignant Transformation via Inhibition of STIL in Pancreatic Cancer.
description: hsa_circ_0000069 knockdown could inhibit pancreatic cancer tumorigenesis and exosomes with downregulated hsa_circ_0000069 could suppress HPDE cell malignant transformation.

title: CircRNA_102272 Promotes Cisplatin-Resistance in Hepatocellular Carcinoma by Decreasing MiR-326 Targeting of RUNX2.
description: CircRNA_102272 is significantly increased in HCC tissues and cells and promotes HCC cell proliferation and cisplatin-resistance.

title: Cisplatin-resistant osteosarcoma cell-derived exosomes confer cisplatin resistance to recipient cells in an exosomal circ_103801-dependent manner.
description: serum exosomal hsa_circ_103801 may serve as an effective prognostic biomarker for OS.

title: Differential expression of circular RNAs in bone marrow-derived exosomes from essential thrombocythemia patients.
description: circDAP3, circASXL1 and circRUNX1 were significantly down-regulated in ET patients when compared with healthy people. And we confirmed that circ_0014614 could inhibit K562 cells differentiate into megakaryocytes.

title: Differential expression of circular RNAs in bone marrow-derived exosomes from essential thrombocythemia patients.
description: circDAP3, circASXL1 and circRUNX1 were significantly down-regulated in ET patients when compared with healthy people. And we confirmed that circ_0014614 could inhibit K562 cells differentiate into megakaryocytes.

title: Differential expression of circular RNAs in bone marrow-derived exosomes from essential thrombocythemia patients.
description: circDAP3, circASXL1 and circRUNX1 were significantly down-regulated in ET patients when compared with healthy people. And we confirmed that circ_0014614 could inhibit K562 cells differentiate into megakaryocytes.

title: [Over-expression of circNR4A1/Hsa-circ-0026352 inhibits proliferation and induces apoptosis in MCF-7 cells].
description: Over-expression of circNR4A1 can inhibit cell proliferation and induce cell apoptosis in MCF-7 cells.

title: Identification, biogenesis and function prediction of novel circRNA during the chicken ALV-J infection.
description: Bioinformatics analysis results showed that circRNA_3079 and the predicted target genes are enriched in many pathways related to immunity or tumors, such as p53 signaling pathway, JakSTAT signaling pathway and NODlike receptor signaling pathway, which revealed that circRNA_3079 may indirectly regulate the ALV-J infection process through the regulation of target genes.

title: Association study of hsa_circ_0001946, hsa-miR-7-5p and PARP1 in coronary atherosclerotic heart disease.
description: The present work demonstrated the predictive power of hsa_circ_0001946, hsa-miR-7-5p and PARP1 as combined biomarkers for CHD, and suggests a regulatory axis they consisted might contribute to the CHD development.

title: CircDUSP16 Contributes to Cell Development in Esophageal Squamous Cell Carcinoma by Regulating miR-497-5p/TKTL1 Axis.
description: CircDUSP16 knockdown suppressed hypoxia-induced ESCC cell growth, invasion, and glycolysis by regulating TKTL1 expression through sponging miR-497-5p.

title: Diagnostic and Therapeutic Value of Hsa_circ_0002594 for T Helper 2-Mediated Allergic Asthma.
description: hsa_circ_0002594 was upregulated in CD4+ T cells and might have potential value in the diagnosis and treatment of Th2-mediated allergic asthma.

title: Circular RNA 0001313 Knockdown Suppresses Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Cell Proliferation and Invasion via the microRNA-452/HMGB3/ERK/MAPK Axis.
description: circ0001313 blunted the ERK/MAPK pathway via the miR-452/HMGB3 axis.

title: Expression Profile of Circular RNAs in Oral Squamous Cell Carcinoma.
description: knocking down circRNA0001766 inhibited the expression of VEGFA and the proliferation of OSCC cells.

title: CircASH2L Promotes Ovarian Cancer Tumorigenesis, Angiogenesis, and Lymphangiogenesis by Regulating the miR-665/VEGFA Axis as a Competing Endogenous RNA.
description: circASH2L plays a critical role in regulating ovarian cancer cell tumorigenesis, angiogenesis, and lymphangiogenesis through the miR-665/VEGFA axis.

title: Expression Profiles of Circular RNA in Human Atrial Fibrillation With Valvular Heart Diseases.
description: This study provided a preliminary landscaping of circRNAs expression profiles which are involved in persistent AF due to VHD, and established the probability for future related researches in this field.

title: Expression Profiles of Circular RNA in Human Atrial Fibrillation With Valvular Heart Diseases.
description: This study provided a preliminary landscaping of circRNAs expression profiles which are involved in persistent AF due to VHD, and established the probability for future related researches in this field.

description: This study provided a preliminary landscaping of circRNAs expression profiles which are involved in persistent AF due to VHD, and established the probability for future related researches in this field.

title: Expression Profiles of Circular RNA in Human Atrial Fibrillation With Valvular Heart Diseases.
description: This study provided a preliminary landscaping of circRNAs expression profiles which are involved in persistent AF due to VHD, and established the probability for future related researches in this field.

title: Knockdown of circ_0006528 Suppresses Cell Proliferation, Migration, Invasion, and Adriamycin Chemoresistance via Regulating the miR-1236-3p/CHD4 Axis in Breast Cancer.
description: Downregulation of circ_0006528 restrained cell proliferation, migration, invasion, and drug resistance of ADM-resistant BCa cells through inhibiting CHD4 and inducing miR-1236-3p.

title: circ_0067934: A Potential Biomarker and Therapeutic Target for Hepatocellular Carcinoma.
description: circ_0067934 may function as a potential biomarker for the diagnosis and prognosis of HCC.

title: A Circular RNA Derived from Golgi Glycoprotein 1 mRNA Regulates KRAS Expression and Promotes Colorectal Cancer Progression by Targeting microRNA-622.
description: Circ_GLG1 promoted KRAS expression at both the mRNA and protein levels by acting as an miR-622 sponge.

title: Oxidative Stress-Induced circHBEGF Promotes Extracellular Matrix Production via Regulating miR-646/EGFR in Human Trabecular Meshwork Cells.
description: circHBEGF could competitively bind to miR-646 as a miRNA sponge to regulate EGFR expression in HTMCs.

title: Circular RNA circ_SETD2 represses breast cancer progression via modulating the miR-155-5p/SCUBE2 axis.
description: circ_SETD2 curbed BC progression via upregulating SCUBE2 via binding to miR-155-5p.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0007121 regulates proliferation, migration, invasion, and epithelial-mesenchymal transition of trophoblast cells by miR-182-5p/PGF axis in preeclampsia.
description: Hsa_circ_0007121 mediated the progression of PE via miR-182-5p/PGF axis.

title: Circular RNA circ_0000034 upregulates STX17 level to promote human retinoblastoma development via inhibiting miR-361-3p.
description: circ_0000034 knockdown suppressed the development of RB by the modulation of miR-361-3p/STX17 axis.

title: Circular RNA ZNF292 affects proliferation and apoptosis of hepatocellular carcinoma cells by regulating Wnt/beta-catenin pathway.
description: Knock downing circRNA ZNF292 leads to cell cycle arrest in G1 phase, thus suppressing cell proliferation and promoting cell apoptosis.

title: Circ-ABCB10 promotes growth and metastasis of nasopharyngeal carcinoma by upregulating ROCK1.
description: circ-ABCB10 promoted NPC cell proliferation and metastasis via upregulating ROCK1 in vitro.

title: CircRNA_100395 protects breast carcinoma deterioration by targeting MAPK6.
description: CircRNA_100395 serves as an anti-cancer gene in breast carcinoma progression by targeting MAPK6.

title: Hsa_circ_0000337 promotes proliferation, migration and invasion in glioma by competitively binding miRNA-942-5p and thus upregulates MAT2A.
description: hsa_circ_0000337 sponged miRNA-942-5p to upregulate MAT2A, thus inducing the malignant phenotypes of glioma.

title: Three CircRNAs Function as Potential Biomarkers for Colorectal Cancer.
description: circ-FMN2, circ-LMNB1, and circ-ZNF609 may function as potential diagnostic and prognostic indicators for CRC detection.

title: Three CircRNAs Function as Potential Biomarkers for Colorectal Cancer.
description: circ-FMN2, circ-LMNB1, and circ-ZNF609 may function as potential diagnostic and prognostic indicators for CRC detection.

title: Three CircRNAs Function as Potential Biomarkers for Colorectal Cancer.
description: circ-FMN2, circ-LMNB1, and circ-ZNF609 may function as potential diagnostic and prognostic indicators for CRC detection.

title: CircAMOTL1 Promotes Tumorigenesis Through miR-526b/SIK2 Axis in Cervical Cancer.
description: circAMOTL1 exerted an oncogenic role in cervical cancer progression through sponging miR-526b.

title: HSA_CIRC_0004050 on proliferation and apoptosis of A549 cells through ERK/JNK signaling pathway.
description: hsa_circ_0004050 could markedly increase the protein expression of DUSP9 via targeting miR-1233-3p in A549 cells, thereby inhibiting the ERK/JNK signaling pathway.

title: Circular RNA ITCH mediates H(2)O(2)-induced myocardial cell apoptosis by targeting miR-17-5p via wnt/beta-catenin signalling pathway.
description: Circ-ITCH could protect myocardial cells from injuries caused by H2O2 by suppressing apoptosis while miR-17-5p played a reverse role.

title: Hsa_circ_0075960 Serves as a Sponge for miR-361-3p/SH2B1 in Endometrial Carcinoma.
description: hsa_circ_0075960 functioned as a sponge for miR-361-3p/SH2B1 in EC cells and regulated the progression of EC through the modulation of miR-361-3p.

title: Circ-CCS is identified as a cancer-promoting circRNA in lung cancer partly by regulating the miR-383/E2F7 axis.
description: Circ-CCS was shown to facilitate lung cancer progression via the miR-383/E2F7 axis.

title: Circ_DHRS3 positively regulates GREM1 expression by competitively targeting miR-183-5p to modulate IL-1beta-administered chondrocyte proliferation, apoptosis and ECM degradation.
description: Circ_DHRS3 mediated IL-1beta-administered chondrocyte proliferation, apoptosis and ECM degradation by positively regulating GREM1 expression via competitively targeting miR-183-5p.

title: CircRNA-SORE mediates sorafenib resistance in hepatocellular carcinoma by stabilizing YBX1.
description: silencing circRNA-SORE by injection of siRNA could substantially overcome sorafenib resistance.

title: CircRNA_ACAP2 Suppresses EMT in Head and Neck Squamous Cell Carcinoma by Targeting the miR-21-5p/STAT3 Signaling Axis.
disease_details: head and neck squamous cell carcinoma
description: CircRNA_ACAP2 functions as a tumor suppressor gene in HNSCC and that its function is regulated via the miR-21-5p/STAT3 signaling axis.

title: Hsa_circ_0046263 Drives the Carcinogenesis and Metastasis of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Through the Promotion of NOVA2 by Absorbing Mir-940 as a Molecular Sponge.
description: Hsa_circ_0046263 was identified as a cancer-promoting factor in NSCLC via sponging miR-940 and upregulating NOVA2.

title: Circ-PRKDC Facilitates the Progression of Colorectal Cancer Through miR-198/DDR1 Regulatory Axis.
description: Knockdown of circ-PRKDC inhibited CRC progression via modulating miR-198/DDR1 pathway.

title: CircPVT1 Regulates Cell Proliferation, Apoptosis and Glycolysis in Hepatocellular Carcinoma via miR-377/TRIM23 Axis.
description: CircPVT1 aggravated the progression of HCC by upregulating TRIM23 via sponging miR-377.

title: Circular RNA circ_DROSHA alleviates the neural damage in a cell model of temporal lobe epilepsy through regulating miR-106b-5p/MEF2C axis.
description: enforced expression of circ_DROSHA alleviated the cell damage of the TLE cell model at least in part through the regulation of the miR-106b-5p/MEF2C axis.

title: CircASPH promotes KGN cells proliferation through miR-375/MAP2K6 axis in Polycystic Ovary Syndrome.
description: circASPH promotes KGN cells proliferation through miR-375/MAP2K6 axis in PCOS.

title: N(6) -methyladenosine modification of circular RNA circ-ARL3 facilitates Hepatitis B virus-associated hepatocellular carcinoma via sponging miR-1305.
description: circ-ARL3 is a critical regulator in HBV-related HCC, targeting the axis of circ-ARL3/miR-1305 may be a promising treatment for HBV+ HCC patients.

title: Profiling and Integrated Analysis of Differentially Expressed Circular RNAs in Plasma Exosomes as Novel Biomarkers for Advanced-Stage Lung Adenocarcinoma.
description: We identified hsa_circ_0102537 to be downregulated in both LUAD plasma exosomes and tissues. GO, KEGG pathway analysis, circRNA-miRNA-mRNA meshwork, and further experiments suggest that hsa_circ_0102537 could be involved in LUAD progression.

title: hsa_circRNA_000166 Facilitated Cell Growth and Limited Apoptosis through Targeting miR-326/LASP1 Axis in Colorectal Cancer.
description: downregulation of hsa_circRNA_000166 inhibited the cell growth and facilitated apoptosis during CRC development by sponging the miR-326/LASP1 pathway.

title: circPHIP promotes oral squamous cell carcinoma progression by sponging miR-142-5p and regulating PHIP and ACTN4 expression.
description: circPHIP is overexpressed in OSCC and enhances its malignancy via an miR-142-5p/PHIP-ACTN4/AKT serine/threonine kinase 1 signaling axis.

title: Circular RNA circHIPK3 as a novel circRNA regulator of autophagy and endothelial cell dysfunction in atherosclerosis.
description: CircHIPK3 could inhibit lipid content in ox-LD-treated HUVECs via activating autophagy.

title: Knockdown of Circular RNA Hsa_circ_0000714 Can Regulate RAB17 by Sponging miR-370-3p to Reduce Paclitaxel Resistance of Ovarian Cancer Through CDK6/RB Pathway.
description: Hsa_circ_0000714 acts as a sponge for miR-370-3p, and regulates RAB17 expression through the CDK6/RB signaling pathway.

title: circBICD2 targets miR-149-5p/IGF2BP1 axis to regulate oral squamous cell carcinoma progression.
description: circBICD2 knockdown repressed OSCC cell proliferation, migration, invasion, and glutaminolysis and increased apoptosis via modulating miR-149-5p/IGF2BP1 axis, which might act as a potential target for OSCC treatment.

title: CircRNA-100284 activates aurora kinase B by inducing methylation of HSP70 via microRNA-217 to promote proliferation of bladder cancer cells.
description: CircRNA-100284 activates aurora kinase B by inducing methylation of HSP70 via microRNA-217 to promote the proliferation of bladder cancer cells.

title: Circ_0001247 functions as a miR-1270 sponge to accelerate cervical cancer progression by up-regulating ZEB2 expression level.
description: Circ_0001247 promotes progression of CC by sponging miR-1270 to upregulate ZEB2 expression level.

title: Circ_PGPEP1 Serves as a Sponge of miR-1297 to Promote Gastric Cancer Progression via Regulating E2F3.
description: Circ_PGPEP1 Serves as a Sponge of miR-1297 to Promote Gastric Cancer Progression via Regulating E2F3.

title: Circular PVT1 regulates cell proliferation and invasion via miR-149-5p/FOXM1 axis in ovarian cancer.
description: circular PVT1 increased FOXM1 level via binding to miR-149-5p and thus affected ovarian cancer cell viability and migration.

title: Circular RNA circDLC1 inhibits MMP1-mediated liver cancer progression via interaction with HuR.
description: circDLC1, a downstream target of KIAA1429, is a promising prognostic marker for HCC patients, and the circDLC1-HuR-MMP1 axis may serve as a potential therapeutic target for HCC treatment.

title: Circ-ZDHHC5 Accelerates Esophageal Squamous Cell Carcinoma Progression in vitro via miR-217/ZEB1 Axis.
description: circ-ZDHHC5 could impact on ESCC progression by sponging miR-217 with ZEB1.

title: Circ_0061012 contributes to IL-22-induced proliferation, migration and invasion in keratinocytes through miR-194-5p/GAB1 axis in psoriasis.
description: Circ_0061012 elevated the expression of GAB1 through sponging miR-194-5p in HaCaT cells. Circ_0061012 accelerated IL-22-induced proliferation and metastasis in HaCaT cells through enhancing GAB1 expression via sponging miR-194-5p in psoriasis.

title: CircNOL10 suppresses breast cancer progression by sponging miR-767-5p to regulate SOCS2/JAK/STAT signaling.
description: CircNOL10 repressed BC development via inactivation of JAK2/STAT5 signaling by regulating miR-767-5p/SOCS2 axis. Our findings offer the possibility of exploiting circNOL10 as a therapeutic and prognostic target for BC patients.

title: Circular RNA circLMO7 acts as a microRNA-30a-3p sponge to promote gastric cancer progression via the WNT2/beta-catenin pathway.
description: CircLMO7 promotes the development of GC by releasing the inhibitory effect of miR-30a-3p on its target gene WNT2.

title: Circular RNA RBM33 contributes to cervical cancer progression via modulation of the miR-758-3p/PUM2 axis.
description: CircRBM33 fostered CC advancement via absorbing miR-758-3p and upregulating PUM2, indicating that circRBM33 was a possible target for CC treatment.

title: Silencing of circHIPK3 Inhibits Pressure Overload-Induced Cardiac Hypertrophy and Dysfunction by Sponging miR-185-3p.
description: circHIPK3 serve as a miR-185-3p sponge to regulate cardiac hypertrophy revealing a potential new target for the prevention of TAC- and Ang-II induced cardiac hypertrophy.

title: CircRNA DNA methyltransferase 1 silence inhibits breast cancer development by regulating micoRNA-485-3p/zinc finger E-box binding homeobox 1 axis.
description: Circ-DNMT1 knockdown constrains breast cancer development via modulating miR-485-3p/ZEB1 axis.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0061395 accelerates hepatocellular carcinoma progression via regulation of the miR-877-5p/PIK3R3 axis.
description: Circ_0061395 facilitated HCC progression via regulating the miR-877-5p/PIK3R3 axis, providing a new perspective on the advancement of HCC.

title: Circ-CCDC66 upregulates REXO1 expression to aggravate cervical cancer progression via restraining miR-452-5p.
description: Our results demonstrated the role of circ-CCDC66/miR-452-5p/REXO1 axis in cervical cancer progression, we might provide novel therapeutic targets for cervical cancer clinical intervention.

title: Circ_0001175 Promotes Hepatocellular Carcinoma Cell Proliferation and Metastasis by Regulating miR-130a-5p.
description: Circ_0001175 is highly expressed in HCC and facilitates HCC progression through regulating miR-130a-5p/SNX5 axis.

title: Circular RNA circGSE1 Promotes Cervical Cancer Progression Through miR-138-5p/Vimentin.
description: CircGSE1 promotes the progression and may act as a novel diagnostic biomarker for disease progression of cervical cancer.

title: CircSKA3 Modulates FOXM1 to Facilitate Cell Proliferation, Migration, and Invasion While Confine Apoptosis in Medulloblastoma via miR-383-5p.
description: CircSKA3 augmented MB progression partly through miR-383-5p/FOXM1 axis.

title: Circ_101341 Deteriorates the Progression of Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma Through the miR- 411/EGLN3 Axis.
description: Circ_101341 functioned as a tumor promoter to strengthen proliferation, migration and invasion by regulating EGLN3 via sponging miR-411.

title: CircWHSC1 serves as an oncogene to promote hepatocellular carcinoma progression.
description: CircWHSC1 played a tumour-promoting role in HCC by elevating HOXA1 through sponging miR-142-3p.

title: Downregulation of circFASTKD1 ameliorates myocardial infarction by promoting angiogenesis.
description: circFASTKD1 is a potent inhibitor of angiogenesis after myocardial infarction and that silencing circFASTKD1 exerts therapeutic effects during hypoxia by stimulating angiogenesis in vitro and in vivo.

title: Circ-FOXM1 knockdown suppresses non-small cell lung cancer development by regulating the miR-149-5p/ATG5 axis.
description: circ-FOXM1 knockdown attenuated the development of NSCLC through modulating the miR-149-5p/ATG5 axis, providing a theoretical basis for the therapy of NSCLC.

title: CircRNA PIP5K1A promotes the progression of glioma through upregulation of the TCF12/PI3K/AKT pathway by sponging miR-515-5p.
description: CircPIP5K1A is a potential prognostic marker in glioma and regulates glioma evolvement by modulating the miR-515-5p-mediated TCF12/PI3K/AKT axis.

title: Downregulation of circ-TRPS1 suppressed prostatic cancer prognoses by regulating miR-124-3p/EZH2 axis-mediated stemness.
description: circ-TRPS1 suppressed PCa progression through functioning similar to a miR-124-3p sponge to enhance EZH2 expression and cancer stem-like cell differentiation.

title: Downregulation of hsa_circ_0026123 suppresses ovarian cancer cell metastasis and proliferation through the miR_124_3p/EZH2 signaling pathway.
description: hsa_circ_0026123 knockdown inhibited OVA cell progression by regulating the miR_124_3p/EZH2 axis.

title: Circular RNA CSNK1G1 promotes the progression of osteoarthritis by targeting the miR_4428/FUT2 axis.
description: circCSNK1G1 promotes the development of OA by targeting the miR_4428/FUT2 axis.

title: circHIPK3 promotes proliferation and migration and invasion via regulation of miR_637/HDAC4 signaling in osteosarcoma cells.
description: circHIPK3 sponged miR_637 to promote HDAC4 expression and OS cell proliferation, migration and invasion.

title: Hsa_circ_0016760 exacerbates the malignant development of non_small cell lung cancer by sponging miR_145_5p/FGF5.
description: hsa_circ_0016760 exacerbated the malignant development of NSCLC by sponging miR_145_5p/FGF5.

title: circ_0044516 functions in the progression of gastric cancer by modulating MicroRNA-149-5p/HuR axis.
description: circ_0044516 may promote HuR expression through sponging miR-149-5p, thereby playing a part in GC progression.

title: Identification of Circular RNA hsa_Circ_0003391 in Peripheral Blood Is Potentially Associated With Alzheimer Disease.
description: downregulation of hsa_circ_0003391 in the peripheral blood has a potential relationship with AD.

title: Cyclic RNA Circ_0000735 sponges miR-502-5p to promote bladder cancer cell proliferation and invasion and inhibit apoptosis.
description: Circ_0000735 can adsorb miR-502-5p to promote bladder cancer cell proliferation and invasion and inhibit apoptosis.

title: circRNA circARNT2 Suppressed the Sensitivity of Hepatocellular Carcinoma Cells to Cisplatin by Targeting the miR-155-5p/PDK1 Axis.
description: circARNT2 acts as a sponge for miR-155-5p and verified that PDK1 is a novel target of miR-155-5p.

title: CircMEG3 inhibits telomerase activity by reducing Cbf5 in human liver cancer stem cells.
description: CircMEG3 inhibits telomerase activity and shortens telomere lifespan dependent on HULC and Cbf5 in human liver cancer stem cell.

title: circDCUN1D4 suppresses tumor metastasis and glycolysis in lung adenocarcinoma by stabilizing TXNIP expression.
description: circDCUN1D4 suppressed metastasis and glycolysis of lung cancer cells in a TXNIP-dependent manner.

title: CircRNA_000864 Upregulates B-cell Translocation Gene 2 Expression and Represses Migration and Invasion in Pancreatic Cancer Cells by Binding to miR-361-3p.
description: the overexpression of circRNA_000864 could promote BTG2 expression to inhibit pancreatic cancer development by binding to miR-361-3p.

title: CircHmbox1 Targeting miRNA-1247-5p Is Involved in the Regulation of Bone Metabolism by TNF-alpha in Postmenopausal Osteoporosis.
description: circHmbox1-targeting miR-1247-5p is involved in the regulation of bone metabolisms by TNF-alpha in PMOP .

title: CircRNA_25487 inhibits bone repair in trauma-induced osteonecrosis of femoral head by sponging miR-134-3p through p21.
description: CircRNA_25487 suppression and miR-134-3p overexpression could promote cell proliferation and invasion while inhibited apoptosis of BMSCs and OLCs. miR-134-3p could target p21. CircRNA_25487 inhibited bone repair in TIONFH by sponging miR-134-3p to upregulate the expression of p21.

title: Circular RNA circ_0068,888 protects against lipopolysaccharide-induced HK-2 cell injury via sponging microRNA-21-5p.
description: hsa_circ_0068,888 shows a protective effect on AKI by sponging miR-21-5p. Hence, up-regulation of hsa_circ_0068,888 might be a potential strategy in treatment for AKI.

title: As a biomarker for gastric cancer, circPTPN22 regulates the progression of gastric cancer through the EMT pathway.
description: CircPTPN22 can be used as a potential diagnostic and prognostic marker for GC and can inhibit cell proliferation and metastasis through the competitive binding of miRNA to inhibit the EMT pathway.

title: Circular RNA hsa_Circ_0005795 mediates cell proliferation of cutaneous basal cell carcinoma via sponging miR-1231.
description: Circ_0005795 works as an oncogene in BCC, which might be used as a promising biomarker and a potential therapeutic target for BCC diagnosis and treatment.

title: Circular RNA circZFR Promotes Hepatocellular Carcinoma Progression by Regulating miR-375/HMGA2 Axis.
description: Knockdown of circZFR suppressed the progression of HCC by upregulating miR-375 and downregulating HMGA2, providing new insight into the pathogenesis of HCC.

title: Lidocaine Inhibits Hepatocellular Carcinoma Development by Modulating circ_ITCH/miR-421/CPEB3 Axis.
description: Lidocaine represses hepatocellular carcinoma cell proliferation, migration, and invasion and promotes apoptosis via regulating circ_ITCH/miR-421/CPEB3 axis, indicating a new insight into the mechanism of lidocaine in hepatocellular carcinoma.

title: Circular RNA circ_0081001 knockdown enhances methotrexate sensitivity in osteosarcoma cells by regulating miR-494-3p/TGM2 axis.
description: Knockdown of circ_0081001 enhanced MTX sensitivity of OS cells through downregulating TGM2 by sponging miR-494-3p, elucidating a novel regulatory mechanism for chemoresistance of OS and providing a potential circRNA-targeted therapy for OS.

title: Hsa_circ_0123190 acts as a competitive endogenous RNA to regulate APLNR expression by sponging hsa-miR-483-3p in lupus nephritis.
description: Hsa_circ_0123190 may function as a ceRNA to regulate APLNR expression by sponging hsa-miR-483-3p in LN.

title: Hsa_circ_0005273 facilitates breast cancer tumorigenesis by regulating YAP1-hippo signaling pathway.
description: Hsa_circ_0005273 regulates the miR-200a-3p/YAP1 axis and inactivates Hippo signaling pathway to promote BC progression, which may become a potential biomarker and therapeutic target.

title: circNDUFB2 inhibits non-small cell lung cancer progression via destabilizing IGF2BPs and activating anti-tumor immunity.
description: circNDUFB2 participates in the degradation of IGF2BPs and activation of anti-tumor immunity during NSCLC progression via the modulation of both protein ubiquitination and degradation, as well as cellular immune responses.

title: Identification of circ-FAM169A sponges miR-583 involved in the regulation of intervertebral disc degeneration.
description: circ-FAM169A-miR-583 pathway may regulate NPCs apoptosis and extracellular matrix synthesis and catabolism by targeting Sox9.

title: Astragaloside IV alleviates atherosclerosis through targeting circ_0000231/miR-135a-5p/CLIC4 axis in AS cell model in vitro.
description: ASV protected HUVECs against ox-LDL-induced injury through targeting circ_0000231/miR-135a-5p/CLIC4 axis. Targeting circ_0000231/miR-135a-5p/CLIC4 axis might provide a novel insight to develop effective strategy for AS treatment.

title: CircRNA hsa_circ_0030018 regulates the development of glioma via regulating the miR-1297/RAB21 axis.
description: The hsa_circ_0030018 knockdown repressed glioma progression by mediating the miR-1297/RAB21 pathway, providing potential therapeutic targets for glioma treatment.

title: Circ_0006404 Accelerates Prostate Cancer Progression Through Regulating miR-1299/CFL2 Signaling.
description: Circ_0006404 accelerated the survival, motility and proliferation while impeded the apoptosis of PCa cells via miR-1299/CFL2 axis. Circ_0006404 might be a stable potential bio-marker for PCa diagnosis and treatment.

title: Circ_0007444 Inhibits the Progression of Ovarian Cancer via Mediating the miR-570-3p/PTEN Axis.
description: circ_0007444 is a tumor suppressor in OC, which inhibits OC progression by mediating the miR-570-3p/PTEN. circ_0007444 can be a potential candidate for targeted therapy of OC.

title: Circular RNA circ_0020123 Promotes Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Progression Through miR-384/TRIM44 Axis.
description: circ_0020123 knockdown suppressed NSCLC cell progression by regulating the miR-384/TRIM44 axis, providing the theoretical basis for the therapy of NSCLC.

title: AUF1 ligand circPCNX reduces cell proliferation by competing with p21 mRNA to increase p21 production.
description: we propose that the interaction of circPCNX with AUF1 selectively prevents AUF1 binding to p21 mRNA, leading to enhanced p21 mRNA stability and p21 protein production, thereby suppressing cell growth.

title: Knockdown of cir_RNA PVT1 Elevates Gastric Cancer Cisplatin Sensitivity via Sponging miR-152-3p.
description: CircPVT1 regulated the chemoresistance and malignancy of GC through modulating HDGF expression via sponging miR-152-3p, providing a theoretical basis for the development of effective therapeutic strategies for GC.

title: Reduced expression of circRNA novel_circ_0005280 and its clinical value in the diagnosis of non-small cell lung cancer.
description: Novel_circ_0005280 may be a useful biomarker for the diagnosis and prognosis of NSCLC.

title: The decreased expression of hsa_circ_0043278 and its relationship with clinicopathological features of breast cancer.
description: hsa_circ_0043278 is downregulated and may play a key role in human breast cancer.

title: Circ_0004104 Accelerates the Progression of Gastric Cancer by Regulating the miR-539-3p/RNF2 Axis.
description: Circ_0004104 accelerated GC progression via regulating the miR-539-3p/RNF2 axis, indicating that circ_0004104 might be a potential therapeutic target for GC.

title: Plasma Exosomal CircNEK9 Accelerates the Progression of Gastric Cancer via miR-409-3p/MAP7 Axis.
description: CircNEK9 accelerated the proliferation, migration, and invasion of GC cells through targeting miR-409-3p/MAP7 axis. Plasma exosomal circNEK9 promoted the migration and invasion of recipient GC cells.

title: CircPVT1 promotes progression in clear cell renal cell carcinoma by sponging miR-145-5p and regulating TBX15 expression.
description: circPVT1 promotes ccRCC growth and metastasis through sponging miR-145-5p and regulating downstream target TBX15 expression. The circPVT1/miR-145-5p/TBX15 axis might be a potential diagnostic marker and therapeutic target in ccRCC.

title: Circ_SMAD4 promotes gastric carcinogenesis by activating wnt/beta-catenin pathway.
description: Circ_SMAD4 facilitated GC tumorigenesis by activating CTNNB1-dependent Wnt/beta-catenin pathway. Hopefully, the findings could provide new clues for improving GC prognosis and treatment.

title: FUS-induced circular RNA ZNF609 promotes tumorigenesis and progression via sponging miR-142-3p in lung cancer.
description: FUS-induced circZNF609 exerts promotional effects on LC cell proliferation and migration through modulation of the miR-142-3p/GNB2 axis.

title: Circular RNA circSDHC serves as a sponge for miR-127-3p to promote the proliferation and metastasis of renal cell carcinoma via the CDKN3/E2F1 axis.
description: Our data indicates, for the first time, an essential role for the circSDHC/miR-127-3p/CDKN3/E2F1 axis in RCC progression. Thus, circSDHC has potential to be a new therapeutic target in patients with RCC.

title: Knockdown of circ-FANCA alleviates LPS-induced HK2 cell injury via targeting miR-93-5p/OXSR1 axis in septic acute kidney injury.
description: Circ-FANCA knockdown attenuated LPS-induced HK2 cell injury by regulating OXSR1 expression via targeting miR-93-5p.

title: Up-Regulation of circEIF6 Contributes to Pancreatic Cancer Development Through Targeting miR-557/SLC7A11/PI3K/AKT Signaling.
description: CircEIF6 aggravated pancreatic cancer development through promoting cell proliferation, migration and invasion and suppressing cell apoptosis through targeting miR-557/SLC7A11/PI3K/AKT signaling.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0000554 promotes progression and elevates radioresistance through the miR-485-5p/fermitin family members 1 axis in esophageal cancer.
description: FERMT1 enhancement reversed circ_0000554 inhibition-mediated effects on the colony formation, migration, invasion, radiosensitivity and apoptosis of esophageal cancer cells. Circ_0000554 silencing repressed EC progression and enhanced cell radiosensitivity through downregulating FERMT1 via sponging miR-485-5p, which provided a possible method for improving the radioresistence of esophageal cancer.

title: Silencing of circular RNA PUM1 inhibits clear cell renal cell carcinoma progression through the miR-340-5p/FABP7 axis.
description: CircPUM1 upregulates FABP7 expression by competitively binding to miR-340-5p, and then activates the MEK/ERK pathway, thus promoting ccRCC progression.

title: Circular RNA circ_0008274 enhances the malignant progression of papillary thyroid carcinoma via modulating solute carrier family 7 member 11 by sponging miR-154-3p.
description: the knockdown of circ_0008274 repressed PTC malignant progression at least in part through regulating the miR-154-3p/SLC7A11 axis, providing a promising therapeutic opportunity for PTC treatment.

title: Hsa_circ_0001073 targets miR-626/LIFR axis to inhibit lung cancer progression.
description: circ_0001073 represses lung cancer progression via miR-626/LIFR axis, indicating the potential value of circ_0001073 in lung cancer treatment.

title: Circular RNA circRUNX1 promotes papillary thyroid cancer progression and metastasis by sponging MiR-296-3p and regulating DDHD2 expression.
description: The strong antitumor effect of miR-296-3p and the tumor-promoting effect of DDHD2 were further investigated in PTC, indicating that circRUNX1 modulates PTC progression through the miR-296-3p/DDHD2 pathway. Overall, circRUNX1 plays an oncogenic role in PTC and provides a potentially effective therapeutic strategy for PTC progression.

title: Circular RNA circNINL promotes breast cancer progression through activating beta-catenin signaling via miR-921/ADAM9 axis.
description: we demonstrated that circNINL could interact with miR-921 and facilitate BC cells malignant process including proliferation acceleration, migration enhancement and apoptosis evasion via sponging miR-921 in vitro. Further investigations revealed that circNINL/miR-921 axis could mediate the expression of ADAM9 which was a direct target of miR-921.

title: circGFRA1 affects the sensitivity of triple-negative breast cancer cells to paclitaxel via the miR-361-5p/TLR4 pathway.
description: circGFRA1 knockdown can inhibit the resistance of TNBC cells to PTX by promoting the expression of miR-361-5p, and subsequently reduce the expression of TLR4.

title: CircCAMSAP1 promotes hepatocellular carcinoma progression through miR-1294/GRAMD1A pathway.
description: CircCAMSAP1 was up-regulated in HCC tissues, and circCAMSAP1 up-regulated GRAMD1A expression to promote HCC proliferation, migration and invasion through miR-1294. CircCAMSAP1 might be a potential prognosis and therapeutic target for HCC.

title: Silencing circ-USP1 protects the renal tubular from kidney injury induced by hypoxia via modulating miR-194-5p/DNMT3A axis in acute renal allografts.
description: silencing circ-USP1 reduced DNMT3A expression in the kidney of mice that received renal allografts. Circ-USP1 functions as a competing endogenous RNA for miR-194-5p. This occurs in order to regulate DNMT3A expression in kidney injury induced by hypoxia in acute renal allografts.

title: Hsa_circ_0006571 promotes spinal metastasis through sponging microRNA-138 to regulate sirtuin 1 expression in lung adenocarcinoma.
description: Hsa_circ_0006571 promoted tumor cell migration and invasion via the miR-138/Sirt1 pathway.

title: CircRNAs Dysregulated in Juvenile Myelomonocytic Leukemia: CircMCTP1 Stands Out.
description: In conclusion, this study provides insight into the circRNAome of JMML and paves the path to elucidate new molecular disease mechanisms putting forward circMCTP1 up-regulation as a robust example.

title: Circular RNA CircNOLC1, Upregulated by NF-KappaB, Promotes the Progression of Prostate Cancer via miR-647/PAQR4 Axis.
description: CircNOLC1, elevated by transcription factor NF-kappaB, promotes PCa progression via a miR-647/PAQR4 axis, and circNOLC1 is a potential biomarker and target for PCa treatment.

title: Hsa_circ_0010235 functions as an oncogenic drive in non-small cell lung cancer by modulating miR-433-3p/TIPRL axis.
description: Hsa_circ_0010235 knockdown suppressed NSCLC progression by regulating miR-433-3p/TIPRL axis, affording a novel mechanism of NSCLC progression.

title: Circular RNA 0081146 facilitates the progression of gastric cancer by sponging miR-144 and up-regulating HMGB1.
description: Circ_0081146 functions as an oncogene in GC to promote cell growth, migration and invasion via modulating the miR-144/HMGB1 axis.

title: Circular RNA ITCH suppresses metastasis of gastric cancer via regulating miR-199a-5p/Klotho axis.
description: circ-ITCH suppresses metastasis of GC by acting as the sponge of miR-199a-5p and increasing Klotho expression, which serves as a potential biomarker and targets for the diagnosis and therapy of GC.

title: Circular RNA FLNA acts as a sponge of miR-486-3p in promoting lung cancer progression via regulating XRCC1 and CYP1A1.
description: circFLNA acted as a sponge of miR-486-3p to promote the proliferation, migration, and invasion of lung cancer cells in vitro and in vivo by regulating XRCC1 and CYP1A1.

title: CircSKA3 Downregulates miR-1 Through Methylation in Glioblastoma to Promote Cancer Cell Proliferation.
description: circSKA3 may downregulate miR-1 through methylation in GBM to promote cancer cell proliferation.

title: circRNA_141539 can serve as an oncogenic factor in esophageal squamous cell carcinoma by sponging miR-4469 and activating CDK3 gene.
description: circRNA_141539 served as an oncogenic factor in ESCC by sponging miR-4469 and activating CDK3 expression. circRNA_141539 may present as a novel diagnostic and prognostic biomarker and a therapeutic target for patients with ESCC.

title: Propofol suppresses lung cancer tumorigenesis by modulating the circ-ERBB2/miR-7-5p/FOXM1 axis.
description: Propofol inhibited lung cancer progression via mediating circ-ERBB2/miR-7-5p/FOXM1 axis, which might provide an effective therapeutic target for lung cancer therapy.

title: Circular RNA CircMTO1 suppressed proliferation and metastasis of osteosarcoma through miR-630/KLF6 axis.
description: circMTO1 could suppress osteosarcoma progression by regulating miR-630/KLF6 axis, which may highlight the diagnostic and therapeutic potential of these molecules in osteosarcoma treatment.

title: Upregulated circRNA hsa_circ_0071036 promotes tumourigenesis of pancreatic cancer by sponging miR-489 and predicts unfavorable characteristics and prognosis.
description: upregulated hsa_circ_0071036 promotes PDAC pathogenesis and progression by directly sponging miR-489, which implies an important role for this circRNA-miRNA functional network.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0004277 Stimulates Malignant Phenotype of Hepatocellular Carcinoma and Epithelial-Mesenchymal Transition of Peripheral Cells.
description: exosomal circ-0004277 from HCC cells stimulates EMT of peripheral cells through cellular communication to further promote the invasion of HCC into normal surrounding tissues.

title: Circ_0003998 Regulates the Progression and Docetaxel Sensitivity of DTX-Resistant Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Cells by the miR-136-5p/CORO1C Axis.
description: Our present work identified that circ_0003998 regulated DTX-resistant NSCLC cell colony formation, apoptosis and DTX sensitivity at least partially by controlling CORO1C expression by sponging miR-136-5p, illuminating a rationale for developing circ_0003998 as a therapeutic target of chemoresistant NSCLC.

title: The circular RNA circZFR phosphorylates Rb promoting cervical cancer progression by regulating the SSBP1/CDK2/cyclin E1 complex.
description: circZFR bound with SSBP1, thereby promoting the assembly of CDK2/cyclin E1 complexes. The activation of CDK2/cyclin E1 complexes induced p-Rb phosphorylation, thus releasing activated E2F1 leading to cell cycle progression and cell proliferation.

title: Circular RNA AKT3 governs malignant behaviors of esophageal cancer cells by sponging miR-17-5p.
description: CircAKT3 contributed to the malignant behaviors of esophageal cancer in vitro and in vivo by sponging miR-17-5p thus providing a potential target for treatment of esophageal cancer.

title: Circular RNA circPHC3 Promotes Cell Death and Apoptosis in Human BMECs After Oxygen Glucose Deprivation via miR-455-5p/TRAF3 Axis in vitro.
description: circPHC3 promotes cell death and apoptosis in ischemic stroke in vitro model, which might be a novel molecular target for acute cerebrovascular protection.

title: Circular RNA circSEC24A Promotes Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma Progression by Regulating miR-1193/MAP3K9 Axis.
description: CircSEC24A interference suppressed the progression of CSCC by regulating miR-1193/MAP3K9 axis, which might be a promising strategy for CSCC treatment.

title: A circGLIS3/miR-644a/PTBP1 positive feedback loop promotes the malignant biological progressions of non-small cell lung cancer.
description: CircGLIS3 functions as an oncogene via sponging multiple tumor-suppressive miRNAs in NSCLC. A circGLIS3/miR-644a/PTBP1 positive feedback loop exists in the tumorigenesis and development of NSCLC.

title: CircularRNA circPARP4 promotes glioblastoma progression through sponging miR-125a-5p and regulating FUT4.
description: Our findings illustrate functions of circPARP4 in modulating glioma progression through miR-125a-5p/FUT4 pathway, which provides a novel and potential target for glioma therapy.

title: Circ0083429 Regulates Osteoarthritis Progression via the Mir-346/SMAD3 Axis.
description: Circ0083429 regulates the ECM via the regulation of the downstream miRNA-346/SMAD3 in human chondrocytes.

title: Hsa_circ_0020095 Promotes Oncogenesis and Cisplatin Resistance in Colon Cancer by Sponging miR-487a-3p and Modulating SOX9.
description: Circ_0020095 functions as an oncogene to accelerate CC cell proliferation, invasion, migration and cisplatin resistance through the miR-487a-3p/SOX9 axis.

title: Identification of circ_0089153/miR-608/EGFR p53 axis in ameloblastoma via MAPK signaling pathway.
description: Six novel circRNAs were identified. Hsa_circ_0089153/hsa-miR-608 sponging was validated, hsa-miR-608 downregulated EGFR and p53, which might further regulate cell proliferation, differentiation, apoptosis, and cell cycle processes via the MAPK signaling pathway.

title: CircTM7SF3 contributes to oxidized low-density lipoprotein-induced apoptosis, inflammation and oxidative stress through targeting miR-206/ASPH axis in atherosclerosis cell model in vitro.
description: CircTM7SF3 contributed to ox-LDL-induced injury in AS cell model through up-regulating the expression of ASPH via targeting miR-206.

title: CircNR3C2 promotes HRD1-mediated tumor-suppressive effect via sponging miR-513a-3p in triple-negative breast cancer.
description: we elucidated a bona fide circNR3C2/miR-513a-3p/HRD1/Vimentin axis that negatively regulates the metastasis of TNBC, suggesting that circNR3C2 and HRD1 can act as potential prognostic biomarkers. Our study may facilitate the development of therapeutic agents targeting circNR3C2 and HRD1 for patients with aggressive breast cancer.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0009172 suppresses gastric cancer by regulation of microRNA-485-3p-mediated NTRK3.
description: Functionally, hsa_circ_0009172 overexpression inhibited proliferative, invasive and migrative potential of gastric cancer cells as well as epithelial-mesenchymal transition (EMT)-related proteins by sponging miR-485-3p to inhibit NTRK3, while miR-485-3p overexpression could reverse the inhibitory effect of hsa_circ_0009172 on gastric cancer.

title: Circ_0035483 Functions as a Tumor Promoter in Renal Cell Carcinoma via the miR-31-5p-Mediated HMGA1 Upregulation.
description: These findings clarified that the tumor-promoting function of circ_0035483 in RCC was partly achieved by regulating the miR-31-5p/HMGA1 axis.

title: Circ_0031242 Silencing Mitigates the Progression and Drug Resistance in DDP-Resistant Hepatoma Cells by the miR-924/POU3F2 Axis.
description: circ_0031242 functioned as an important regulator in DDP-resistant HCC cell progression and DDP resistance through the miR-924/POU3F2 axis, illuminating circ_0031242 as a potential therapeutic target for the chemoresistant HCC.

title: Circular RNA circEPSTI1 accelerates cervical cancer progression via miR-375/409-3P/515-5p-SLC7A11 axis.
description: our results revealed that circRNAs may also play very important roles in cervical cancer acting as miRNA sponges. We found that circEPSTI1-miR-375/409-3P/515-5p-SLC7A11 axis promotes the cervical cancer cell proliferation through a mechanism involving ceRNA.

title: Hsa_circ_0025202 suppresses cell tumorigenesis and tamoxifen resistance via miR-197-3p/HIPK3 axis in breast cancer.
description: Hsa_circ_0025202 repressed cell tumorigenesis and TAM resistance via miR-197-3p/HIPK3 axis in BC, suggesting a potential therapeutic strategy to overcome chemoresistance in BC patients.

title: Circ_TOP2A acts as a ceRNA for miR_346 and contributes to glioma progression via the modulation of sushi domain_containing 2.
description: circ_TOP2A promoted GM proliferation and aggressiveness via miR_346/SUSD2 signaling, which is a potential prognostic biomarker and therapeutic target for GM.

title: CircRNA_0000429 Regulates Development of NSCLC by Acting as a Sponge of miR-1197 to Control MADD.
description: circ_0000429 exhibited a carcinogenic role by sponging miR-1197 and regulating CMADD expression in NSCLC. These findings provided evidence for understanding the role of circ_0000429 in NSCLC tumorigenesis.

title: circEHBP1 promotes lymphangiogenesis and lymphatic metastasis of bladder cancer via miR-130a-3p/TGFbetaR1/VEGF-D signaling.
description: the circEHBP1/miR-130a-3p/TGFbetaR1/VEGF-D axis contributes to lymphangiogenesis and lymphatic metastasis of bladder cancer independent of VEGF-C, which might lead to the development of circEHBP1 as a potential biomarker and promising therapeutic target for lymphatic metastasis in bladder cancer.

title: Hsa_circ_0001696 modulates cell proliferation and migration in colorectal cancer.
description: hsa_circ_0001696 expression was downregulated in CRC tissues, and inhibition of hsa_circ_0001696 promoted cell proliferation and migration by regulating the levels of CDK4, cyclin D, cyclin E and MMP9.

title: Circular RNA circANKIB1 promotes the progression of osteosarcoma by regulating miR-217/PAX3 axis.
description: Knockdown of circANKIB1 suppressed OS progression by upregulating miR-217 and downregulating PAX3, which might provide a novel insight into the pathogenesis of OS.

title: Down-regulation of circular RNA hsa_circ_0007534 suppresses cell growth by regulating miR-219a-5p/SOX5 axis in osteosarcoma.
description: circ_0007534 knockdown suppressed the growth of OS cells via regulating miR-219a-5p/SOX5 axis, providing a potential target for OS treatment and diagnosis.

title: circ_NOTCH3 Functions as a Protooncogene Competing With miR-205-5p, Modulating KLF12 Expression and Promoting the Development and Progression of Basal-Like Breast Carcinoma.
description: circ_NOTCH3, being an protooncogene and a powerful biomarker, can function as a sponge, compete with miR-205-5p, modulate KLF12 expression, and promote the development and progression of BLBC.

title: Circular RNA circANKS1B acts as a sponge for miR-152-3p and promotes prostate cancer progression by upregulating TGF-alpha expression.
description: Knockdown of circANKS1B markedly suppressed cell migration and invasion and TGF-alpha expression in PC cells, whereas the effects of circANKS1B silencing were reversed by miR-152-3p deficiency. In addition, the impact of miR-152-3p silencing on invasion of circANKS1B-deficient PC cells was also abrogated by TGF-alpha deficiency. Overall, circANKS1B acts as a sponge for miR-152-3p to promote PC progression by upregulating TGF-alpha expression.

title: Circ_0000735 enhances the proliferation, metastasis and glycolysis of non-small cell lung cancer by regulating the miR-635/FAM83F axis.
description: Circ_0000735 promoted NSCLC progression by the miR-635/FAM83F axis, showing that circ_0000735 might be a promising biomarker for NSCLC. Highlights: Circ_0000735 knockdown represses NSCLC cell progression and tumor growth. Circ_0000735 functions as a miR-635 sponge. FAM83F is targeted by miR-635.

title: Circular RNA circHECTD1 facilitates glioma progression by regulating the miR-296-3p/SLC10A7 axis.
description: this study investigated a novel biomarker panel consisting of the circHECTD1/miR-296-3p/SLC10A7 axis, which is critical for glioma tumorigenesis and invasiveness and may represent a novel therapeutic target for intervening in glioma progression.

title: Repression of circRNA_000684 inhibits malignant phenotypes of pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma cells via miR-145-mediated KLF5.
description: CircRNA_000684 negatively regulated miR-145 expression, while miR-145 negatively regulated KLF5. In-vivo, circRNA_000684 elevation or miR-145 repression promoted tumor growth.

title: circST6GALNAC6 suppresses bladder cancer metastasis by sponging miR-200a-3p to modulate the STMN1/EMT axis.
description: Thus, our findings indicate an important underlying mechanism in BCa metastasis by which SP1-induced circST6GALNAC6 sponges miR-200a-3p to promote STMN1/EMT signalling. This mechanism could provide pivotal potential prognostic biomarkers and therapeutic targets for BCa.

title: Circ-AASDH functions as the progression of early stage lung adenocarcinoma by targeting miR-140-3p to activate E2F7 expression.
description: Circ-AASDH/miR-140-3p/E2F7 regulating axis promoted the progression in LUAD. Our results provided ideas for understanding the biological mechanism of circ-AASDH and clarify potential therapeutic targets in LUAD.

title: M6A modification of circNSUN2 promotes colorectal liver metastasis.
description: These discoveries not only expand our understanding of circRNAs biology in tumor, but also demonstrate that m6A modification plays a key role for circRNAs in RNA metabolism. Therefore, these findings indicate that circRNAs may be a new approach for therapeutic target of cancers.

title: Exosomal circ_PIP5K1A regulates the progression of non-small cell lung cancer and cisplatin sensitivity by miR-101/ABCC1 axis.
description: circ_PIP5K1A positively regulated ABCC1 expression by sponging miR-101. Exosomal circ_PIP5K1A knockdown inhibited NSCLC progression and promoted cisplatin sensitivity by regulating miR-101/ABCC1 axis, providing a novel avenue for treatment of NSCLC.

title: CircRNA ZNF609 Knockdown Represses the Development of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer via miR-623/FOXM1 Axis.
description: circZNF609 knockdown repressed NSCLC development via regulating miR-623 and FOXM1.

title: CircUSP36 knockdown alleviates oxidized low_density lipoprotein_induced cell injury and inflammatory responses in human umbilical vein endothelial cells via the miR_20a_5p/ROCK2 axis.
description: circUSP36 targeted miR_20a_5p to regulate the expression of ROCK2. On the whole, the present study demonstrates that, circUSP36 regulates ox_LDL_induced HUVEC injury and inflammation by modulating ROCK2 via competitively targeting miR_20a_5p.

title: Circ_0119872 promotes uveal melanoma development by regulating the miR-622/G3BP1 axis and downstream signalling pathways.
description: Circ_0119872 may act as an oncogene in UM through a novel circ_0119872/miR-622/G3BP1 axis, activating the Wnt/beta-catenin and mTOR signalling pathways, which in turn may provide potential biomarkers and therapeutic targets for the management of UM.

title: Circular RNA TTC3 regulates cerebral ischemia-reperfusion injury and neural stem cells by miR-372-3p/TLR4 axis in cerebral infarction.
description: Thus, we conclude that circTTC3 regulates CIR injury and NSCs by the miR-372-3p/TLR4 axis in cerebral infarction. Our finding presents new insight into the mechanism by which circTTC3 modulates CIR injury and NSC dysfunction. CircTTC3, miR-372-3p, and TLR4 may serve as potential targets for the treatment of CIR injury during stroke.

title: Circular RNA circARPP21 Acts as a Sponge of miR-543 to Suppress Hepatocellular Carcinoma by Regulating LIFR.
description: The circARPP21/miR-543/LIFR axis suppresses the proliferation, invasion, and migration of hepatocellular carcinoma cells. In addition, circARPP21 can serve as a biomarker in HCC, thus offering a potential new approach to HCC therapy.

title: Hsa_circ_0107593 Suppresses the Progression of Cervical Cancer via Sponging hsa-miR-20a-5p/93-5p/106b-5p.
description: hsa_circ_0107593 has tumor-suppressing activity in CC by physically binding with hsa-miR-20a-5p, hsa-miR-93-5p, and hsa-miR-106b-5p.

title: The novel circular RNA circ-PGAP3 retards cervical cancer growth by regulating the miR-769-5p/p53 axis.
description: our data clearly expounded the tumor-inhibiting role of circ-PGAP3 in CC, circ-PGAP3 repressed CC tumorigenesis via regulating the miR-769-5p/p53 axis. Therefore, restoration of circ-PGAP3 may be a promising therapeutic target for this thorny disease.

title: Circ_ 0115744 acts as miR-144 sponge to promote and predict the metastasis of colorectal cancer.
description: we found that increased expression of circ_0115744 could differentiate CRLM from CRC and that the newly identified circ_0115744/miR-144/EZH2 axis was involved in the progression of CRC, which might be used as a potential diagnostic and therapeutic target for patients with CRC.

title: Circ_0004872 promotes platelet-derived growth factor-BB-induced proliferation, migration and dedifferentiation in HA-VSMCs via miR-513a-5p/TXNIP axis.
description: TXNIP was modulated by circ_0004872/miR-513a-5p signaling cascade in HA-VSMCs. Circ_0004872 accelerated PDGF-BB-induced proliferation, migration and dedifferentiation in HA-VSMCs through enhancing TXNIP level via sponging miR-513a-5p.

title: Circular RNA CDR1as promotes tumor progression by regulating miR-432-5p/E2F3 axis in pancreatic cancer.
description: circCDR1as could promote the development of PC and might be a novel diagnostic target for PC.

title: Circular RNA circ_0014717 Suppresses Hepatocellular Carcinoma Tumorigenesis Through Regulating miR-668-3p/BTG2 Axis.
description: circ_0014717 Suppresses Hepatocellular Carcinoma Tumorigenesis Through Regulating miR-668-3p/BTG2 Axis.

title: Effects of circular RNA Ttc3/miR-148a/Rcan2 axis on inflammation and oxidative stress in rats with acute kidney injury induced by sepsis.
description: CIRC-Ttc3 relieved inflammation and oxidative stress through regulating the miR-148a/Rcan2 axis in rats with AKI induced by sepsis. Therefore, CIRC-Ttc3 may be a potential therapeutic target for sepsis-induced AKI.

title: CircRNA circYY1 (hsa_circ_0101187) Modulates Cell Glycolysis and Malignancy Through Regulating YY1 Expression by Sponging miR-769-3p in Breast Cancer.
description: CircYY1 promoted glycolysis and tumor growth via increasing YY1 expression through sponging miR-769-3p in BC, offering a promising therapeutic target and prognostic biomarker for BC.

title: Circ_0056285 Regulates Proliferation, Apoptosis and Glycolysis of Osteosarcoma Cells via miR-1244/TRIM44 Axis.
description: Circ_0056285 facilitated OS progression by sponging miR-1244 and increasing TRIM44 expression, providing a promising therapeutic target for OS.

title: CircGDI2 Regulates the Proliferation, Migration, Invasion and Apoptosis of OSCC via miR-454-3p/FOXF2 Axis.
description: CircGDI2 served as a repressor to restrain OSCC malignancy via miR-454-3p/FOXF2 axis, which might be a novel biomarker for targeted OSCC therapy.

title: circFOXM1 contributes to sorafenib resistance of hepatocellular carcinoma cells by regulating MECP2 via miR-1324.
description: miR-1324 overexpression was capable of reversing the circFOXM1-induced malignant phenotypes and elevated expression of MECP2 in HCC cells. circFOXM1 partially contributed to sorafenib resistance of HCC cells through upregulating MECP2 expression by sponging miR-1324.

title: Circular RNA circPSD3 alleviates hepatic fibrogenesis by regulating the miR-92b-3p/Smad7 axis.
description: our present findings reveal a novel mechanism by which circPSD3 alleviates hepatic fibrogenesis by targeting the miR-92b-3p/Smad7 axis, and they also indicate that circPSD3 may serve as a potential biomarker for HF.

title: Circular RNA RBPMS inhibits bladder cancer progression via miR-330-3p/RAI2 regulation.
description: We summarize the circRBPMS/miR-330-3p/RAI2 axis, where circRBPMS acts as a tumor suppressor, and provide a potential biomarker and therapeutic target for BC.

title: hsa_circNFXL1_009 modulates apoptosis, proliferation, migration, and potassium channel activation in pulmonary hypertension.
description: hsa_circNFXL1_009 as a key regulator of PAH, and it may be used as a potential therapeutic target for the treatment of PAH.

title: Hsa_circ_0102171 aggravates the progression of cervical cancer through targeting miR-4465/CREBRF axis.
description: circ_0102171 aggravates CC progression via targeting miR-4465/CREBRF axis.

title: Circular RNA circEIF4G2 aggravates renal fibrosis in diabetic nephropathy by sponging miR-218.
description: circEIF4G2 promotes renal tubular epithelial cell fibrosis via the miR-218/SERBP1 pathway.

title: CircAGAP1 promotes tumor progression by sponging miR-15-5p in clear cell renal cell carcinoma.
description: Our results clarify that circAGAP1 exerts its oncogenic functions as a competitive endogenous RNA (ceRNA) by sponging miR-15-5p, which promotes E2F3 expression. Targeting circAGAP1 might be a new attractive therapeutic strategy in ccRCC.

title: CircVAPA exerts oncogenic property in non-small cell lung cancer by the miR-876-5p/WNT5A axis.
description: CircVAPA promotes aggressive phenotypes of NSCLC cells by the miR-876-5p/WNT5A axis activating Wnt/beta-catenin signaling.

title: Circular RNA circ_0002137 regulated the progression of osteosarcoma through regulating miR-433-3p/ IGF1R axis.
description: circ_0002137 could restrain the progression of OS through regulating miR-433-3p/IGF1R axis, providing a comprehensive landscape of circ_0002137 in the generation and development of OS.

title: Inhibition of hsa_circ_0003489 shifts balance from autophagy to apoptosis and sensitizes multiple myeloma cells to bortezomib via miR-874-3p/HDAC1 axis.
