description: the circPFKP/miR-644/ADAMTSL5 regulatory pathway inhibited the malignant progression of GC.

title: circ-Pank1 promotes dopaminergic neuron neurodegeneration through modulating miR-7a-5p/alpha-syn pathway in Parkinson disease.
description: circ-Pank1 is overexpressed in PD and enhances the locomotor dysfunction via the miR-7a-5p/alpha-syn signaling axis.

title: Knockdown of Circ_0003506 Impedes Radioresistance, Cell Growth, Migration and Invasion in Gastric Cancer.
description: Knockdown of circ_0003506 suppressed radioresistance in GC through the regulation of miR-1256/bone morphogenetic protein type 2 receptor axis.

title: Circ-RHOJ1 regulated myocardial cell proliferation and apoptosis via targeting the miR-124-3p/NRG-1 axis in myocardial ischemia/reperfusion injury.
description: Circ-RHOJ.1 served as a molecular marker of myocardial I/R injury via regulation of miR-124-3p and NRG1 expression.

title: CircFGGY Inhibits Cell Growth, Invasion and Epithelial-Mesenchymal Transition of Hepatocellular Carcinoma via Regulating the miR-545-3p/Smad7 Axis.
description: circFGGY inhibits the proliferation and invasion of HCC cells by sponging miR-545-3p and promote the expression of Smad7.

title: CircERBB2IP promotes post-infarction revascularization via the miR-145a-5p/Smad5 axis.
description: circERBB2IP can promote angiogenesis after myocardial infarction through the miR-145a-5p/Smad5 axis.

title: CircKIAA0368 Promotes Proliferation, Migration, and Invasion by Upregulating HOXA10 in Nasopharyngeal Carcinoma.
description: CircKIAA0368 upregulates HOXA10 expression via miR-6838-5p and PCAF, consequently promoting NPCcell and tumor growth.

title: M2 macrophage facilitated angiogenesis in cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma via circ_TNFRSF21/miR-3619-5p/ROCK axis.
description: circ_TNFRSF21 was elevated in M2 macrophages and mediated M2 macrophage-induced tube formation in vitro.

title: Oncogenic circTICRR suppresses autophagy via binding to HuR protein and stabilizing GLUD1 mRNA in cervical cancer.
description: circTICRR acts as an oncogene in cervical cancer and the interaction between circTICRR and HuR protein may be a potential target in cervical cancer therapeutics.

title: Circ_0039960 regulates growth and Warburg effect of breast cancer cells via modulating miR-1178/PRMT7 axis.
description: circ_0039960 regulates cell growth and Warburg effect in BC cells via miR-1178/PRMT7 axis.

title: The circ_FAM53B-miR-183-5p-CCDC6 axis modulates the malignant behaviors of papillary thyroid carcinoma cells.
description: circ_FAM53B affects PTC cell biological behaviors via the miR-183-5p-CCDC6 axis.

title: Oxidized low-density lipoprotein contributes to injury of endothelial cells via the circ_0090231/miR-9-5p/TXNIP axis.
description: Circ_0090231 could attenuate ox-LDL-mediated HUVEC damage by the miR-9-5p/TXNIP axis.

title: The Expression Profile, Clinical Application and Potential Tumor Suppressing Mechanism of hsa_circ_0001675 in Head and Neck Carcinoma.
description: hsa_circ_0001675 is downregulated in HNC and could be an effective biomarker for HNC diagnosis.

title: Circ_0001998 Regulates the Proliferation, Invasion, and Apoptosis of Lung Adenocarcinoma via Sponging miR-145.
description: Circ_0001998 regulates the proliferation, invasion, and apoptosis of LUAD via sponging miR-145.

title: hsa_circ_0001955 Promotes Colorectal Cancer Progression by Regulating miR-583/FGF21 Axis.
description: hsa_circ_0001955 facilitated CRC progression via miR-583/FGF21 axis.

title: CircNMD3 relieves endothelial cell injury induced by oxidatively modified low-density lipoprotein through regulating miR-498/ BMP and activin membrane-bound inhibitor (BAMBI) axis.
description: circNMD3 regulates the level of miR-498, which in turn modulates BAMBI expression and suppresses ox-LDL-induced injury in HUVECs.

title: The involvement of copper, circular RNAs, and inflammatory cytokines in chronic respiratory disease.
description: the relative expression of circ_0008882 was decreased after copper exposure in vitro and in vivo.

title: Oxymatrine induces anti-tumor response in cervical cancer by modulating circ_0008460/miR-197-3p/ribonucleotide reductase subunit M2 (RRM2).
description: OMT restrained CC cell progression in vitro and tumor growth in vivo by downregulating circ_0008460 to mediate miR-197-3p/RRM2 axis.

title: Circular RNA_0001187 participates in the regulation of ulcerative colitis development via upregulating myeloid differentiation factor 88.
description: circ_0001187 facilitated UC progression through miR-1236-3p/MYD88 axis.

title: CircSLC8A1 targets miR-181a-5p/HIF1AN pathway to inhibit the growth, migration and extracellular matrix deposition of human keloid fibroblasts.
description: circSLC8A1 regulates the miR-181a-5p/HIF1AN axis to restrain HKFs biological functions.

description: 6 circRNAs showed high diagnostic values (AUC = 0.6860, AUC = 0.8127, AUC = 0.7502, AUC = 0.9945, AUC = 0.9642, AUC = 0.9486 for hsa_circRNA_100833, hsa_circRNA_103828, hsa_circRNA_103831 and hsa_circRNA_103752, hsa_circRNA_071106, hsa_circRNA_102293).

title: Identification of circ_0000375 and circ_0011536 as novel diagnostic biomarkers of colorectal cancer.
description: Circ_0000375 and circ_0011536 may function as tumor suppressors in CRC progression.

title: Identification of circ_0000375 and circ_0011536 as novel diagnostic biomarkers of colorectal cancer.
description: Circ_0000375 and circ_0011536 may function as tumor suppressors in CRC progression.

title: Circular RNA circLRCH3 Inhibits Proliferation, Migration, and Invasion of Colorectal Cancer Cells Through miRNA-223/LPP Axis.
description: circLRCH3/miR-223/LPP axis likely plays a critical role in CRC.

title: CircRNF220 plays a pathogenic role to facilitate cell progression of AML in vitro via sponging miR-330-5p to induce upregulation of SOX4.
description: circRNF220 contributed to AML cell development in vitro via upregulating SOX4 expression by targeting miR-330-5p.

title: Knockout of circRNA single stranded interacting protein 1 (circRBMS1) played a protective role in myocardial ischemia-reperfusion injury though inhibition of miR-2355-3p/Mammalian Sterile20-like kinase 1 (MST1) axis.
description: circRBMS1 played a protective role in myocardial I/R injury though inhibition of miR-2355-3p/MST1 axis.

title: Circ_0014359 promotes oral squamous cell carcinoma progression by sponging miR-149.
description: The circ_0014359-miR-149 pathway may be a novel target for developing strategies for the diagnosis and treatment of OSCC.

title: circ_000166/miR-296 Aggravates the Process of Diabetic Renal Fibrosis by Regulating the SGLT2 Signaling Pathway in Renal Tubular Epithelial Cells.
description: circ_000166/miR-296/SGLT2 may become a new target in the progression of DN renal fibrosis.

title: Extracellular Vesicle-Derived circITGB1 Regulates Dendritic Cell Maturation and Cardiac Inflammation via miR-342-3p/NFAM1.
description: circITGB1 competitively binds to miR-342-3p and inhibits its expression, which in turn increase the expression of NFAT activating molecule 1 (NFAM1).

title: Hsa_circ_0006732 regulates colorectal cancer cell proliferation, invasion and EMT by miR-127-5p/RAB3D axis.
description: hsa_circ_0006732 might be an oncogene in CRC through the regulation of the miR-127-5p/RAB3D axis.

title: PIK3CA mutations-mediated downregulation of circLHFPL2 inhibits colorectal cancer progression via upregulating PTEN.
description: Downregulation of circLHFPL2 sustains the activation of the PI3K/AKT signaling pathway via a positive feedback loop in PIK3CA-mutant CRC.

title: Circ_ROBO2/miR-186-5p/TRIM14 axis regulates oxidized low-density lipoprotein-induced cardiac microvascular endothelial cell injury.
description: Circ_ROBO2 played a promoting role in ox-LDL-induced CMECs injury by sponging miR-186-5p and regulating TRIM14.

title: CircPVT1 facilitates the progression of oral squamous cell carcinoma by regulating miR-143-3p/SLC7A11 axis through MAPK signaling pathway.
description: circPVT1 impeded OSCC progression via the miR-143-3p/SLC7A11 axis through MAPK signaling pathway.

title: The circSPON2/miR-331-3p axis regulates PRMT5, an epigenetic regulator of CAMK2N1 transcription and prostate cancer progression.
description: PRMT5 aggravates PCa progression by inhibiting the transcription of CAMK2N1 and is modulated by the circSPON2/miR-331-3p axis.

title: Hsa_circ_0006692 Promotes Lung Cancer Progression via miR-205-5p/CDK19 Axis.
description: sa_circ_0006692 promoted NSCLC progression via enhancing cell growth, invasion, and metastasis through sponging mir-205-5p, up-regulating the downstream oncogene CDK19 and modulating EMT of lung cancer cells.

title: Circ_0008068 facilitates the oral squamous cell carcinoma development by microRNA-153-3p/acylgycerol kinase (AGK) axis.
description: circ_0008068 expedited the growth of OSCC by miR-153-3p/AGK axis.

title: Circ_0066881 targets miR-144-5p/RORA axis to alleviate LPS-induced apoptotic and inflammatory damages in human periodontal ligament cells.
description: circ_0066881 partly prevented LPS-evoked cell dysfunction in PDLCs through miR-144-5p-mediated up-regulation of RORA.

title: circNup188/miR-760-3p/Map3k8 axis regulates inflammation in cerebral ischemia.
description: circNup188 might up-regulate Map3k8 expression through sponging miR-760-3p and then activate NF-kappaB pathway, which was involved in cerebral ischemia development.

title: Knockdown of circ_0026579 ameliorates lipopolysaccharide (bacterial origin)-induced inflammatory injury in bronchial epithelium cells by targeting miR-338-3p/TBL1XR1 axis.
description: Circ_0026579 RNA knockdown promoted cell proliferation but inhibited apoptosis and inflammation in LPS-induced BEAS-2B cells through regulating miR-338-3p RNA/TBL1XR1 protein axis.

title: Glioblastoma-associated microglia-derived exosomal circKIF18A promotes angiogenesis by targeting FOXC2.
description: M2 GAM-derived exosomal circKIF18A participating in GBM angiogenesis via targeting FOXC2.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0026344 suppresses gastric cancer cell proliferation, migration and invasion via the miR-590-5p/PDCD4 axis.
description: Circ_0026344 up-regulates PDCD4 expression via sponging miR-590-5p, thus inhibiting the progression of GC.

title: circRNA422 enhanced osteogenic differentiation of bone marrow mesenchymal stem cells during early osseointegration through the SP7/LRP5 axis.
description: circRNA422 could regulate early osseointegration in in vivo.

title: Exosomal circRNA BTG2 derived from RBP-J overexpressed-macrophages inhibits glioma progression via miR-25-3p/PTEN.
description: RBP-J OE Mphi inhibits tumor progression through the circBTG2/miR-25-3p/PTEN pathway.

title: CircRNA circ-MYBL2 absorbs precursor miR-92b in the nucleus to suppress its role in enhancing gastric cancer cell proliferation.
description: Circ-MYBL2 may absorb precursor miR-92b in the nucleus to suppress its role in promoting gastric cancer cell proliferation.

title: Circ-0002814 participates in proliferation and migration through miR-210 and FUS/VEGF pathway of preeclampsia.
description: A low expression of circ-0002814 was detected in the plasma and placental tissue in preeclampsia patients.  circ-0002814 participated in the proliferation and invasion of HTR8 and JEG3 cells.

title: circRNA TCFL5 Promote Esophageal Cancer Progression by Modulating M2 Macrophage Polarization via the miR-543-FMNL2 Axis.
description: circRNA TCFL5 was dramatically upregulated in esophageal cancer, and circRNA TCFL5 promotes esophageal cancer progression by modulating M2 macrophage polarization via the miR-543-FMNL2 axis.

title: CircNRIP1 Exerts Oncogenic Functions in Papillary Thyroid Carcinoma by Sponging miR-653-5p and Regulating PBX3 Expression.
description: Silencing of circNRIP1 suppressed PTC development via miR-653-5p elevation and PBX3 reduction.

title: Exosomal Circsafb2 Reshaping Tumor Environment to Promote Renal Cell Carcinoma Progression by Mediating M2 Macrophage Polarization.
description: circSAFB2 leads to immune escape from RCC by mediating M2 macrophage polarization via the miR-620/JAK1/STAT3 axis.

title: Silencing circular RNA-friend leukemia virus integration 1 restrained malignancy of CC cells and oxaliplatin resistance by disturbing dyskeratosis congenita 1.
description: circ-FLI1 might confer L-OHP resistance and malignant progression of CC presumably through the circ-FLI1/miR-197-3p/DKC1 ceRNA axis.

title: CircRIP2 aggravates the deterioration of colorectal carcinoma by negatively regulating CBFB.
description: CircRIP2 is a potential indicator for predicting tumor staging and distant metastasis of CRC.

title: CircPVT1 promotes the tumorigenesis and metastasis of osteosarcoma via mediation of miR-26b-5p/CCNB1 axis.
description: Silencing of circPVT1 notably suppressed the tumorigenesis and metastasis of OS via miR-26b-5p/CCNB1 axis.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0068252 Functions in Cisplatin Resistance and Immune Response via miR-1304-5p/PD-L1 Axis in Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer.
description: The circ_0068252/miR-1304-5p/PD-L1 signal axis participates in the regulation of DDP resistance and immune escape of NSCLC cells.

title: Exosomal circ-CACNG2 promotes cardiomyocyte apoptosis in multiple myeloma via modulating miR-197-3p/caspase3 axis.
description: MM-exosomes could inhibit cardiomyocyte viability and promote apoptosis partially through circ-CACNG2/miR-197-3p/caspase3 axis.

title: CircSTX6 promotes pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma progression by sponging miR-449b-5p and interacting with CUL2.
description: circSTX6 facilitates proliferation and metastasis of PDAC cells by regulating the expression of MYH9 through the circSTX6/miR-449b-5p axis and circSTX6/CUL2/HIF1A signaling pathway.

title: circPDE5A regulates prostate cancer metastasis via controlling WTAP-dependent N6-methyladenisine methylation of EIF3C mRNA.
description: FOXO4-mediated upregulation of circPDE5A controls PCa metastasis via the circPDE5A-WTAP-EIF3C-MAPK signaling pathway.

title: The molecular mechanism of circRHOBTB3 inhibits the proliferation and invasion of epithelial ovarian cancer by serving as the ceRNA of miR-23a-3p.
description: circRHOBTB3 could serve as the ceRNA of miR_23a-3p to facilitate PTEN expression, suppress proliferation, G1/S transition, invasion, and promote apoptosis in EOC.

title: CircSCAF8 promotes growth and metastasis of prostate cancer through the circSCAF8-miR-140-3p/miR-335-LIF pathway.
description: circSCAF8 contributes to PCa progression through the circSCAF8-miR-140-3p/miR-335-LIF pathway.

title: CircCEMIP promotes anoikis-resistance by enhancing protective autophagy in prostate cancer cells.
description: circ_0004585 played an oncogenic role during PCa invasion and metastasis by targeting the miR-1248/TM9SF4 axis .

description: Upregulated circTMEM59 Inhibits Cell Growth and Metastasis by miR-668-3p/ID4 Axis in Colorectal Cancer.

title: Role of hippocampal circKcnk9 in visceral hypersensitivity and anxiety comorbidity of irritable bowel syndrome.
description: early life stress induces increased expression of circKcnk9 in the CA1 of IBS-like rats.  Increased circKcnk9 expression regulates synaptic transmission and enhances LTP, leading to visceral hypersensitivity and anxiety in IBS-like rats.  The underlying circKcnk9 signaling pathway is miR124-3p/EZH2.  Increased circKcnk9 reinforces its sponging of miR124-3p and strongly suppresses miR124-3p activity, resulting in increased expression of the target gene EZH2.

description: The five upregulated circRNAs in ICH were hsa_circ_0001707, hsa_circ_0091669, hsa_circ_0005505, hsa_circ_0001481 and hsa_circ_0027725; the 4 downregulated circRNAs in ICH were hsa_circ_0000914 and three novel circRNAs that we named according to their host genes, circCHST12 (host gene_HST12), circERBB2 and circGLTSCR1 (host gene_LTSCR1).

title: Microarray profiling of circular RNAs in LPS-induced Beas-2B cells and identification of circ_2979 as a potential biomarker for ARDS.
description: Among them, circ_2979, circ_5438 and circ_4557 were upregulated, and circ_2066 and circ_5431 were downregulated.

title: Microarray profiling of circular RNAs in LPS-induced Beas-2B cells and identification of circ_2979 as a potential biomarker for ARDS.
description: Among them, circ_2979, circ_5438 and circ_4557 were upregulated, and circ_2066 and circ_5431 were downregulated.

title: Microarray profiling of circular RNAs in LPS-induced Beas-2B cells and identification of circ_2979 as a potential biomarker for ARDS.
description: Among them, circ_2979, circ_5438 and circ_4557 were upregulated, and circ_2066 and circ_5431 were downregulated.

title: Microarray profiling of circular RNAs in LPS-induced Beas-2B cells and identification of circ_2979 as a potential biomarker for ARDS.
description: Among them, circ_2979, circ_5438 and circ_4557 were upregulated, and circ_2066 and circ_5431 were downregulated.

title: Microarray profiling of circular RNAs in LPS-induced Beas-2B cells and identification of circ_2979 as a potential biomarker for ARDS.
description: Among them, circ_2979, circ_5438 and circ_4557 were upregulated, and circ_2066 and circ_5431 were downregulated.

title: Exosome-mediated circTTLL5 transfer promotes hepatocellular carcinoma malignant progression through miR-136-5p/KIAA1522 axis.
description: Exosomal circTTLL5 promoted HCC progression through miR-136-5p/KIAA1522 axis, suggesting that blockage of the exosome-mediated transfer of circTTLL5 might be a therapeutic target for HCC.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0004689 (circSWT1) promotes NSCLC progression via the miR-370-3p/SNAIL axis by inducing cell epithelial-mesenchymal transition (EMT).
description: CircSWT1 promoted the invasion, migration, and EMT of NSCLC. CircSWT1 could serve as a potential biomarker and a potential therapeutic target for NSCLC.

title: CircRNA PDE3B regulates tumorigenicity via the miR-136-5p/MAP3K2 axis of esophageal squamous cell carcinoma.
description: In conclusion, circ_PDE3B acted as oncogenic circRNA in ESCC and accelerated ESCC progression by adsorption of miR-136-5p and activation of MAP3K2, supporting circ_PDE3B as a potential therapeutic target for ESCC.

title: CircNTNG1 inhibits renal cell carcinoma progression via HOXA5-mediated epigenetic silencing of Slug.
description: Based on the experimental data, in RCC, circNTNG1/miR-19b-3p/HOXA5 axis can regulate the epigenetic silencing of Slug, thus interfering EMT and metastasis of RCC.

title: Circ_0000284 upregulates RHPN2 to facilitate pancreatic cancer proliferation, metastasis, and angiogenesis through sponging miR-1179.
description: To sum up, our data confirmed that circ_0000284 facilitated PC malignant progression depending on the regulation of miR-1179/RHPN2 axis, suggesting that circ_0000284 might be a potential target for PC treatment.

title: Comprehensive Analysis of Circular RNA Expression Profiles in Gefitinib-Resistant Lung Adenocarcinoma Patients.
description: Our study provides valuable data on circRNAs expression profiles detected in liquid biopsy for LUAD patients with acquired gefitinib resistance, and we validate that upregulations of hsa_circ_0030591 and hsa_circ_0040348 may play key roles in EGFR-TKI resistance and thus serving as candidates for biomarker.

title: Comprehensive Analysis of Circular RNA Expression Profiles in Gefitinib-Resistant Lung Adenocarcinoma Patients.
description: Our study provides valuable data on circRNAs expression profiles detected in liquid biopsy for LUAD patients with acquired gefitinib resistance, and we validate that upregulations of hsa_circ_0030591 and hsa_circ_0040348 may play key roles in EGFR-TKI resistance and thus serving as candidates for biomarker.

title: Bone marrow stromal cell-derived exosomal circular RNA improves diabetic foot ulcer wound healing by activating the nuclear factor erythroid 2-related factor 2 pathway and inhibiting ferroptosis.
description: Exosomal circ-ITCH from BMSCs inhibited ferroptosis and improved the angiogenesis of HUVECs through activation of the Nrf2 signalling pathway by recruiting TAF15 protein, ultimately accelerating the wound healing process in DFU.

title: CircSTK39 suppresses the proliferation and invasion of bladder cancer by regulating the miR-135a-5p/NR3C2-mediated epithelial-mesenchymal transition signaling pathway.
description: In conclusion, our results revealed that circSTK39 inhibited EMT of BCa cells through the miR-135a-5p/NR3C2 axis and may provide promising biomarkers for the diagnosis or prospective therapeutic targets for BCa.

title: Circ_0058608 contributes to the progression and taxol resistance of non-small cell lung cancer by sponging miR-1299 to upregulate GBP1.
description: Circ_0058608 promoted the progression and taxol resistance of NSCLC by regulating the miR-1299/GBP1 axis.

title: CircPIM3 regulates taxol resistance in non-small cell lung cancer via miR-338-3p/TNFAIP8 axis.
description: CircPIM3 and TNFAIP8 were upregulated in Tax-resistant NSCLC tissue and cell samples.

title: Circ-ABCC4 contributes to prostate cancer progression and radioresistance by mediating miR-1253/SOX4 cascade.
description: Circ-ABCC4 could enhance SOX4 abundance by absorbing miR-1253. Circ-ABCC4 exerted a pro-tumor activity by facilitating PCa cell viability, proliferation, invasion, and radioresistance and suppressing apoptosis.

title: Hsa_circ_0007380 silencing restrains the growth and enhances radiosensitivity in esophagus cancer by miR-644a/Spindlin 1 axis.
description: Hsa_circ_0007380 silencing impedes cell growth and reinforces radiosensitivity in esophagus cancer by miR-644a/SPIN1 axis, suggesting a promising therapeutic target for esophagus cancer combined treatment.

title: The hsa_circ_0039857/miR-338-3p/RAB32 axis promotes the malignant progression of colorectal cancer.
description: This study demonstrated that circ_0039857 knockdown suppressed CRC malignant progression through miR-338-3p/RAB32 axis. Most importantly, this will help us to better understand the circRNA network in CRC, and may find potential biomarkers and targets for CRC clinical treatment.

title: Increased expression of miR-194-5p through the circPVRL3/miR-194-5p/SOCS2 axis promotes proliferation and metastasis in pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma by activating the PI3K/AKT signaling pathway.
description: Our findings indicated that an increase of miR-194-5p caused by circPVRL3 downregulation stimulates the PI3K/AKT signaling pathway to promote PDAC progression via the circPVRL3/miR-194-5p/SOCS2 axis, which suggests that the circPVRL3/miR-194-5p/SOCS2 axis may be a potential therapeutic target for PDAC patients.

title: Silencing of circ-NT5C2 retards the progression of IL-1beta-induced osteoarthritis in an in vitro cell model by targeting the miR-142-5p/NAMPT axis.
description: Collectively, circ-NT5C2 accelerated the OA process by targeting the miR-142-5p/NAMPT axis. This study provides valuable information to find a better treatment for OA.

title: Circ_0018909 knockdown inhibits the development of pancreatic cancer via the miR-545-3p/FASN axis and reduces macrophage polarization to M2.
description: Circ_0018909 knockdown retarded the development of pancreatic cancer by modulating miR-545-3p to regulate FASN expression.

title: Role of m6A modification and novel circ_0066715/ miR-486-5p/ ETS1 axis in rheumatoid arthritis macrophage polarization progression.
description: The overexpression of circ_0066715 significantly increased the ETS1 levels in RA-FLS cells, decreased cytokine secretion by M1-type macrophages, elevated M2-type cytokines, and inhibited FLS proliferation.

title: Circ-IGF1R Affects the Progression of Colorectal Cancer by Activating the miR-362-5p/HMGB3-Mediated Wnt/beta-Catenin Signal Pathway.
description: This study hypothesized that circ-IGF1R sponged miR-362-5p to regulate HMGB3 level and activate HMGB3/Wnt/beta-catenin pathway in CRC cell development.

title: Circular RNA Circ_0005962 Contributes to Lung Adenocarcinoma Cell Proliferation and Stem Cell Formation Through Sponging of miR-3611 and Modulating CYP24A1 Expression.
description: Together, circ_0005962 was overexpressed in LUAD, and its deficiency repressed LUAD progression via targeting the miR-3611/ CYP24A1 axis, providing a novel mechanism for understanding the development of LUAD.

title: circ-ZEB1 regulates epithelial-mesenchymal transition and chemotherapy resistance of colorectal cancer through acting on miR-200c-5p.
description: In conclusion, circ-ZEB1 could promote CRC cells progression, EMT, and chemoresistance via acting on miR-200c, elucidating a potential therapeutic target to inhibit CRC progression.

title: CircBFAR correlates with poor prognosis and promotes laryngeal squamous cell cancer progression through miR-31-5p/COL5A1 axis.
description: CircBFAR, miR-31-5p, and COL5A1 in LSCC progression might provide novel therapeutic targets for LSCC clinical intervention.

title: Hsa_circ_0092887 targeting miR-490-5p/UBE2T promotes paclitaxel resistance in non-small cell lung cancer.
description: Hsa_circ_0092887 depletion alleviated PTX-resistance in NSCLC cells via modulating the miR-490-5p/UBE2T axis, and the targeted management of hsa_circ_0092887-mediated signaling axis might contribute to PTX-resistance intervention in NSCLC.

title: Circ_0083964 knockdown impedes rheumatoid arthritis progression via the miR-204-5p-dependent regulation of YY1.
description: Circ_0083964 inhibition confined RA development by sponging miR-204-5p to hamper the YY1 level, which will provide a theoretical basis for the treatment of RA.

title: CircDOCK1 Regulates miR-186/DNMT3A to Promote Osteosarcoma Progression.
description: CircDOCK1 promotes OS progression by interacting with miR-186/DNMT3ADNMT3A, representing a novel therapeutic approach.

title: circPVT1 and PVT1/AKT3 show a role in cell proliferation, apoptosis, and tumor subtype-definition in small cell lung cancer.
description: In conclusion, we have uncovered a functional role of circular and chimeric PVT1 transcripts in SCLC; these entities may prove useful as novel biomarkers in MYC-amplified tumors.

title: Circular RNA circ0104103 inhibits colorectal cancer progression through interactions with HuR and miR-373-5p.
description: Taken together, our study revealed that circ0104103 acts as a tumor suppressor and may be a novel biomarker and therapeutic target in CRC.

title: CircDUSP1 regulates tumor growth, metastasis, and paclitaxel sensitivity in triple-negative breast cancer by targeting miR-761/DACT2 signaling axis.
description: Taken together, our findings revealed a role for the regulation of the miR-761/DACT2 axis by circDUSP1 in the biological process of TNBC. These results provided new insights into the biological mechanism and targeted therapy of TNBC.

title: CircPDIA4 Induces Gastric Cancer Progression by Promoting ERK1/2 Activation and Enhancing Biogenesis of Oncogenic circRNAs.
description: These findings reveal a dual tumor-promoting mechanism for circPDIA4 by regulating oncogenic circRNA biogenesis and increasing MAPK activity. CircPDIA4 should be investigated further as a potential prognostic biomarker and therapeutic target in gastric cancer.

title: Circular RNA expression profile identifies circMGEA5 as a novel metastasis-promoting factor and potential biomarker in osteosarcoma.
description: In sum, our findings, for the first time, reveal the metastasis-promoting role of circMGEA5 in OS. Targeting of this newly identified ceRNA axis may be crucial in the development of novel therapies for metastatic OS patients.

title: Circular RNA Sec61 subunit alpha isoform 1 by competitive absorption of microRNA-513a-5p mediates peroxisomal biogenesis factor 5 expression and promotes the malignant phenotype of non-small cell lung cancer.
description: Generally, circSEC61A1 is a potential biomarker for NSCLC, and circSEC61A1 serves tumor-promoting action in the progression of NSCLC.

title: Knockdown of hsa_circ_0008922 inhibits the progression of glioma.
description: We found that the expression of hsa_circ_0008922 in glioma tissues was 3.4 times higher than that in normal tissues. The expression of has_circ_0008922 was correlated with WHO tumor grade. After down-regulating the expression of hsa_circ_0008922, malignant biological behavior of glioma cells was inhibited, such as cell proliferation, colony formation, migration, and invasion.

title: Hsa_circ_0020378 targets miR-556-5p/MAPK1 to regulate osteosarcoma cell proliferation and migration.
description: Circ_0020378 acts as a novel tumor promoter that controls OS growth by miR-556-5p/MAPK1 axis, suggesting circ_0020378/miR-556-5p/MAPK1 might be a novel target for OS intervention.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0008003 promotes the progression of non-small-cell lung cancer by sponging miR-548I and regulating KPNA4 expression.
description: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0008003 promoted progression in NSCLC by sponging miR-548I and regulating KPNA4 expression, hinting that circ_0008003 participates in NSCLC pathogenesis.

title: circTAB2 inhibits lung cancer proliferation, migration and invasion by sponging miR-3142 to upregulate GLIS2.
description: Taken together, circTAB2 serves as an inhibitory role in lung cancer through a novel circTAB2 /miR-3142 /GLIS2 /AKT pathway and could be exploited a novel marker in lung cancer.

title: Circ_0006220 Contributes to NSCLC Progression through miR-342-3p/GOT2 Axis.
description: Circ_0006220 promoted the malignant behaviors of NSCLC cells through mediating the miR-342-3p/GOT2 regulation cascade.

title: Circ-PGAM1 Enhances Matrine Resistance of Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer via the miR-326/CXCR5 Axis.
description: circ-PGAM1 enhances matrine resistance of NSCLC cells through the miR-326/CXCR5 axis. The authors findings provide new insights into NSCLC-targeted therapy.

title: circRNA DENND1B inhibits tumorigenicity of clear cell renal cell carcinoma via miR-122-5p/TIMP2 axis.
description: circ_DENND1B inhibited ccRCC cell progression by promoting TIMP2 expression by sponging miR-122-5p, suggesting that circ_DENND1B might be an effective therapeutic target for ccRCC.

title: Circ_0001060 Upregulates and Encourages Progression in Osteosarcoma.
description: To sum up, circ_0001060 is a novel tumor biomarker for OS as well as a potential therapeutic target.

title: Hsa_circ_0049396 inhibited oral squamous cell carcinoma progression by regulating the miR-663b/ENDOU axis.
description: Our study illustrated that circ_0049396 overexpression inhibited the malignant behavior of OSCC cells by regulating the miR-663b/ENDOU axis. Based on our findings, circ_0049396 can be used as a potential therapeutic agent for OSCC.

title: Circ_0006646 Accelerates the Growth and Metastasis of Cervical Cancer by Elevating RRM2 Through miR-758-3p.
description: Circ_0006646 expedited CC cell growth and metastasis by regulating miR-758-3p/RRM2 axis, and exosomal circ_0006646 might be a potential diagnostic indicator of CC.

title: Circ_0026218 ameliorates oxidized low-density lipoprotein-induced vascular endothelial cell dysfunction by regulating miR-188-3p/TLR4/NF-kappaB pathway.
description: Circ_0026218 knockdown attenuated ox-LDL-induced dysfunction in HUVECs via regulating miR-188-3p/TLR4/NF-kB pathway.

title: Transcriptomic analysis of human ALS skeletal muscle reveals a disease-specific pattern of dysregulated circRNAs.
description: A summary of the changes for circRNAs based on RT-qPCR analysis in human and mouse tissues is shown in Table 4. Several circRNAs showed consistent changes in human and mouse skeletal muscle (5 upregulated and 4 downregulated circRNAs). Several circRNAs also showed consistent changes (all decreased) in human and mouse spinal cord tissues, including hsa_circ_0000119, hsa_circ_0000567, hsa_circ_0005171, hsa_circ_0047886, hsa_circ_0001948, and hsa_circ_0000033.

title: Transcriptomic analysis of human ALS skeletal muscle reveals a disease-specific pattern of dysregulated circRNAs.
description: A summary of the changes for circRNAs based on RT-qPCR analysis in human and mouse tissues is shown in Table 4. Several circRNAs showed consistent changes in human and mouse skeletal muscle (5 upregulated and 4 downregulated circRNAs). Several circRNAs also showed consistent changes (all decreased) in human and mouse spinal cord tissues, including hsa_circ_0000119, hsa_circ_0000567, hsa_circ_0005171, hsa_circ_0047886, hsa_circ_0001948, and hsa_circ_0000033.

title: Transcriptomic analysis of human ALS skeletal muscle reveals a disease-specific pattern of dysregulated circRNAs.
description: A summary of the changes for circRNAs based on RT-qPCR analysis in human and mouse tissues is shown in Table 4. Several circRNAs showed consistent changes in human and mouse skeletal muscle (5 upregulated and 4 downregulated circRNAs). Several circRNAs also showed consistent changes (all decreased) in human and mouse spinal cord tissues, including hsa_circ_0000119, hsa_circ_0000567, hsa_circ_0005171, hsa_circ_0047886, hsa_circ_0001948, and hsa_circ_0000033.

title: An evaluation of gastric adenocarcinoma-associated CircRNAs based on microarray meta-analysis and ceRNA networks.
description: A microarray meta-analysis of circRNAs revealed 32 dysregulated circRNAs in GAC. Using real-time PCR, the expression levels of one up-regulated circRNA (hsa_circ_0002019) and one down-regulated circRNA (hsa_circ_0074736) were evaluated in plasma samples.

title: An evaluation of gastric adenocarcinoma-associated CircRNAs based on microarray meta-analysis and ceRNA networks.
description: A microarray meta-analysis of circRNAs revealed 32 dysregulated circRNAs in GAC. Using real-time PCR, the expression levels of one up-regulated circRNA(hsa_circ_0002019)_nd one down-regulated circRNA (hsa_circ_0074736)_ere evaluated in plasma samples.

title: Inhibition by rno-circRNA-013017 of the apoptosis of motor neurons in anterior horn and descending axonal degeneration in rats after traumatic spinal cord injury.
description: our future work will include rescue experiments on rno-circRNA-013017 and its target genes to verify their relationship in vitro and in vivo. Namely, we will verify the rno_circRNA_013017/rno-miR-16-5p/bcl-2 pathway in cell lines and then perform the animal experiments.

title: circPOLR1C Promotes the Development of Esophageal Cancer by Adsorbing miR-361-3p and Regulating Cancer Cell Apoptosis and Metastasis.
description: circPOLR1C adsorbs miR-361-3p and regulates apoptosis- and EMT-related gene expressions to promote the development of EC.

title: CircVAPA contributes to hyper-proliferation and inflammation of keratinocytes through miR-125b-5p/sirt6 axis in psoriasis.
description: CircVAPA participate in the progression of psoriasis through miR-125b-5p/sirt6 axis by regulating proliferation and inflammation of keratinocytes, highlighting a potential therapeutic target for psoriasis.

title: Hsa_circ_0000520 Promotes Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer Progression through the miR-1258/AKT3 Axis.
description: circ_0000520 upregulates AKT3 by competitively binding with miR-1258 to facilitate NSCLC progression.

title: Hsa_circ_0006988 Promotes Sorafenib Resistance of Hepatocellular Carcinoma by Modulating IGF1 Using miR-15a-5p.
description: Hsa_circ_0006988 partly promoted the SOR-R of HCC cells through miR-15a-5p sequestering and upregulation of IGF1 levels.

title: Matrine inhibits hepatocellular carcinoma cell malignancy through the circ_0013290/miR-139-5p/MMP16 pathway.
description: Matrine inhibited HCC cell malignancy through the circ_0013290/miR-139-5p/MMP16 pathway, suggesting that Matrine is a potential therapeutic agent for HCC.

title: Exosome-derived circTFDP2 promotes prostate cancer progression by preventing PARP1 from caspase-3-dependent cleavage.
description: In general, our study demonstrated that circTFDP2 promoted PCa cell progression through the PARP1/DNA damage axis, which may be a promising therapeutic target for PCa.

title: Circ_0114428 Influences the Progression of Septic Acute Kidney Injury Via Regulating Mir-370-3p/Timp2 Axis.
description: Our data demonstrated that circ_0114428 contributed to septic AKI progression by regulating miR-370-3p-mediated TIMP2 expression, which provided a promising target for septic AKI treatment.

title: Hsa_circ_0001944 enhanced GSPT1 expression via sponging miR-498 to promote proliferation and invasion of gastric cancer.
description: The present study demonstrates the hsa_circ_0001944/miR-498/GSPT1 axis contributes to GC development. This may provide a target for GC therapy and potential prognostic biomarker.

title: Silencing circUSP48 suppresses osteosarcoma progression by regulating the miR-335/ smad nuclear interacting protein 1 pathway.
description: Overall, these findings suggested that circUSP48 acted as an oncogene in OS, which might become a new target for OS therapy.

title: Hsa_circ_0097009 regulates proliferation, apoptosis, migration and invasion of hepatocellular carcinoma cells via miR-568/RNF38 axis.
description: Together, this study indicated that the oncogenic function of circ_0097009 in HCC, and circ_0097009/miR-568/RNF38 axis was expected to be a novel therapeutic option for HCC patients.

title: Suppression of exosomal hsa_circ_0001005 eliminates the Vemurafenib resistance of melanoma.
description: This study confirmed that the level of hsa_circ_0001005 in exosomes is the key factor affecting drug resistance of melanoma, which provides a new potential therapeutic target for melanoma patients.

title: Identification of Circular RNA Circ_0003256 as a Novel Player in Pediatric Acute Myeloid Leukemia.
description: Our findings identify that suppression of circ_0003256 impedes the malignant behaviors of pediatric AML cells by regulating PRKACB expression by competing for shared miR-582-3p.

title: METTL3-mediated Hsa_circ_0000390 downregulation enhances the proliferation, migration, and invasion of colorectal cancer cells by increasing Notch1 expression.
description: This study suggested that circ_0000390 might be anti-tumor factor in CRC and METTL3/Notch1 might be a therapeutic targets for CRC.

title: Circ_0002762 Regulates Oncoprotein YBX1 in Cervical Cancer via mir-375 to Regulate the Malignancy of Cancer Cells.
description: Circ_0002762 promotes the progression of CC via sponging miR-375 and up-regulating YXB1 expression.

title: CircRNA B cell linker regulates cisplatin sensitivity in nonsmall cell lung cancer via microRNA-25-3p/BarH_like homeobox 2 axis.
description: Circ_BLNK promoted the DDP sensitivity of NSCLC via regulating miR-25-3p/BARX2 axis.

title: Circ_0124055 promotes the progression of thyroid cancer cells through the miR-486-3p/MTA1 axis.
description: Circ_0124055 promoted the progression of thyroid cancer cells through the miR-486-3p /MTA1 axis.

title: CircZSWIM6 mediates dysregulation of ECM and energy homeostasis in ageing chondrocytes through RPS14 post-translational modification.
description: Our results revealed a significant role of CircZSWIM6 in age-related OA by regulating ECM metabolism and AMPK-associated energy metabolism. We highlight the CircZSWIM6-RPS14-PCK1-AMPK axis is a potential biomarker for OA.

title: Hypoxia-induced miR-653 enhances colorectal cancer progression by targeting circSETD3/KLF6 axis.
description: Taken together, these findings indicated that circSETD3/miR-653/KLF6 axis may be an effective therapeutic target for CRC patients.

title: CircAGK regulates high dihydrotestosterone-induced apoptosis in DPCs through the miR-3180-5p/BAX axis.
description: By regulating the miR-3180-5p/BAX axis, circAGK promotes DPC apoptosis in a high DHT environment in vitro and inhibits hair growth in AGA mice in vivo, indicating that circAGK is a potential target for the clinical treatment of AGA.

title: Circular RNA Fibroblast Growth Factor Receptor 1 Promotes Pancreatic Cancer Progression by Targeting MicroRNA-532-3p/PIK3CB Axis.
description: Our data revealed that circFGFR1 driven the malignant progression of PDAC by targeting miR-532-3p/PIK3CB axis, suggesting that inhibition of circFGFR1 might be considered as a therapeutic target for PDAC.

title: Association of genetic variants of CircCHST15 with oral squamous cell carcinoma in the Chinese Han population.
description: The results of this study suggested that genetic variants of circCHST15 may contribute to OSCC susceptibility.

title: Circ_0101692 knockdown retards the development of clear cell renal cell carcinoma through miR-384/FN1 pathway.
description: This points out that circ_0101692/miR-384/FN1 axis might be a prospective target implemented for the future treatment of ccRCC.

title: Depletion of circ_0006459 protects human brain microvascular endothelial cells from oxygen-glucose deprivation-induced damage through the miR-940/FOXJ2 pathway.
description: Depletion of circ_0006459 protected human brain microvascular endothelial cells from oxygen-glucose deprivation-induced damage through miR-940/FOXJ2 pathway, providing a promising therapeutic target for ischemic stroke.

title: Hsa_circ_0021727 (circ-CD44) promotes ESCC progression by targeting miR-23b-5p to activate the TAB1/NFkappaB pathway.
description: In short, hsa_circ_0021727 promotes ESCC progression by targeting miR-23b-5p to activate the TAB1/NFB pathway. These findings might provide potential targets to treat ESCC.

title: Circular RNA_0003800 exacerbates IL-1beta-induced chondrocyte injury via miR-197-3p/SOX5 axis.
description: circ_0003800 exacerbates IL-1beta-induced chondrocyte injury via miR-197-3p/SOX5 axis.

title: Circular RNA circEMB promotes osteosarcoma progression and metastasis by sponging miR-3184-5p and regulating EGFR expression.
description: CircEMB plays a critical role in promoting cancer via the miR-3184-5p/EGFR pathway, indicating that circEMB may serve as a therapeutic target for OSA.

title: Hsa_circ_0015278 Regulates FLT3-ITD AML Progression via Ferroptosis-Related Genes.
description: In summary, we constructed the hsa_circ_0015278/miRNAs/FerRGs signaling axis, which provides new insight into the pathogenesis and therapeutic targets of AML with FLT3-ITD mutation.

title: Tumor Cell-Derived Exosomal circ-PRKCI Promotes Proliferation of Renal Cell Carcinoma via Regulating miR-545-3p/CCND1 Axis.
description: In conclusion, this study will provide a new understanding about the molecular mechanisms of RCC progression.

title: circRNA circSnx12 confers Cisplatin chemoresistance to ovarian cancer by inhibiting ferroptosis through a miR-194-5p/SLC7A11 axis.
description: CircARNT2 may thus serve as an effective therapeutic target for overcoming cisplatin resistance in OC.

title: Has_circ_0048764 promotes breast cancer progression by sponging miR-578 and regulating HMGA2 expression.
description: Circ_0048764 promotes BC cell growth, migration and invasion via absorbing miR-578 and up-regulating HMGA2.

title: CircHGS enhances the progression of bladder cancer by regulating the miR-513a-5p/VEGFC axis and activating the AKT/mTOR signaling pathway.
description: Our findings indicated that circHGS promotes BCa progression via the miR-513a-5p/VEGFC/AKT/mTOR pathway and can be a promising therapeutic target of BCa.

title: Detecting plasma hsa_circ_0061276 in patients with gastric cancer by reverse transcription-digital polymerase chain reaction.
description: Hsa_circ_0061276 may be a new biomarker for gastric cancer. The tumor suppressor role of hsa_circ_0061276 on gastric cancer likely occurs through a sponge effect on miRNAs such as hsa-miR-7705.

title: Circular RNA SESN2 aggravates gestational trophoblast cell damage induced by high glucose by binding to IGF2BP2.
description: Collectively, circSESN2 exacerbated HG-induced trophoblast cell damage by binding IGF2BP2 and upregulating its protein expression.

title: Circular RNA circPOFUT1 enhances malignant phenotypes and autophagy-associated chemoresistance via sequestrating miR-488-3p to activate the PLAG1-ATG12 axis in gastric cancer.
description: Our findings show the potential of circPOFUT1 as biomarkers and targeting circPOFUT1 as a therapeutic strategy for GC.

title: circFLNA promotes intestinal injury during abdominal sepsis through Fas-mediated apoptosis pathway by sponging miR-766-3p.
description: The circFLNA/miR-766-3p/Fas axis has potential as a novel therapeutic target for treating intestinal injury in sepsis.

title: CircMAN1A2 contributes to nasopharyngeal carcinoma progression via enhancing the ubiquitination of ATMIN through miR-135a-3p/UBR5 axis.
description: Together, our study uncovered the tumor-initiating and pro-metastatic role of circMAN1A2-miR-135a-3p-UBR5-ATMIN axis in NPC regulation that may be a potential therapeutic target for human NPC.

title: Increased transcription of hsa_circ_0000644 upon RUNX family transcription factor 3 downregulation participates in the malignant development of bladder cancer.
description: This study demonstrates that transcriptional activation of circ_644 upon RUNX3 downregulation drives the malignant development of BCa through the miR-143-3p/MSI2 axis. RUNX3 restoration or specific inhibition of circ_644 or MSI2 may help block BCa progression.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0000519 contributes to angiogenesis and tumor progression in hepatocellular carcinoma through the miR-1296/E2F7 axis.
description: These data suggest the potential clinical application of hsa_circ_0000519 in HCC treatment.

title: Circular RNA FOXO3 regulates endometrial carcinoma progression through the microRNA-29a-3p/HDAC4 axis.
description: In conclusion, circ_FOXO3 promotes EC progression by sponging miR-29a-3p and upregulating HDAC4, making it a promising therapeutic target in EC.

title: Hsa_circ_0008673 Promotes Breast Cancer Progression by MiR-578/GINS4 Axis.
description: Hsa_circ_0008673 might promote BC progression via modulating miR-578/GINS4 pathway.

title: Circ-0000979 promotes the development of gastric carcinoma by sponging miR-136 and modulating SP1 mRNA expression level.
description: Taken together, our results demonstrated that circ-0000979, as a carcinogenic circRNA, promotes the progression of GC by regulating the miR-136/SP1 pathway. Circ-0000979 is a potential RNA-based therapeutic target for GC treatment.

title: Apelin promotes osteosarcoma metastasis by upregulating PLOD2 expression via the Hippo signaling pathway and hsa_circ_0000004/miR-1303 axis.
description: APLN increased PLOD2 expression in human osteosarcoma cell lines and cell migration via the mammalian Sterile 20-like kinase 1 (MST1), monopolar spindle-one-binder protein (MOB)1, and YAP cascades, and through hsa_circ_0000004 functioning as a sponge of miR-1303.

title: Circular RNA ARHGAP5 inhibits cisplatin resistance in cervical squamous cell carcinoma by interacting with AUF1.
description: Collectively, our data indicated that circARHGAP5 directly bound to AUF1 and prevented AUF1 from interacting with BIM mRNA, thereby playing a pivotal role in cisplatin resistance in CSCC. Our study provides insights into overcoming cancer resistance to cisplatin treatment.

title: Circ_0060937 Contributes to the Development of Lung Cancer via Positively Regulating LAD1 Expression by Binding to miR-1304-5p.
description: Circ_0060937 downregulation decreased the expression of LAD1 by releasing miR-1304-5p to effectively repress lung cancer cell growth and in vivo tumorigenesis.

title: Circ_0001821 Potentiates Cell Growth, Metastasis, and Stemness in Colorectal Cancer by Regulating miR-339-3p/CST1.
description: Circ_0001821 promoted CRC cell proliferation, migration, invasion, and stemness by regulating the miR-339-3p/CST1 axis.

title: Circ_0001402 knockdown suppresses the chemoresistance and development of DDP-resistant cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma cells by functioning as a ceRNA for miR-625-5p.
description: Circ_0001402 knockdown can suppress the development and chemoresistance of DDP-resistant CSCC cells at least partly through targeting miR-625-5p/KPNA4 axis.

title: Circular RNA circTRPS1-2 inhibits the proliferation and migration of esophageal squamous cell carcinoma by reducing the production of ribosomes.
description: Our results suggest that circTRPS1-2 can inhibit ESCC proliferation and migration by reducing the production of ribosomes, establishing its potential usefulness in ESCC treatment and prediction of prognosis.

title: The U2AF65/circNCAPG/RREB1 feedback loop promotes malignant phenotypes of glioma stem cells through activating the TGF-beta pathway.
description: Our findings support the existence of a novel feedback loop U2AF65/circNCAPG/RREB1 that promotes malignant progression in GSCs and could be a novel therapeutic target for glioma patients.

title: CircRNA MBOAT2 promotes intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma progression and lipid metabolism reprogramming by stabilizing PTBP1 to facilitate FASN mRNA cytoplasmic export.
description: Our results identified that circMBOAT2 was upregulated in ICC and promoted progression by stabilizing PTBP1 to facilitate FASN mRNA cytoplasmic export, which altered lipid metabolic profile and regulated redox homeostasis in ICC, suggesting that circMBOAT2 may serve as an available therapeutic target for ICC with active lipid metabolism.

title: CircZNF236 facilitates malignant progression in oral squamous cell carcinoma by sequestering miR-145-5p.
description: CircZNF236 modulates OSCC via the miR-145-5p/MBTD1 axis. These results support the potential of circZNF236 as a treatment target for OSCC.

title: CircNDC80 promotes glioblastoma multiforme tumorigenesis via the miR-139-5p/ECE1 pathway.
description: According to our research, circNDC80 is an oncogenic factor that promotes glioblastoma through the miR-139-5p/ECE1 pathway. This implies that circNDC80 may be employed as a novel therapeutic target and a possible predictive biomarker.

title: Guggulsterone Promotes Nasopharyngeal Carcinoma Cells Exosomal Circfip1L1 to Mediate miR-125a-5p/VEGFA Affecting Tumor Angiogenesis.
description: GS promoted exosomal circFIP1L1 in NPC cells to mediate miR-125a-5p/VEGFA axis affecting tumor angiogenesis.

title: The hsa_circ_0007396-miR-767-3p-CHD4 axis is involved in the progression and carcinogenesis of gastric cancer.
description: We identified an important hsa_circ_0007396-miR-767-3p-CHD4 axis, which is associated with GC proliferation and carcinogenesis, and may represent a promising therapeutic target for the future cure of GC.

title: Circ-N4BP2L2 enhances mitochondrial function in non-small cell lung cancer cells through regulating the miR-135a-5p/ARL5B axis.
description: Taken together, circ-N4BP2L2 enhanced NSCLC progression via the miR-135a-5p/ARL5B axis, which may provide a novel therapeutic target of NSCLC.

title: CircFhit Modulates GABAergic Synaptic Transmission via Regulating the Parental Gene Fhit Expression in the Spinal Dorsal Horn in a Rat Model of Neuropathic Pain.
description: In summary, we revealed that the exon-intron circFhit contributes to GABAergic neuron-mediated NK1R+ neuronal hyperexcitation and neuropathic pain via regulating Fhit in cis.

title: CircIFNGR2 enhances proliferation and migration of CRC and induces cetuximab resistance by indirectly targeting KRAS via sponging to MiR-30b.
description: We predicted that circIFNGR2 could sponged miR-30b via bioinformatic method and subsequently confirmed that circIFNGR2 promoted the proliferation and migration of CRC cells by targeting miR-30b/KRAS. In addition, we demonstrated that circIFNGR2 might act as a potential chemotherapy resistance marker in CRC.

title: CircStrn3 targeting microRNA-9-5p is involved in the regulation of cartilage degeneration and subchondral bone remodelling in osteoarthritis.
description: Taken together, these results demonstrate that reduction of circStrn3 causes an increase in miR-9-5p, which acts as a protective factor in mechanical instability-induced OA, and provides a novel mechanism of communication among joint components and a potential application for the treatment of OA.

title: Circ_0004491 stimulates guanine nucleotide-binding protein alpha subunit to inhibit the malignant progression of oral squamous cell carcinoma by sponging miR-2278.
description: Circ_0004491 can repress OSCC progression by regulation of miR-2278/GNAS axis, providing a possible circRNA-targeted therapy for OSCC.

title: Circ_0138960 knockdown alleviates lipopolysaccharide-induced inflammatory response and injury in human dental pulp cells by targeting miR-545-5p/MYD88 axis in pulpitis.
description: Circ_0138960 knockdown attenuated LPS-induced inflammatory response and injury in hDPCs by targeting the miR-545-5p/MYD88/NF-kB axis.

title: Hsa_circ_0005050 regulated the progression of oral squamous cell carcinoma via miR-487a-3p/CHSY1 axis.
description: Circ_0005050 acted as an oncogenic factor in OSCC progression through miR-487a-3p/CHSY1 axis.

title: Exosome-Delivered circSTAU2 Inhibits the Progression of Gastric Cancer by Targeting the miR-589/CAPZA1 Axis.
description: Exosome-delivered circSTAU2 may act as a tumor suppressor that restrains GC progression via miR-589/CAPZA1 axis, which demonstrates a potential therapeutic target for GC.

title: Serum circular RNA hsa_circ_0000702 as a novel biomarker for diagnosis of gastric cancer.
description: Serum hsa_circ_0000702 was variably expressed in GC patients, indicating that serum hsa_circ_0000702 may be a novel biomarker for GC diagnosis and dynamic monitoring.

title: Circular RNA SPI1 expression before and after induction therapy and its correlation with clinical features, treatment response, and survival of acute myeloid leukemia patients.
description: Decreased circ-SPI1 expression is related to lower WBC, favorable risk stratification, and better therapy response; moreover, its decline during therapy is an independent factor to predict longer EFS and OS in AML patients.

title: Evaluation of Circ_0000977-Mediated Regulatory Network in Breast Cancer: A Potential Discriminative Biomarker for Triple-Negative Tumors
description: This study uncovered the potential clinical implication of circ_0000977 for the diagnosis and treatment of TNBC patients.

title: Hsa_circ_0000078 Regulates miR-205-5p/EREG Pathway to Inhibit Cervical Cancer Progression.
description: Circ_0000078 inhibits the growth of cancer by interfering with the miR-205-5p/EREG network, acting as a tumor suppressor in CC. These results provide a better understanding of the pathogenesis of this disease.

title: Human umbilical cord mesenchymal stem cell-derived extracellular vesicles alleviated silica induced lung inflammation and fibrosis in mice via circPWWP2A/miR-223-3p/NLRP3 axis.
description: Our study found that circPWWP2A could adsorb miR-223_3p to regulate NLRP3 after silica stimulation in pulmonary fibrosis.

title: CircLPAR1 Promotes Neuroinflammation and Oxidative Stress in APP/PS1 Mice by Inhibiting SIRT1/Nrf-2/HO-1 Axis Through Destabilizing GDF-15 mRNA.
description: Herein, UPF1 was predicted to have binding sites on both circLPAR1 and GDF-15 using starBase (version 3.0); therefore, we speculated that circLPAR1 might regulate the expression of GDF-15 through the interaction with UPF1, thus participating in AD pathogenesis.

title: Circular RNA hsa_circ_0075323 promotes glioblastoma cells proliferation and invasion via regulation of autophagy.
description: Hsa_circ_0075323 regulates p62-mediated autophagy pathway to promote GBM progression and may serve as a prognostic biomarker potentially.

title: Circ_0001326 suppresses trophoblast cell proliferation, invasion, migration and epithelial-mesenchymal transition progression in preeclampsia by miR-188-3p/HtrA serine peptidase 1 axis.
description: Our study demonstrated that circ_0001326 could promote trophoblast cell proliferation, invasion, migration and EMT in PE by miR-188-3p/HTRA1 axis, indicating a novel insight into the pathogenesis of PE.

title: RNA sequencing and bioinformatics analysis of circular RNAs in asphyxial newborns with acute kidney injury.
description: Top five upregulated and five downregulated circRNAs with higher fold changes were selected for qPCR validation. Hsa_circ_0008898 (Fold Change = 5.48, p = 0.0376) and hsa_circ_0005519 (Fold Change = 4.65, p = 0.0071) were significantly upregulated, while hsa_circ_0132279 (Fold Change = -4.47, p = 0.0008), hsa_circ_0112327 (Fold Change = -4.26, p = 0.0048), and hsa_circ_0017647 (Fold Change = -4.15, p = 0.0313) were significantly downregulated in asphyxia-induced AKI group compared with the control group.

title: RNA sequencing and bioinformatics analysis of circular RNAs in asphyxial newborns with acute kidney injury.
description: Top five upregulated and five downregulated circRNAs with higher fold changes were selected for qPCR validation. Hsa_circ_0008898 (Fold Change = 5.48, p = 0.0376) and hsa_circ_0005519 (Fold Change = 4.65, p = 0.0071) were significantly upregulated, while hsa_circ_0132279 (Fold Change = -4.47, p = 0.0008), hsa_circ_0112327 (Fold Change = -4.26, p = 0.0048), and hsa_circ_0017647 (Fold Change = -4.15, p = 0.0313) were significantly downregulated in asphyxia-induced AKI group compared with the control group.

title: RNA sequencing and bioinformatics analysis of circular RNAs in asphyxial newborns with acute kidney injury.
description: Top five upregulated and five downregulated circRNAs with higher fold changes were selected for qPCR validation. Hsa_circ_0008898 (Fold Change = 5.48, p = 0.0376) and hsa_circ_0005519 (Fold Change = 4.65, p = 0.0071) were significantly upregulated, while hsa_circ_0132279 (Fold Change = -4.47, p = 0.0008), hsa_circ_0112327 (Fold Change = -4.26, p = 0.0048), and hsa_circ_0017647 (Fold Change = -4.15, p = 0.0313) were significantly downregulated in asphyxia-induced AKI group compared with the control group.

Hsa_circ_0008898 (Fold Change = 5.48, p = 0.0376) and hsa_circ_0005519 (Fold Change = 4.65, p = 0.0071) were significantly upregulated, while hsa_circ_0132279 (Fold Change = -4.47, p = 0.0008), hsa_circ_0112327 (Fold Change = -4.26, p = 0.0048), and hsa_circ_0017647 (Fold Change = -4.15, p = 0.0313) were significantly downregulated in asphyxia-induced AKI group compared with the control group.

title: CircVPRBP inhibits nodal metastasis of cervical cancer by impeding RACK1 O-GlcNAcylation and stability.
description: Taken together, the results demonstrate that circVPRBP is a potential prognostic biomarker and a novel therapeutic target for LN metastasis in CCa patients.

title: CircSMAD2 accelerates endometrial cancer cell proliferation and metastasis by regulating the miR-1277-5p/MFGE8 axis.
description: CircSMAD2 functions as an oncogene in promoting the progression of EC through miR-1277-5p/MFGE8 axis.

title: Silencing of circCRIM1 Drives IGF2BP1-Mediated NSCLC Immune Evasion.
description: This study identifies circCRIM1 as a new tumor suppressor that inhibits tumor immune evasion through a competitive combination with IGF2BP1 to destabilize HLA-F mRNA.

title: CircZBTB46 Protects Acute Myeloid Leukemia Cells from Ferroptotic Cell Death by Upregulating SCD.
description: circZBTB46 protects AML cells from ferroptosis and promotes the proliferation by upregulating SCD, thus suggesting that circZBTB46 may be a potential therapeutic target for AML.

title: CircRNA-PI4KB Induces Hepatic Lipid Deposition in Non-Alcoholic Fatty Liver Disease by Transporting miRNA-122 to Extra-Hepatocytes.
description: The levels of circPI4KB in intra- and extra-hepatocytes corresponded to that of miRNA-122, and the overexpression of circPI4KB increased the miRNA-122 in extra-hepatocytes, consequently accomplishing a decreased protective role of miRNA-122 in inhibiting the lipid deposition.

title: Circ_0043256 upregulates KLF2 expression by absorbing miR-1206 to suppress the tumorigenesis of lung cancer.
description: Forced expression of circ_0043256 could impede the tumorigenesis of lung cancer via miR-1206/KLF2 axis, indicating a potential therapeutic approach for lung cancer.

title: CircRNA mannosidase alpha class 1A member 2 promotes esophageal squamous cell carcinoma progression by regulating C-C chemokine ligand 5.
description: Our results suggest that circMAN1A2 can promote the progression of ESCC by regulating CCL5. Thus, circMAN1A2 might be a novel diagnostic biomarker of ESCC, and targeting circMAN1A2 using inhibitors could be a potential therapeutic strategy to treat ESCC.

title: Chemotherapy-Induced Senescence Reprogramming Promotes Nasopharyngeal Carcinoma Metastasis by circRNA-Mediated PKR Activation.
description: This study uncovers a new mechanism of circWDR37 activated PKR in senescence-driven metastasis and provides appealing therapeutic targets in NPC.

title: Circular RNA circ_0029589 promotes ox-LDL-induced endothelial cell injury through regulating RAB22A by serving as a sponge of miR-1197.
description: Circ_0090231 might protect against ox-LDL-mediated HUVEC injury via the miR-1197/RAB22A axis, which provides a therapeutic strategy for endothelial cell damage of AS.

title: Hsa_circ_0001658 accelerates the progression of colorectal cancer through miR-590-5p/METTL3 regulatory axis.
description: Circ_0001658 regulates the miR-590-5p/METTL 3-axis to increase CRC cell growth and decrease apoptosis.

title: Identification of an unrecognized circRNA associated with development of renal fibrosis.
description: CircRNA_0002158 is associated with regulating Renal fibrosis, and may contribute to ameliorating the progression of Renal fibrosis in the future.

title: Circular RNA SMARCA5 Modulates Epithelial-Mesenchymal Transformation, Proliferation, and Metastasis of Nasopharyngeal Carcinoma Cells via microRNA-582-3p/Phosphatase and Tensin Homolog Axis.
description: In brief, the results of the research clarified circSMARCA5 modulated NPC cells vital movement via the miR-582-3p/PTEN molecular axis.

title: Differential Circular RNA Expression Profiles in Induced Sputum of Patients with Asthma.
description: Differentially expressed circRNAs existed in induced sputum cells of asthma patients, among which has_circSORT1 and has_circSERPINB1 were significantly upregulated and may be involved in the process of asthma disease, which could be expected to be a potential biomarker for asthma diagnosis. In addition, a ceRNA regulatory network, has_circSORT1/has-miR-185-3p/ZNFX1, may exist in asthma.

title: Differential Circular RNA Expression Profiles in Induced Sputum of Patients with Asthma.
description: Differentially expressed circRNAs existed in induced sputum cells of asthma patients, among which has_circSORT1 and has_circSERPINB1 were significantly upregulated and may be involved in the process of asthma disease, which could be expected to be a potential biomarker for asthma diagnosis. In addition, a ceRNA regulatory network, has_circSORT1/has-miR-185-3p/ZNFX1, may exist in asthma.

title: CircRNA Uxs1/miR-335-5p/PGF axis regulates choroidal neovascularization via the mTOR/p70 S6k pathway.
description: In conclusion, circRNA Uxs1 promoted CNV by sponging miR-335-5p, which stimulated PGF expression and subsequently activated the mTOR/p70 S6k pathway. Therefore, circRNA Uxs1 may serve as a promising therapeutic target for CNV.

title: A novel polypeptide encoded by the circular RNA ZKSCAN1 suppresses HCC via degradation of mTOR.
description: These results reveal that a novel circZKSCAN1-encoded peptide acts as a tumor suppressor on PI3K/AKT/mTOR pathway, and sensitizes HCC cells to sorafenib via ubiquitination of mTOR. These findings demonstrated that circZKSaa has the potential to serve as a therapeutic target and biomarker for HCC treatment.

title: Circ_0110498 facilitates the cisplatin resistance of non-small cell lung cancer by mediating the miR-1287-5p/RBBP4 axis.
description: Circ_0110498 facilitated DDP resistance partly through mediating the miR-1287-5p/RBBP4 signaling in NSCLC.

title: circAR-E2E4-miR-665-STAT3 axis is a potential regulatory network in triple-negative breast cancer.
description: Collectively, the regulatory network circAR-E2E4-miR-665-STAT3 axis we constructed was associated with TNBC progression, providing a promising diagnostic, prognostic, and therapeutic target in future treatment for TNBC.

title: circRNA ITGA7 restrains growth and enhances radiosensitivity by up-regulating SMAD4 in colorectal carcinoma.
description: In all, circ_ITGA7 suppressed CRC growth and enhanced radiosensitivity by up-regulating SMAD4 through sequestering miR-766, providing an insight for the further development of CRC treatment.

title: CircRNA hsa_circ_0070659 predicts poor prognosis and promotes non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) progression via microRNA-377 (miR-377) / Ras-Associated Binding Protein 3C (RAB3C) pathway.
description: Our study revealed a novel signaling pathway that circ_0070659/miR-377/RAB3C axis regulates tumor progression, and it may become a new therapeutic target for NSCLC.

title: Circular ribonucleic acid circ-FADS2 promotes colorectal cancer cell proliferation and invasion by regulating miR-498/S100A16.
description: A study of the molecular mechanism suggests that a circ-FADS2/miR-498/S100A16/AKT signaling cascade may be a potential therapeutic target for the treatment of CRC.

title: Characterization of circSCL38A1 as a novel oncogene in bladder cancer via targeting ILF3/TGF-beta2 signaling axis.
description: Thus, our study revealed an essential role and clinical significance of circSLC38A1 in BC via activating the transcription of TGF-beta2 in an ILF3-dependent manner, extending the understanding of the importance of circRNA-mediated transcriptional regulation in BC metastasis.

title: Circ-ATIC regulates esophageal squamous cell carcinoma growth and metastasis through miR-1294/PBX3 pathway.
description: Collectively, circ-ATIC promoted ESCC proliferation and invasion by regulating miR-1294/PBX3 axis.

title: Exosomal circ-PTPN22 and circ-ADAMTS6 mark T cell exhaustion and neutrophil extracellular traps in Asian intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma.
description: Our results revealed a subgroup of Asian ICC characterized by T cell exhaustion and neutrophil extracellular traps and marked by elevated levels of circ-PTPN22 and circ-ADAMTS6 in tumor tissues and plasma exosomes.

title: Exosomal circ-PTPN22 and circ-ADAMTS6 mark T cell exhaustion and neutrophil extracellular traps in Asian intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma.
description: Our results revealed a subgroup of Asian ICC characterized by T cell exhaustion and neutrophil extracellular traps and marked by elevated levels of circ-PTPN22 and circ-ADAMTS6 in tumor tissues and plasma exosomes.

title: Circ_0044411 silencing protects infantile pneumonia from lipopolysaccharide-induced cell injury by sponging miR-141-3p to inhibit CCL16 expression.
description: Circ_0044411 knockdown promoted cell viability and proliferation, inhibited inflammatory response and apoptosis by regulating miR-141-3p/CCL16 axis, indicating that circ_0044411 might be a potential therapeutic target for IP.

title: circRNA_0067717 promotes paclitaxel resistance in nasopharyngeal carcinoma by acting as a scaffold for TRIM41 and p53.
description: We demonstrate that circRNA_0067717 acts as a scaffold for TRIM41 and p53, enhancing paclitaxel chemoresistance in NPC by promoting TRIM41-induced p53 degradation via ubiquitination.

title: Identification of pathological-related and diagnostic potential circular RNAs in Stanford type A aortic dissection.
description: The 4 key circRNAs, namely circPTGR1 (chr9:114341075-114348445[-]), circNOX4 (chr11:89069012-89106660[-]), circAMN1 (chr12:31854796-31862359[-]) and circUSP3 (chr15:63845913-63855207[+]), demonstrated a high power to discriminate between TAAD and control tissues, suggesting that these molecules stand for a major difference between the tissues at gene regulation level.

title: Identification of pathological-related and diagnostic potential circular RNAs in Stanford type A aortic dissection.
description: The 4 key circRNAs, namely circPTGR1 (chr9:114341075-114348445[-]), circNOX4 (chr11:89069012-89106660[-]), circAMN1 (chr12:31854796-31862359[-]) and circUSP3 (chr15:63845913-63855207[+]), demonstrated a high power to discriminate between TAAD and control tissues, suggesting that these molecules stand for a major difference between the tissues at gene regulation level.

title: Identification of pathological-related and diagnostic potential circular RNAs in Stanford type A aortic dissection.
description: The 4 key circRNAs, namely circPTGR1 (chr9:114341075-114348445[-]), circNOX4 (chr11:89069012-89106660[-]), circAMN1 (chr12:31854796-31862359[-]) and circUSP3 (chr15:63845913-63855207[+]), demonstrated a high power to discriminate between TAAD and control tissues, suggesting that these molecules stand for a major difference between the tissues at gene regulation level.

title: Identification of pathological-related and diagnostic potential circular RNAs in Stanford type A aortic dissection.
description: The 4 key circRNAs, namely circPTGR1 (chr9:114341075-114348445[-]), circNOX4 (chr11:89069012-89106660[-]), circAMN1 (chr12:31854796-31862359[-]) and circUSP3 (chr15:63845913-63855207[+]), demonstrated a high power to discriminate between TAAD and control tissues, suggesting that these molecules stand for a major difference between the tissues at gene regulation level.

title: Hsa_circ_0072765 knockdown inhibits proliferation, activation and migration in transforming growth factor-beta (TGF-beta)-induced hepatic stellate cells (HSCs) by the miR-197-3p/TRPV3 axis.
description: Hsa_circ_0072765 promoted the progression of TGF-beta-treated HSCs by decoying miR-197-3p and upregulating TRPV3.

title: Splicing factor SNRPA associated with microvascular invasion promotes hepatocellular carcinoma metastasis through activating NOTCH1/Snail pathway and is mediated by circSEC62/miR-625-5p axis.
description: Taking these results together, our study identified a novel regulatory mechanism among SNRPA, miR-625-5p, circSEC62 and the NOTCH1/Snail pathway in HCC, which promoted metastasis of HCC and may provide effective suggestions for improving the prognosis of HCC patients with metastasis.

title: Hsa_circ_0119412 Contributes to Development of Retinoblastoma by Targeting miR-186-5p/ELK4 Axis.
description: Circ_0119412 was found to be upregulated in RB, and could accelerate the progression of RB via the miR-186-5p/ELK4 axis, indicating circ_0119412 may serve a promising clinical therapeutic target of RB.

title: Circ-calm4 regulates hypoxia-induced pulmonary artery smooth muscle autophagy by binding Purb.
disease_details: hypoxia-induced pulmonary artery smooth muscle autophagy
description: Overall, our results confirm that the circ-calm4/Purb/Beclin1 signal axis is involved in the occurrence of hypoxia-induced PASMCs autophagy, and the novel regulatory mechanisms and signals transduction pathways in PASMC autophagy induced by hypoxia.

title: Circular hsa_circ_0020377 regulates KLF7 by targeting miR-194-5p to facilitate tumor cell malignant behaviors and glycolysis in oral squamous cell carcinoma progression.
description: These results broaden our insights regarding the regulation of OSCC progression via circRNA and act as a reference for future clinical studies in OSCC diagnosis and treatment.

title: FTO-dependent m(6)A modification of Plpp3 in circSCMH1-regulated vascular repair and functional recovery following stroke.
description: Our data demonstrate that circSCMH1 enhances vascular repair via FTO-regulated m(6)A methylation after stroke, providing insights into the mechanism of circSCMH1 in promoting stroke recovery.

title: Circular RNA PVT1 Regulates Cell Proliferation, Migration, and Apoptosis by Stabilizing c-Myc and Downstream Target CXCR4 Expression in Acute Myeloid Leukemia.
description: Our findings showed that circPVT1 was highly expressed in AML patients and was related to shorter OS and RFS. CircPVT1 may exert an oncogenic effect in THP-1 cells by stabilizing c-Myc protein expression and downstream target CXCR4 expression.

title: circRNA-SMO upregulates CEP85 to promote proliferation and migration of glioblastoma via sponging miR-326.
description: CircRNA-SMO sponges miR-326 to promote glioblastoma proliferation and migration by upregulating CEP85 expression. This study clarified the role of circRNA-SMO in the development of glioblastoma, providing novel insights for its treatment.

title: Dexmedetomidine promotes ferroptotic cell death in gastric cancer via hsa_circ_0008035/miR-302a/E2F7 axis.
description: Taken together, DEX mediated ferroptotic cell death in GC through regulating the circ0008035/miR-302a/E2F7 axis, suggesting a feasible therapy option for GC.

title: CircRNA Circ_0000118 Regulates Malignancy of Cervical Cancer Cells by Regulating miR-211-5p/miR-377-3p/AKT2 Axis.
description: Our study suggested that circ_0000118 functions as an oncogenic factor in progression of CC by maintaining AKT2 level through targeting miR-211-5p and miR-377-3p as a ceRNA (competitive endogenous RNA), which provides novel therapeutic target in the management of CC.

title: Exosome-transmitted circIFNGR2 Modulates Ovarian Cancer Metastasis via miR-378/ST5 Axis.
description: Our study revealed a previously unknown regulatory pathway whereby CAFs-derived exosomes delivered circIFNGR2 and inhibited the malignant progression of OVCA by circIFNGR2/miR-378/ST5 axis.

title: Human umbilical cord mesenchymal stem cells-derived exosomal circDLGAP4 promotes angiogenesis after cerebral ischemia-reperfusion injury by regulating miR-320/KLF5 axis.
description: hUC-MSCs-Exos-derived circDLGAP4 reduced cerebrovascular injury by regulating miR-320/KLF5 signaling. These results provide a stem cell-based approach to treat CIRI.

title: Circular RNA SMARCA5 inhibits cholangiocarcinoma via microRNA-95-3p/tumor necrosis factor receptor associated factor 3 axis.
description: CircRNA SMARCA5 is involved in CHOL development by interosculating miRNA-95-3p/TRAF3 axis and may become a novel approach for treating CHOL.

title: Circ_0091537 promotes gefitinib chemoresistance in non-small cell lung cancer by mediating the miR-520h/YAP1 network.
description: Circ_0091537 strengthens gefitinib chemoresistance to promote NSCLC progression by mediating the miR-520h/YAP1 network, suggesting that circ_0091537 may be a key indicator in resistance to treatment of NSCLC.

title: Circular RNA circ_0005667 promotes cisplatin resistance of endometrial carcinoma cells by regulating IGF2BP1 through miR-145-5p.
description: Circ_0005667 enhanced DDP resistance in EC by elevating IGF2BP1 through sponging miR-145-5p.

title: Circular RNA circ_0000212 accelerates cervical cancer progression by acting as a miR-625-5p sponge to upregulate PTP4A1.
description: circ_0000212 acted as an oncogene in cervical cancer progression, and knockdown of circ_0000212 repressed cervical cancer development by increasing miR-625-5p and decreasing PTP4A1.

title: CircSETDB1 contributes to paclitaxel resistance of ovarian cancer cells by sponging miR-508-3p and regulating ABCC1 expression.
description: In conclusion, circSETDB1 regulated Ptx resistance of ovarian cancer by targeting miR-508-3p/ ABCC1 axis.

title: Circ_0058063 regulates the development of esophageal cancer through miR-377-3p/HOXA1 axis.
description: Our study found that circ_0058063 could regulate the expression of HOXA1 by targeting miR-377-3p, thereby affecting the progress of esophageal cancer.

title: Circular RNA circ_0003028 regulates cell development through modulating miR-498/ornithine decarboxylase 1 axis in hepatocellular carcinoma.
description: In brief, the results demonstrated that circ_0003028 exerted tumourigenicity roles via miR-498/ODC1 signaling axis, providing a promising biomarker and therapeutic target for HCC.

title: CircBNC2 affects epithelial ovarian cancer progression through the miR-223-3p/ LARP4 axis.
description: Overexpression of circBNC2 decreased proliferation, migration, and invasion of EOC cells by regulating the miR-223-3p/ LARP4 axis, suggesting that circBNC2/miR-223-3p/ LARP4 axis may be a potential regulatory mechanism for the treatment of EOC.

title: CircRNA circ_POLA2 overexpression suppresses cell apoptosis by downregulating PTEN in glioblastoma.
description: Circ_POLA2 is overexpressed in MCL and might promote GBM cell apoptosis through downregulating PTEN.

title: Knockdown of circ-PIP5K1A overcomes resistance to cisplatin in ovarian cancer by miR-942-5p/NFIB axis.
description: Besides that, circ-PIP5K1A was packaged into exosomes and exosomal circ-SKA3 could mediate intercellular communication between OC cells. These findings provided a promising therapeutic target for OC.

title: circIPO7 dissociates caprin-1 from ribosomes and inhibits gastric cancer cell proliferation by suppressing EGFR and mTOR.
description: Thus, the complex containing overexpressed circIPO7 blocked the caprin-1-G3BP1 interaction and dissociated caprin-1 and its target mRNAs (EGFR and mTOR) from ribosomes, resulting in their translational inhibition, followed by PI3K/AKT/mTOR pathway inactivation.

title: Circular RNA circ_0026218 Suppressed Atherosclerosis Progression via miR-338-3p/SIRT6 Axis.
description: Collectively, circ_0026218 upregulates SIRT6 expression through decoying miR-338-3p, thereby inhibiting ox-LDL-initiated injury of HUVECs. circ_0026218 is involved in the pathogenesis of AS.

title: Investigation of the clinicopathological and prognostic role of circMTO1 in multiple cancers.
description: The low expression of circMTO1 may predict big tumor size, poor differentiation and worse outcome of cancer, presenting that circMTO1 may be a useful biomarker for prognosis of tumors.

title: circ_0013613 Promotes the recovery of spinal cord injury by regulating mir-370-3p/caspase1 to regulate neuronal pyroptosis.
description: circ_0013613 can promote the recovery of SCI by regulating miR-370-3p/CASP1 to mediate neuronal pyroptosis.

title: Circ_0003340 regulates the expression of ENAH to affect the development of esophageal cancer through miR-874-3p.
description: The data demonstrated that circ_0003340 promoted the progression of esophageal cancer through miR-874-3p/ENAH axis, which might provide novel therapeutic targets for esophageal cancer intervention.

title: Circ_0000285 regulates nasopharyngeal carcinoma progression through miR-1278/FNDC3B axis.
description: Circ_0000285 upregulates FNDC3B expression by adsorbing miR-1278 to promote NPC development.

title: CircKRT14 upregulates E2F3 by interacting with miR-1256 to act as an oncogenic factor in esophageal cancer.
description: These results uncovered that circKRT14 up-regulated the expression of E2F3 and promoted the malignant development of EC through sponging miR-1256.

title: Circular RNA 0001789 sponges miR-140-3p and regulates PAK2 to promote the progression of gastric cancer.
description: The present data suggested that the upregulation of circ_0001789 was associated with the progression of GC and with poor prognosis in patients with GC, and that miR-140-3p/PAK2 served as the downstream axis to mediate the oncogenic effect of circ_0001789.

title: circANKRD28 inhibits cisplatin resistance in non-small-cell lung cancer through the miR-221-3p/SOCS3 axis.
description: The present study revealed the regulatory effects and molecular mechanism of circANKRD28 on the development and cisplatin resistance in NSCLC, which may provide experimental basis and theoretical support to identify new targets for therapy of DDP resistance in NSCLC.
